{"id": "142814", "revid": "5064773", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=142814", "title": "Friede", "text": ""}
{"id": "143028", "revid": "51254358", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=143028", "title": "Friede's Great Scythe", "text": "Friede's Great Scythe (\u30d5\u30ea\u30fc\u30c7\u306e\u5927\u938c) is a &lt;a href=\"Boss%20Soul%20Items%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;soul-transposed&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Reapers%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;reaper&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;: &lt;a href=\"Ashes%20of%20Ariandel\"&gt;Ashes of Ariandel&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nObtained by transposing\u00a0the &lt;a href=\"Soul%20of%20Sister%20Friede\"&gt;Soul of Sister Friede&lt;/a&gt; with &lt;a href=\"Ludleth%20of%20Courland\"&gt;Ludleth of Courland&lt;/a&gt; for 10,000 &lt;a href=\"Soul%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;souls&lt;/a&gt;.\nCharacteristics.\nWhereas most reapers are designed to keep foes at arm's length away, Friede's Great Scythe breaks the mold by allowing its wielder to employ an aggressive playstyle, making it one of the most unique weapons in the game.\nUnlike most reapers, which do full damage when hitting the target with the blade and incur a damage penalty when the target is inside of its arc, Friede's Great Scythe instead does full damage at any range and inflicts increased damage when striking the target at its maximum reach. Additionally, the blade is imbued with &lt;a href=\"Frost\"&gt;Frost&lt;/a&gt;, making it the only reaper in the game that builds up Frostbite without having to buff it, as well as one of only four weapons in the game with innate Frost build-up on all of its attacks.\nThese advantages do not come without drawbacks, however. In order to wield the weapon, players must first invest a non-negligible amount of levels in &lt;a href=\"Faith%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Faith&lt;/a&gt;, which makes the weapon more difficult to build for. Additionally, despite what is listed in the weapon's information, with its normal moveset it cannot inflict &lt;a href=\"Magic%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Magic&lt;/a&gt; damage at all. As such, in regular situations this reaper is little different from the &lt;a href=\"Pontiff%20Knight%20Great%20Scythe\"&gt;Pontiff Knight Great Scythe&lt;/a&gt;.\nHowever, all of this changes when utilizing the weapon's &lt;a href=\"skill\"&gt;skill&lt;/a&gt;, which is what truly sets this weapon apart from its peers. Entering the skill stance brings the support scythe to bear in the off-hand, allowing the completed weapon system to function like &lt;a href=\"Paired%20Weapons\"&gt;paired weapons&lt;/a&gt;. The primary scythe will inflict purely physical damage, &lt;a href=\"Parameter%20Bonus%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;scaling&lt;/a&gt; primarily with the wielder's &lt;a href=\"Dexterity%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Dexterity&lt;/a&gt;, while the conjured support scythe will inflict purely Magic damage, scaling purely with the wielder's &lt;a href=\"Intelligence%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Intelligence&lt;/a&gt;. While in this stance, the wielder gains &lt;a href=\"Hyper%20Armor\"&gt;Hyper Armor&lt;/a&gt; on all attacks, allowing them to take to the offensive against foes.\nIn the right hands, Friede's Great Scythe is a powerful and well-balanced weapon that combines range, damage, Frostbite buildup and strong aggressive options into a single package. Care must be taken to utilize it properly, however, as any mistakes made using the weapon can have disastrous consequences.\nUpgrades.\n&lt;br&gt;\nDescription.\n&lt;tabber&gt;Official translation=\n&lt;/tabber&gt;"}
{"id": "99308", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=99308", "title": "Frigid Outskirts", "text": "The\u00a0Frigid Outskirts is a &lt;a href=\"Locations%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;location&lt;/a&gt; in . It is a bleak, arctic wasteland plagued by constant blizzards and inhabited by dangerous creatures.\nOverview.\nThe location can only be accessed after unlocking the door in front of the &lt;a href=\"Expulsion%20Chamber\"&gt;Expulsion Chamber&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Bonfire%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;bonfire&lt;/a&gt; using the &lt;a href=\"Garrison%20Ward%20Key\"&gt;Garrison Ward Key&lt;/a&gt;. Inside is a coffin that can be used to slide down the icy slopes and into the Frigid Outskirts. Once there, severe blizzards will begin to cycle every few moments, which inhibits the player's vision and cause &lt;a href=\"Ice%20Stallion\"&gt;Ice Stallion&lt;/a&gt;s to spawn at random.\nThe goal is to reach the dwelling of &lt;a href=\"Lud%20and%20Zallen\"&gt;Lud and Zallen&lt;/a&gt;, the &lt;a href=\"Ivory%20King\"&gt;king's&lt;/a&gt; pets, who are found in a pit some distance away. Along the way are various enemies who will attack and dilapidated buildings that contain loot.\nOnce at the outskirts, one cannot return to &lt;a href=\"Frozen%20Eleum%20Loyce\"&gt;Frozen Eleum Loyce&lt;/a&gt; by normal means. The player must use a warping &lt;a href=\"Homeward%20Bone%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;item&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Homeward%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;spell&lt;/a&gt;, die or make use of the warp point provided after killing the area bosses."}
{"id": "9959", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=9959", "title": "Frog-Ray", "text": "Frog-Rays are &lt;a href=\"enemies\"&gt;enemies&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\".\nLocation.\nFrog-Rays are located in a specific area of\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Darkroot%20Garden\"&gt;Darkroot Garden&lt;/a&gt;, beyond the &lt;a href=\"Possessed%20Tree\"&gt;Possessed Tree&lt;/a&gt;s.\nCharacteristics.\nThe Frog-Rays are red, black spotted amphibious creatures. Rarely are they threatening, but will occasionally attempt to ambush the player.\nEnemy information.\nDrops.\nNote: Frog-Ray corpses will occasionally glitch through the world geometry, making collecting their drops impossible."}
