{"id": "89601", "revid": "51254358", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=89601", "title": "Galib, God of Disease", "text": "Galib, God of Disease is a in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nLore.\nGalib was worshiped by the &lt;a href=\"Leydia%20Witch\"&gt;Leydia apostles&lt;/a&gt; as the \"&lt;a href=\"Gods\"&gt;god of disease&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAfter the witches were welcomed into the &lt;a href=\"Undead%20Crypt\"&gt;Undead Crypt&lt;/a&gt; and ended up residing beside the Fenito, they gained access to their power of death and disease. However at a certain point the Leydia Witches grew conceived and began to manipulate both the onset and curing of disease, making themselves the effective gatekeepers of the crypt, implying their desires to control the powers of their god and administer the crypt."}
{"id": "140214", "revid": "28000958", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=140214", "title": "Galvanize", "text": "Galvanize is a &lt;a href=\"skill\"&gt;skill&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\".\n&lt;tabber&gt;Pickaxe=\n&lt;/tabber&gt;\nUsage.\nCampaign.\nGalvanize is a simple but effective Skill; casting before entering a boss fog, a room full of enemies, or, if you have the FP, just constantly keeping it up gives a good boost to your Stamina regeneration rate, and if paired with the Chloranthy Ring, Green Blossoms, or the Grass Crest Shield, can provide an incredibly effective Stamina boost.\nOnline gameplay.\nVery helpful to set up right before a duel, or before finding the Host if invading; or, as a phantom, can be used in essentially the same way as it can be in the Campaign."}
