{"id": "163427", "revid": "5064773", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=163427", "title": "Garl Vinland", "text": "Garl Vinland is a character from \"\". He originally hailed from the 2009 &lt;a href=\"From%20Software\"&gt;From Software&lt;/a&gt; game &lt;a href=\"Demon%27s%20Souls\"&gt;Demon's Souls&lt;/a&gt; as an enemy.\nIn \"Dark Souls\".\nGarl appears to be a part of &lt;a href=\"Gwyn%2C%20Lord%20of%20Cinder\"&gt;Gwyn's&lt;/a&gt; legion of &lt;a href=\"Silver%20Knight\"&gt;Silver Knight&lt;/a&gt;s under the leadership of &lt;a href=\"Silver%20Knight%20Arkon\"&gt;Silver Knight Arkon&lt;/a&gt;. Under the orders of Gwyn, Arkon leads a battalion of Silver Knights into the city of &lt;a href=\"Lost%20Izalith\"&gt;Lost Izalith&lt;/a&gt; to investigate the God's suspicion of &lt;a href=\"dark\"&gt;dark&lt;/a&gt; magic and &lt;a href=\"Demon\"&gt;Demon&lt;/a&gt;s. Knight Garl is amongst Arkon and is seen alongside the knights fighting a group of &lt;a href=\"Taurus%20Demon\"&gt;Taurus Demon&lt;/a&gt;. Though Garl frets that there is too many demons to battle, Arkon soon sends the horde into a retreat. Though Garl remarks that the demons are fleeing, Arkon corrects him by stating that \"demons do not flee, they simply return to the shadow whence they came.\"\nAs Arkon and his knights pursue a &lt;a href=\"Demon%20Cleric\"&gt;Demon Cleric&lt;/a&gt;, Garl remarks that the demons flee from their lit torches. As they turn a corner, however, the demon, standing in front of the &lt;a href=\"Bed%20of%20Chaos\"&gt;Bed of Chaos&lt;/a&gt; retorts \"hide from fire? Foolish metal giant. We are flame.\" Garl is suddenly consumed by the flame and disintegrates. With Arkon's dismay, the demon reassures him that \"thy friend is still of this world, only changed\".\n\"Demon's Souls\" lore.\nGarl Vinland is the loyal companion and bodyguard of &lt;a href=\"w%3Ac%3Ademonssouls%3AMaiden%20Astraea\"&gt;Maiden Astraea&lt;/a&gt;. He is also the brother to &lt;a href=\"w%3Ac%3Ademonssouls%3ASelen%20Vinland\"&gt;Selen Vinland&lt;/a&gt; and a member of the Vinland family. Astraea departed into the &lt;a href=\"w%3Ac%3Ademonssouls%3AValley%20of%20Defilement\"&gt;Valley of Defilement&lt;/a&gt; to tend to the suffering and Garl followed, serving as her devoted protector. The two have resided there since, with Garl defending Astraea from any unwanted invaders. Garl, alongside Astraea, are soon slain by a warrior collecting the souls of demons."}
