{"id": "3145", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3145", "title": "Gauntlets", "text": "Gauntlets are a type of &lt;a href=\"Weapons%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;weapon&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\".\nOverview.\nGauntlets have by far the shortest range of all the &lt;a href=\"Weapon%20Types%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;weapon types&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\", which means they require getting up close and personal with the &lt;a href=\"enemy\"&gt;enemy&lt;/a&gt;. They make up for their limited range with their speed. They can attack extremely fast, being able to create long chains of relentless attacks as long as the player's &lt;a href=\"stamina\"&gt;stamina&lt;/a&gt; holds out. Gauntlets are one of the few weapon classes that have the ability to &lt;a href=\"parry\"&gt;parry&lt;/a&gt; when used in the left hand.\nWith a gauntlet weapon (including fists) equipped in the right hand, the kick animation is changed - rather than a heel kick, the character strikes with the knee. This does not seem to affect the function or range of the kick.\nGauntlets have the unique ability that their weak attack can not be deflected. This can allow players to use the rapid combos inherent to gauntlets against enemies with &lt;a href=\"shields\"&gt;shields&lt;/a&gt;, quickly draining their stamina and breaking their block. In &lt;a href=\"PvP\"&gt;PvP&lt;/a&gt; this tactic is ill-advised, as it creates a predictable string of attacks that the opponent will easily be able to parry.\nWearing\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Gauntlets%20of%20Thorns\"&gt;Gauntlets of Thorns&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0will increase the damage dealt by gauntlets.\nGauntlets.\n&lt;tabber&gt;\nDetailed=\nCondensed=\nUpgraded=\n&lt;/tabber&gt;"}
