{"id": "11892", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=11892", "title": "Giant", "text": " \nGiants are both a respawning and non-respawning in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\".\nDescription.\nGigantic humanoids that perform various tasks in &lt;a href=\"Sen%27s%20Fortress\"&gt;Sen's Fortress&lt;/a&gt;. They look identical to the &lt;a href=\"Giant%20Blacksmith\"&gt;Giant Blacksmith&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0and have similar attacks.\nAlthough they share the same name, they share only a few similarities with the &lt;a href=\"Giant%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Giants&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nLocation.\nEncountered at various points in &lt;a href=\"Sen%27s%20Fortress\"&gt;Sen's Fortress&lt;/a&gt;.\nStrategy.\nWhen fighting a giant, hack away at the legs and dodge any of the giants attacks. This is simple, as their attacks are quite slow. After continuing this rhythm for a short while, eventually the giant will flail around angrily and stomp. This is fairly easy to block with a medium shield and easier to dodge. After the giant has finished its rampage it will crouch down leaving itself defenseless. This is the time that the player should exhaust their entire firepower on the giant.\nA safe, although potentially expensive, strategy is to use the &lt;a href=\"Toxic%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;Toxic&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Negative%20Status%20Effects\"&gt;status&lt;/a&gt; to kill the Giants. Throwing two &lt;a href=\"Dung%20Pie\"&gt;Dung Pie&lt;/a&gt;s at a Giant is enough to apply the effect in NG. After the Toxin takes effect, the player must only wait until the Giant dies."}
