{"id": "68086", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=68086", "title": "Giant Basilisk", "text": "Giant Basilisks (also known as Great Basilisks) are in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nDescription.\nIt has a green tone but is otherwise similar in appearance to a regular &lt;a href=\"Basilisk%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Basilisk&lt;/a&gt;. It is also considerably larger and has far more HP than the normal variety."}
{"id": "2933", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=2933", "title": "Giant Blacksmith", "text": "The Giant Blacksmith is a &lt;a href=\"character\"&gt;character&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\". A simple but friendly being, the Giant Blacksmith offers players unique &lt;a href=\"Weapons%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;weapon&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Upgrade%20Paths\"&gt;upgrades&lt;/a&gt;. He is voiced by , who also voiced &lt;a href=\"Solaire%20of%20Astora\"&gt;Solaire of Astora&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Vamos\"&gt;Vamos&lt;/a&gt;.\nLocation.\nIn &lt;a href=\"Anor%20Londo\"&gt;Anor Londo&lt;/a&gt; after rotating the bridge between the &lt;a href=\"Bell%20Gargoyles\"&gt;Bell Gargoyles&lt;/a&gt;, ascend some steps towards a large building guarded by two &lt;a href=\"Sentinel\"&gt;Sentinel&lt;/a&gt;s and several &lt;a href=\"Batwing%20Demon\"&gt;Batwing Demon&lt;/a&gt;s. The door on the left leads towards the Giant Blacksmith, but initially it is locked and can only be opened from the other side, which can be accessed only after clearing most of Anor Londo.\nRemember to open the locked door leading back to the Sentinels, so it is easier to access the blacksmith from the other &lt;a href=\"Bonfire%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;bonfire&lt;/a&gt;.\nPlot.\nThe Giant Blacksmith sells a variety of useful &lt;a href=\"upgrade%20materials\"&gt;upgrade materials&lt;/a&gt; as well as weapons and &lt;a href=\"Armor%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;armor&lt;/a&gt;, and is the only blacksmith that can upgrade down the &lt;a href=\"Lightning%20%28upgrade%20path%29\"&gt;lightning path&lt;/a&gt; (by default), the &lt;a href=\"Crystal%20%28upgrade%20path%29\"&gt;crystal path&lt;/a&gt; (after he receives the &lt;a href=\"Crystal%20Ember\"&gt;Crystal Ember&lt;/a&gt;), and make &lt;a href=\"Boss%20Soul%20Weapons\"&gt;weapons&lt;/a&gt; from the &lt;a href=\"Boss%20Souls\"&gt;souls of bosses&lt;/a&gt;. Many of the things he sells are exclusive only to him, such as &lt;a href=\"Twinkling%20Titanite\"&gt;Twinkling Titanite&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Dragonslayer%20Arrow\"&gt;Dragonslayer Arrow&lt;/a&gt;s.\nLore.\nFrom the Giant Blacksmith's dialogue, it can be hinted that he had resided in Anor Londo before most of its denizens left. It does not mention much other than that, though.\nThe Giant Blacksmith had a friendly relationship with &lt;a href=\"Hawkeye%20Gough\"&gt;Hawkeye Gough&lt;/a&gt;. This is hinted at the &lt;a href=\"Hawk%20Ring\"&gt;Hawk Ring&lt;/a&gt; found in a chest next to him, as well as Hawkeye Gough's friendly remarks about the Giant Blacksmith.\nHis corpse is found in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\" in &lt;a href=\"Anor%20Londo%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Anor Londo&lt;/a&gt;, on the same spot he used to reside. The &lt;a href=\"Giant%27s%20Coal\"&gt;Giant's Coal&lt;/a&gt; is found at his body.\n&lt;a href=\"Andre%20of%20Astora\"&gt;Andre of Astora&lt;/a&gt; apparently knew him, as he says \"I miss the old bugger, I do.\" when given the Giant's Coal. He also assumes the Giant Blacksmith already died a long time ago.\nStrategy.\nIt is not recommended to attack him for he is very strong and the services he offers cannot be replaced. However, he is the only character to drop the &lt;a href=\"Blacksmith%20Giant%20Hammer\"&gt;Blacksmith Giant Hammer&lt;/a&gt;, and so must be defeated for completionists. He has the standard &lt;a href=\"Giant\"&gt;Giant&lt;/a&gt; moveset.\nNotes.\nLocated in the corner next to him is a chest containing the &lt;a href=\"Hawk%20Ring\"&gt;Hawk Ring&lt;/a&gt;. It is not necessary to kill him to access it, just &lt;a href=\"roll\"&gt;roll&lt;/a&gt; right behind him."}
{"id": "11192", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=11192", "title": "Giant Clam", "text": "Giant Clams, also known as Man-Eater Shells, are &lt;a href=\"enemies\"&gt;enemies&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\".\nDescription.\nThey have the appearance of giant clams with red spikes sticking out of their upper valve. Their mouths are littered with bluish skulls that seem crystallized.\nWhile not particularly powerful, Giant Clams have plenty of attacks performed in quick succession that can knock the player off their feet, effectively &lt;a href=\"stun-lock\"&gt;stun-lock&lt;/a&gt;ing the player to &lt;a href=\"death\"&gt;death&lt;/a&gt;. This becomes much more evident when they attack in groups."}
