{"id": "15291", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=15291", "title": "Giant Crow", "text": "The Giant Crow is a minor in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\" and can be found in &lt;a href=\"Firelink%20Shrine\"&gt;Firelink Shrine&lt;/a&gt; throughout all of the story.\nPlot.\nThe Giant Crow is a mysterious entity that transports the &lt;a href=\"Chosen%20Undead\"&gt;Chosen Undead&lt;/a&gt; from the end of the &lt;a href=\"Undead%20Asylum\"&gt;Undead Asylum&lt;/a&gt; to &lt;a href=\"Firelink%20Shrine\"&gt;Firelink Shrine&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Lordran\"&gt;Lordran&lt;/a&gt;.\nOnce the elevator is operated in the &lt;a href=\"Undead%20Parish\"&gt;Undead Parish&lt;/a&gt; Church it is possible to revisit the Undead Asylum by climbing to the top of the ruins in Firelink Shrine to the Giant Crow's nest and curling up into a ball. The Giant Crow will then bring the Chosen Undead onto another nest on the cliff where the player was first carried off from in the Undead Asylum.\nBeyond this, no further interaction can be made with the Crow.\nThe crow can actually be shot at but will fly away upon reaching half health"}
{"id": "150535", "revid": "5064773", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=150535", "title": "Giant Door Greatshield", "text": ""}
{"id": "150126", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=150126", "title": "Giant Door Shield", "text": "The Giant Door Shield is a &lt;a href=\"Paired%20Weapons\"&gt;paired&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Greatshields%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;greatshield&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;: &lt;a href=\"The%20Ringed%20City\"&gt;The Ringed City&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nFound in &lt;a href=\"The%20Dreg%20Heap\"&gt;The Dreg Heap&lt;/a&gt;. Shortly past the &lt;a href=\"Earthen%20Peak%20Ruins\"&gt;Earthen Peak Ruins&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Bonfire%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;bonfire&lt;/a&gt;, an &lt;a href=\"Angel\"&gt;Angel&lt;/a&gt; and several &lt;a href=\"Thrall\"&gt;Thrall&lt;/a&gt;s guard an open area. The Giant Door Shields can be found at the end of a path leading to the bottom of a cliff, where another Thrall guards it.\nCharacteristics.\nPerhaps the most unconventional weapon in \"Dark Souls III\", the Giant Door Shields are towering titans that grant strong defensive power with its attacks.\nWhile classified as paired greatshields, these shields function more akin to &lt;a href=\"Fists%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;fist&lt;/a&gt; weapons, albeit significantly slower. The greatshields perform bashing attacks using the shields as weapons. Unlike normal shields that have limited attacks to back their strictly defensive purpose, the Giant Door Shields possess a robust if short-ranged moveset that allows the wielder to fight offensively with a truly unique playstyle.\nWhat makes the Giant Door Shields so powerful is their ability to utilize block frames (similar to &lt;a href=\"Valorheart\"&gt;Valorheart&lt;/a&gt;) and &lt;a href=\"Hyper%20Armor\"&gt;Hyper Armor&lt;/a&gt; during attacks, which also cannot be &lt;a href=\"Parry%20and%20Riposte%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;parried&lt;/a&gt; under any circumstances due to their nature as ultra weapons. This means that by taking advantage of &lt;a href=\"Poise%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Poise&lt;/a&gt;, the Giant Door Shields are extremely difficult to interrupt once in motion, and most physical attacks will be easily shrugged off by the weapon's block frames.\nOf course, all these strengths come at a steep price. The Door Shields have an extremely high &lt;a href=\"Strength%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Strength&lt;/a&gt; requirement, demand heavy &lt;a href=\"Vitality%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Vitality&lt;/a&gt; investment to support their weight, and consume extreme amounts of &lt;a href=\"Stamina%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;stamina&lt;/a&gt; to attack and to block, forcing the wielder to invest in &lt;a href=\"Endurance%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Endurance&lt;/a&gt;. As well, their wooden nature makes them quite vulnerable to &lt;a href=\"Fire%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Fire&lt;/a&gt; damage, which can only be protected against by utilizing its &lt;a href=\"skill\"&gt;skill&lt;/a&gt;.\nUpgrades.\nReinforced with &lt;a href=\"Upgrade%20Materials%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Titanite&lt;/a&gt;."}
