{"id": "150222", "revid": "51254358", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=150222", "title": "Giant Fly", "text": "Giant Flies are in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;: &lt;a href=\"Ashes%20of%20Ariandel\"&gt;Ashes of Ariandel&lt;/a&gt;\".\nDescription.\nGiant Flies are heavily enlarged flies with big red eyes and human-like arms. They are usually found in large numbers.\nLocations.\n&lt;a href=\"Painted%20World%20of%20Ariandel\"&gt;Painted World of Ariandel&lt;/a&gt; - one is met near first bonfire guarding a &lt;a href=\"Poison%20Gem\"&gt;Poison Gem&lt;/a&gt;. Next there are 3 of them in &lt;a href=\"Corvian%20Settlement\"&gt;Corvian Settlement&lt;/a&gt;. A very large number can be found under &lt;a href=\"Ariandel%20Chapel\"&gt;Ariandel Chapel&lt;/a&gt;, in the basement.\nStrategy.\nTheir attacks deal &lt;a href=\"physical%20damage\"&gt;physical damage&lt;/a&gt;, and they have a flying grab attack and a vomit attack that will infect the player with Maggots (like &lt;a href=\"Corpse%20Grub\"&gt;Corpse Grub&lt;/a&gt;). Therefore, while facing them it is recommended to bring &lt;a href=\"Bloodred%20Moss%20Clump%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Bloodred Moss Clumps&lt;/a&gt; or a &lt;a href=\"Torch%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;torch&lt;/a&gt;. \nWhen encountered in the rotting basement of the Ariandel Chapel, several of the Giant Flies will likely fly at the player with great speed. Evading is the best way to avoid these attacks, as the player can become overwhelmed by sheer numbers if they try to attack the flies. One should be careful not to let themselves be cornered by them, as they can completely decimate one's HP if they attack all at once."}
