{"id": "3259", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3259", "title": "Giant Undead Rat", "text": "The Giant Undead Rat is a &lt;a href=\"miniboss\"&gt;miniboss&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\".\nLocation.\nThe Giant Rat can be found in the &lt;a href=\"Depths\"&gt;Depths&lt;/a&gt; around halfway through the sewer area. It can also be reached from an alternate path by dropping down a hole in the floor behind the first &lt;a href=\"Butcher\"&gt;Butcher&lt;/a&gt;.\nDescription.\nA much larger, more powerful, non-respawning version of the &lt;a href=\"Undead%20Rat\"&gt;Undead Rat&lt;/a&gt;.\nStrategy.\nThe Giant Undead Rat can easily &lt;a href=\"stagger\"&gt;stagger&lt;/a&gt; low &lt;a href=\"Poise%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;poise&lt;/a&gt; players if they are not careful, but is also susceptible to &lt;a href=\"Bleed%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;Bleed&lt;/a&gt; and is weaker to &lt;a href=\"Magic%20%28damage%20type%29\"&gt;Magic&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Fire%20%28damage%20type%29\"&gt;Fire&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Lightning%20%28damage%20type%29\"&gt;Lightning&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Slash\"&gt;Slash&lt;/a&gt; attacks. Also, If the player reaches the Giant Undead Rat via the hidden passageway near the first &lt;a href=\"Butcher\"&gt;Butcher&lt;/a&gt;, it can be killed from above with ranged or &lt;a href=\"Plunging%20Attack%23Dark%20Souls\"&gt;plunging attacks&lt;/a&gt;.\nIt can also be killed from afar using a bow on the bridge leading to the &lt;a href=\"Bonfire%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;bonfire&lt;/a&gt; by shooting &lt;a href=\"Arrow\"&gt;arrows&lt;/a&gt; through the grate.\u00a0"}
{"id": "55891", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=55891", "title": "Giant Warrior Club", "text": "The Giant Warrior Club\u00a0is a &lt;a href=\"Great%20Hammers%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;great hammer&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nThe Giant Warrior Club can be found in the &lt;a href=\"Memory%20of%20Vammar\"&gt;Memory of Vammar&lt;/a&gt;, located on a corpse to the right, behind the elite giant before you go into a tower.\nCharacteristics.\nFully upgraded, the Giant Warrior Club ties with the &lt;a href=\"Malformed%20Skull\"&gt;Malformed Skull&lt;/a&gt; for the weapon with the highest &lt;a href=\"physical\"&gt;physical&lt;/a&gt; attack rating in \"Dark Souls II\", reaching a maximum of 520 damage. Ultimately, the Warrior Club hits harder than the Malformed Skull, as the former has an A &lt;a href=\"Parameter%20Bonus%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;scaling&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Strength%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Strength&lt;/a&gt;, whereas the latter has no attribute scaling bonuses. The base damage of the Giant Warrior Club can be further increased through a &lt;a href=\"Raw\"&gt;Raw&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"infusion\"&gt;infusion&lt;/a&gt;, to reach a maximum of 598 damage, but severely lowering the Strength scaling bonus to D.\nThe weapon also has the highest Strength requirement in the base game to wield one-handed, at 60 Strength. However, the &lt;a href=\"Smelter%20Hammer\"&gt;Smelter Hammer&lt;/a&gt; from the DLC is higher, at 70 Strength. It is also the second &lt;a href=\"Weight\"&gt;heaviest&lt;/a&gt; weapon by a margin of 5 units, being outweighed by the Smelter Hammer.\nThe Giant Warrior Club uses regular &lt;a href=\"Titanite%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Titanite&lt;/a&gt; to upgrade."}
