{"id": "178339", "revid": "51254358", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=178339", "title": "Giants (Lore)", "text": " \nThe Giants are a in the \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\" series. \nDescription.\nGiants are a race of humanoid creatures. They are physically distinguished by a tall, powerful body, long arms, short, stubby legs and a small head. Although the workers/slaves express themselves in simple sentences, the giants have proven to be able to easily understand human language, converse and produce refined objects, demonstrating a normal level of intelligence comparable to that of other advanced races. Depending on their roles they wear different clothes. The Judicators wear a long black robe that covers them from neck to toe, the Sentinels wear heavy golden iron armor with decorated plates or white drapes, the giants who appear to be workers or slaves wear chain mail reinforced by metal plates.\nLore.\n&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;.\nAlthough the history of the giant race is completely shrouded in mystery, they have been strongly connected to the &lt;a href=\"Gods\"&gt;Gods&lt;/a&gt; of &lt;a href=\"Anor%20Londo\"&gt;Anor Londo&lt;/a&gt; since the times of their War against the &lt;a href=\"Dragon\"&gt;Archdragons&lt;/a&gt;. The giant &lt;a href=\"Hawkeye%20Gough\"&gt;Hawkeye Gough&lt;/a&gt; led a group of giants known as the Greatarchers Dragonslayers alongside Lord Gwyn's &lt;a href=\"Silver%20Knight\"&gt;Silver Knight&lt;/a&gt;s. These giants represented the archers who had to fight the high-flying dragons from afar and employed &lt;a href=\"Dragonslayer%20Greatbow\"&gt;immense bows&lt;/a&gt; that had to be anchored to the ground when fired and employed &lt;a href=\"Dragonslayer%20Arrow\"&gt;arrows&lt;/a&gt; that resembled iron spears.\nCough himself possessed a &lt;a href=\"Gough%27s%20Greatbow\"&gt;greatbow&lt;/a&gt; even larger than the archers he led and was the only one with the strength necessary to handle it. He distinguished himself on the battlefield as a dragonslayer and received from Lord Gwyn himself a golden medallion and dragon bone pauldrons as ornaments for his armor, crafted with a similar material of those worn by the Silver Knights symbolizing the highest honors for a warrior. Gwyn further rewarded the giant for his invaluable contribution to the war against the dragons, giving him a fragment of his &lt;a href=\"Lord%20Soul\"&gt;Lord Soul&lt;/a&gt;, a &lt;a href=\"Hawk%20Ring\"&gt;magical ring&lt;/a&gt; with the hawk symbol capable of increasing the range of his bows and made him one of his &lt;a href=\"Four%20Knights%20of%20Gwyn\"&gt;Four Knights&lt;/a&gt;, the highest rank in his army and the most trusted knights of the king.\nAfter the end of the great war, Lord Gwyn and his clan gained dominion over the world and began their Age of Fire and the giants continued to coexist with their civilization in a subordinate but close position. A large numbers of giants became &lt;a href=\"Sentinel\"&gt;Sentinel&lt;/a&gt;s guarding the walls and streets of Anor Londo, the city of the gods, employing &lt;a href=\"Giant%27s%20Halberd\"&gt;giant halberd&lt;/a&gt;s made of brass and retaining the power of lightning, &lt;a href=\"Giant%20Shield\"&gt;giant shield&lt;/a&gt;s of white iron and &lt;a href=\"Giant%20Set\"&gt;heavy armor&lt;/a&gt; of finely decorated golden brass. An even more powerful group of giants defended the royal cathedral in the center of the city and were capable of performing healing and offensive miracles.\nAfter the death of the &lt;a href=\"Nameless%20Blacksmith%20Deity\"&gt;Blacksmith Deity&lt;/a&gt; who was responsible for forging the weapons and armor of the gods, his task was assigned to a &lt;a href=\"Giant%20Blacksmith\"&gt;giant&lt;/a&gt; who thus became the new blacksmith of the gods and came to work and reside inside the cathedral of Anor Londo. Among many things, he was responsible for creating the &lt;a href=\"Dragonslayer%20Greatarrow\"&gt;Dragonslayer Greatarrow&lt;/a&gt;s and the &lt;a href=\"Dragonslayer%20Lightning%20Arrow\"&gt;Dragonslayer Lightning Arrow&lt;/a&gt;s used by dragonsalyers during the sporting hunts of the age of the gods. However he also created &lt;a href=\"Lightning%20Bolt\"&gt;Lightning Bolt&lt;/a&gt;s infused with the power of lightning made for humans, as during those times humans were still servants of the gods\nAfter Lord Gwyn's sacrifice to revive the fading First Flame, &lt;a href=\"Giant\"&gt;Giant&lt;/a&gt;s were used as slaves in &lt;a href=\"Sen%27s%20Fortress\"&gt;Sen's Fortress&lt;/a&gt;, a fortress built on the only route leading to the city of the gods to serve as a testing ground for the Undead that managed to overcome the first challenge of the &lt;a href=\"Bells%20of%20Awakening\"&gt;Bells of Awakening&lt;/a&gt; and seeked to enter Anor Londo to receive the &lt;a href=\"Lordvessel\"&gt;Lordvessel&lt;/a&gt;. After ringing the &lt;a href=\"Bells%20of%20Awakening\"&gt;Bell of Awakening&lt;/a&gt;, an enslaved giant would recognize that an Undead has completed the first trial of their quest and open the gate to allow them to enter the fortress. Additionally other chained giantss were used as gatekeepers, living launchers of firebombs and loaders a machine which will send boulders rolling throughout the fortress, creating environmental hazards capable of destroying those who wandered around the location.\nSometime around the fall of &lt;a href=\"Oolacile\"&gt;Oolacile&lt;/a&gt; due to the Abyss generated by the out-of-control &lt;a href=\"Manus%2C%20Father%20of%20the%20Abyss\"&gt;Manus&lt;/a&gt;, Gough arrived there but was imprisoned in a tower sealed by powerful magic by the citizens of the country. The eye holes of his helm were packed with tree resin by those who dismissed the force of the giant as brutish, indicating a feeling of racism towards the giants by humans.\n&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;.\nWIP\nTheories.\nIt is possible to theorize that Giants and Gods belong to two very close races in evolutionary terms. This is because of their history of constant and close collaboration and coexistence, the fact that the giants of Anor Londo are vulnerable to the power of heretical weapons like the clan of gods and that in the \"&lt;a href=\"Tomb%20of%20the%20Giants\"&gt;Tomb of the Giants&lt;/a&gt;\", where &lt;a href=\"Giant%20Skeleton\"&gt;Giant Skeleton&lt;/a&gt;s are found, even the gods were buried."}
