{"id": "133506", "revid": "51254358", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=133506", "title": "Gnaw", "text": "Gnaw (\u8755\u307f) is a &lt;a href=\"Miracle%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;miracle&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nSold by &lt;a href=\"Irina%20of%20Carim\"&gt;Irina of Carim&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Karla\"&gt;Karla&lt;/a&gt; for 2,000 &lt;a href=\"Soul%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;souls&lt;/a&gt; once either of them has been given the &lt;a href=\"Deep%20Braille%20Divine%20Tome\"&gt;Deep Braille Divine Tome&lt;/a&gt;.\nEffect.\nFires a swarm of insects at the target, inflicting 0.9 times the &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Buff\"&gt;Spell Buff&lt;/a&gt; of the catalyst as &lt;a href=\"Dark%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Dark&lt;/a&gt; damage and dealing 150 &lt;a href=\"Bleed%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Bleed&lt;/a&gt; build-up. As a Dark Miracle, it is subject to augmentation from being cast using a Dark catalyst like &lt;a href=\"Sunless%20Talisman\"&gt;Sunless Talisman&lt;/a&gt;.\n&lt;tabber&gt;Official translation=\n&lt;/tabber&gt;"}
{"id": "68084", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=68084", "title": "Goblin", "text": "Goblins (also known as Forest Grotesque) are in\u00a0\"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nDescription.\nGoblins are grotesque humanoid creatures that either throw rocks or wield poison clubs. Individually, they may be weak, but groups can easily overwhelm players.\nThey have green-brownish pale skin with their veins visible at plain sight. Their most distinctive feature, however, is having a big, tumorous bulk protruding from their lower bellies.\nThey feed on the carcasses of foes and presumably make weapons with their bones.\nStrategy.\nThese creatures are normally found in groups. If allowed to strike all at once, they can inflict &lt;a href=\"Poison%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;poison&lt;/a&gt; fairly quickly on the player. A broad weapon with a high staggering power such as the &lt;a href=\"Greatsword%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Greatsword&lt;/a&gt; would work well on groups. Spells with long casting time will be ineffective, as they move and attack quite fast.\nAttacks.\nUnarmed\nCudgel\nSling\nAll"}
