{"id": "136982", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=136982", "title": "Gold Pine Bundle", "text": "Gold Pine Bundles are consumable in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nDescription.\nQuickly applies 120 &lt;a href=\"Lightning%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;lightning&lt;/a&gt; damage to right-hand weapon. Buff lasts for 11 seconds.\nUsage.\nUnlike resins, which require the user to remain stationary while applying the buff, bundles take less than a second to activate and can be used while moving. While they grant more damage than their respective resins and many more bundles can be carried at once, the trade-off is that the duration of the buff is reduced to less than 20% of that of a resin.\nThe quick application time, high stock and low duration of these items makes them very flexible tools, useful for applying in the midst of combat based on the situation. Whereas a resin may find a large fraction of its duration wasted from inactivity between attacks, a bundle may be quickly activated when an opportunity to deal damage presents itself, and the advantage pressed until the buff expires. This includes, in particular, the short duration of vulnerability between &lt;a href=\"Parry%20and%20Riposte%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;parrying a foe&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Critical%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;taking the riposte&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "2725", "revid": "357152", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=2725", "title": "Gold Pine Resin", "text": "Gold Pine Resins are &lt;a href=\"offensive%20items\"&gt;offensive items&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\".\nGeneral information.\nGold Pine Resin may only be used on &lt;a href=\"enchant\"&gt;enchant&lt;/a&gt;able &lt;a href=\"Weapons%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;weapons&lt;/a&gt; that are upgraded down the &lt;a href=\"Standard%20%28upgrade%20path%29\"&gt;Standard&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Raw%20%28upgrade%20path%29\"&gt;Raw&lt;/a&gt;, or &lt;a href=\"Crystal%20%28upgrade%20path%29\"&gt;Crystal&lt;/a&gt; paths, as well as a limited amount of &lt;a href=\"Weapon%20Augmentation%23Non-standard%20weapons\"&gt;exceptions&lt;/a&gt;.\nGold Pine Resin temporarily adds a flat 150 lightning attack to the weapon equipped in the right hand, making it generally much stronger than its counterparts, &lt;a href=\"Charcoal%20Pine%20Resin\"&gt;Charcoal Pine Resin&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Rotten%20Pine%20Resin\"&gt;Rotten Pine Resin&lt;/a&gt;.\u00a0\nOverview.\nGold Pine Resin is useful at any stage in the game due to the significant amount of Lightning Damage it adds to weapons. The duration is long enough for most encounters at 1 minute. At the highest levels of upgrading, a regular weapon buffed with Gold Pine Resin is stronger than a Lightning weapon equivalent, especially when considering &lt;a href=\"Dexterity%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;Dexterity&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Strength%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;Strength&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"scaling\"&gt;scaling&lt;/a&gt;. For example, an &lt;a href=\"Iaito\"&gt;Iaito&lt;/a&gt; +15 enchanted with Gold Pine Resin deals more damage than a Lightning Iaito +5 given a decent Dexterity level.\nGold Pine Resin pales in comparison to &lt;a href=\"weapon%20augmentation\"&gt;weapon augmentation&lt;/a&gt;s such as &lt;a href=\"Sunlight%20Blade\"&gt;Sunlight Blade&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Crystal%20Magic%20Weapon\"&gt;Crystal Magic Weapon&lt;/a&gt;; however, it is the best choice available as a weapon buff for those that do not boast a high &lt;a href=\"Faith%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;Faith&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Intelligence%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;Intelligence&lt;/a&gt; level."}
{"id": "66318", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=66318", "title": "Gold Pine Resin (Dark Souls II)", "text": "The Gold Pine Resin is an in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nEffect.\nBoosts existing element by 30% and adds 50 &lt;a href=\"Lightning%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Lightning&lt;/a&gt; to the right-hand weapon for 90 seconds."}
{"id": "130347", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=130347", "title": "Gold Pine Resin (Dark Souls III)", "text": "Gold Pine Resins are consumable in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nDescription.\nAdds 95 &lt;a href=\"Lightning%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Lightning&lt;/a&gt; damage to right-hand weapon for 60 seconds.\nTrivia.\nThat it is speculated that it may be a fungal resin may refer to the fact that the &lt;a href=\"Mushroom%20Parent\"&gt;Mushroom Parent&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Mushroom%20Child\"&gt;Mushroom Child&lt;/a&gt; drop this item in the first \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\"."}
{"id": "6924", "revid": "56333033", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=6924", "title": "Gold Tracer", "text": "Gold Tracer is a &lt;a href=\"curved%20sword\"&gt;curved sword&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nThe Gold Tracer is only available in the \"&lt;a href=\"Artorias%20of%20the%20Abyss\"&gt;Artorias of the Abyss&lt;/a&gt;\" DLC. The curved sword may be obtained by either exchanging the &lt;a href=\"Soul%20of%20Artorias\"&gt;Soul of Artorias&lt;/a&gt; with &lt;a href=\"Lord%27s%20Blade%20Ciaran\"&gt;Lord's Blade Ciaran&lt;/a&gt; for both the Gold Tracer and the &lt;a href=\"Dark%20Silver%20Tracer\"&gt;Dark Silver Tracer&lt;/a&gt; or by killing her. Exchanging and killing will not result in two sets of each weapon. Also, upon killing Lord's Blade Ciaran, she will drop the &lt;a href=\"Lord%27s%20Blade%20Set\"&gt;Lord's Blade Set&lt;/a&gt; of &lt;a href=\"Armor%20Sets\"&gt;armor&lt;/a&gt;.\nCharacteristics.\nThe Gold Tracer is designed as an offhand weapon. It has the highest &lt;a href=\"Dexterity%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;Dexterity&lt;/a&gt; requirement of any &lt;a href=\"Curved%20Sword\"&gt;Curved Sword&lt;/a&gt; in the game. This weapon is the only weapon in the game that performs two special attacks while it is in the left hand, eschewing the ability to &lt;a href=\"parry\"&gt;parry&lt;/a&gt; for a heavy attack in the off hand. When the sword is swung it will create an orange-gold visual effect.\nUsing this sword in conjunction with the &lt;a href=\"Dark%20Silver%20Tracer\"&gt;Dark Silver Tracer&lt;/a&gt; is a good match up as it allows the player to deal &lt;a href=\"Bleed%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;Bleed&lt;/a&gt; damage from the Gold Tracer at a rate of 40 per strike, as well as &lt;a href=\"Toxic%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;Toxic&lt;/a&gt; damage with Dark Silver Tracer's strong attack (which can only be done with the right hand). The &lt;a href=\"moveset\"&gt;moveset&lt;/a&gt; for the Gold Tracer is similar to that of the &lt;a href=\"Painting%20Guardian%20Sword\"&gt;Painting Guardian Sword&lt;/a&gt;. Though unlike PGS, this weapon cannot be &lt;a href=\"Weapon%20Augmentation\"&gt;enchanted&lt;/a&gt;. \nMoveset.\nWhen equipped in the left hand, instead of a parry (L2) and single attack (L1), the right handed strong attacks are used instead (L1 is the first attack, and L2 is the follow up attack). Uniquely for left-handed attacks, it still retains the event state of a parry although it has no parry frames, allowing for it to be cancelled for a Parry Backstab."}
