{"id": "11190", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=11190", "title": "Golden Crystal Golem", "text": "Golden Crystal Golems are a non-respawning in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\".\nDescription.\nTheir appearance is very similar to that of &lt;a href=\"Crystal%20Golem\"&gt;Crystal Golem&lt;/a&gt;s, except they have a gold hue and appear slightly larger. \nLocations.\nDarkroot Basin.\nThe Golden Crystal Golem appears at the lowest portion of &lt;a href=\"Darkroot%20Basin\"&gt;Darkroot Basin&lt;/a&gt;, at the far end of the lake that the &lt;a href=\"Hydra\"&gt;Hydra&lt;/a&gt; lives in. There is shallow water that can be safely traversed to the left side of the lake. A &lt;a href=\"Rusted%20Iron%20Ring\"&gt;Rusted Iron Ring&lt;/a&gt; can make the trip faster and easier. It will not appear until the Hydra is defeated and the area is re-loaded. Killing it frees the &lt;a href=\"Dusk%20of%20Oolacile\"&gt;Dusk of Oolacile&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe Duke's Archives.\nThe Golden Crystal Golem appears in the center of the garden, out back of &lt;a href=\"The%20Duke%27s%20Archives\"&gt;The Duke's Archives&lt;/a&gt;. It will not appear until &lt;a href=\"Siegmeyer%20of%20Catarina\"&gt;Siegmeyer of Catarina&lt;/a&gt; has been given &lt;a href=\"Purple%20Moss%20Clump\"&gt;Purple Moss Clump&lt;/a&gt;s in The Great Swamp below &lt;a href=\"Blighttown\"&gt;Blighttown&lt;/a&gt;. It also will not appear if Siegmeyer of Catarina's story line has ended. Killing it frees &lt;a href=\"Sieglinde%20of%20Catarina\"&gt;Sieglinde of Catarina&lt;/a&gt;.\nCrystal Cave.\nTwo Golden Crystal Golems appear in the &lt;a href=\"Crystal%20Cave\"&gt;Crystal Cave&lt;/a&gt;. As they are on optional crystal bridges, they can be avoided. There is no requirement for them to appear. Killing them provides only souls. They do not respawn.\nLore.\nThey seem to be serving &lt;a href=\"Seath\"&gt;Seath&lt;/a&gt; by imprisoning people within themselves. After defeating the\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Hydra\"&gt;Hydra&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0in\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Darkroot%20Basin\"&gt;Darkroot Basin&lt;/a&gt;, a golem can be found at the back of the lake. Killing it will free\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Dusk%20of%20Oolacile\"&gt;Dusk of Oolacile&lt;/a&gt;.\nIn the garden outside\u00a0The Duke's Archives, a golem can be killed to free\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Sieglinde%20of%20Catarina\"&gt;Sieglinde of Catarina&lt;/a&gt;.\nNotes.\nThe Golems located in\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Darkroot%20Basin\"&gt;Darkroot Basin&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0and\u00a0&lt;a href=\"The%20Duke%27s%20Archives\"&gt;The Duke's Archives&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0act as prisons for\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Dusk%20of%20Oolacile\"&gt;Dusk of Oolacile&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0and\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Sieglinde%20of%20Catarina\"&gt;Sieglinde of Catarina&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0respectively. It is possible to see both women trapped within the large crystals on the golems' backs."}
{"id": "55587", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=55587", "title": "Golden Falcon Shield", "text": "The\u00a0Golden Falcon Shield\u00a0is a &lt;a href=\"Small%20Shields%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;small shield&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nChracteristics.\nBoasting relatively-high &lt;a href=\"elemental\"&gt;elemental&lt;/a&gt; defenses for a very lightweight shield, the Golden Falcon Shield is better-suited to combating mages or other sources of elemental damage, instead of &lt;a href=\"physical\"&gt;physical&lt;/a&gt; trauma or &lt;a href=\"Negative%20Status%20Effects%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;negative status effects&lt;/a&gt;. Its stability and physical damage reduction, like most small shields, is mediocre at best, but appreciable."}
{"id": "134843", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=134843", "title": "Golden Falcon Shield (Dark Souls III)", "text": "The Golden Falcon Shield is a &lt;a href=\"Small%20Shields%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Small Shield&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nFound in the &lt;a href=\"Road%20of%20Sacrifices%23Bonfires\"&gt;Crucifixion Woods&lt;/a&gt; area of the &lt;a href=\"Road%20of%20Sacrifices\"&gt;Road of Sacrifices&lt;/a&gt;. Near the end of the ruins that lead to the &lt;a href=\"Crystal%20Sage\"&gt;Crystal Sage&lt;/a&gt;, there is an area to the right guarded by several &lt;a href=\"Sage%27s%20Prentice\"&gt;Sage's Prentice&lt;/a&gt;s and a &lt;a href=\"Sage%27s%20Devout\"&gt;Sage's Devout&lt;/a&gt;, with a stairway that eventually leads to a &lt;a href=\"Ring%20of%20Sacrifice%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Ring of Sacrifice&lt;/a&gt;. Before reaching the top of the stairs, exit out of the structure through the broken wall, and follow the ledges to the left, where the shield can be found on a corpse, overlooking the area guarded by the two &lt;a href=\"Exile%20Watchdog\"&gt;Exile Watchdog&lt;/a&gt;s.\nCharacteristics.\nThe Golden Falcon Shield possesses a respectable amount of stability, but poor overall absorption percentages as it is still a Small Shield. With physical absorption being its highest defense, it is an ideal shield to combat enemies that primarily deal physical damage, and has an easier time &lt;a href=\"Parry%20and%20Riposte%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;parrying&lt;/a&gt; enemies due to its faster startup frames.\nUpgrades.\nReinforced with standard ."}
