{"id": "132014", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=132014", "title": "Golden Ritual Spear", "text": "Golden Ritual Spear (\u91d1\u679d\u306e\u6756\u69cd \"Kinshi no Sh\u014ds\u014d\", Spear-Staff of the Golden Bough) is a &lt;a href=\"Spears%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;spear&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nFound in &lt;a href=\"Irithyll%20of%20the%20Boreal%20Valley\"&gt;Irithyll of the Boreal Valley&lt;/a&gt;. From the &lt;a href=\"Pontiff%20Sulyvahn\"&gt;Pontiff Sulyvahn&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Bonfire%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;bonfire&lt;/a&gt;, exit the cathedral and hug the left wall, going indoors temporarily and then going up the stairs leading to the &lt;a href=\"Deacon\"&gt;Deacon&lt;/a&gt;s patrolling the upper walkway. Turn around and re-enter the cathedral, then cross the bridge and turn right, leading to a &lt;a href=\"Mimic%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Mimic&lt;/a&gt; that drops it.\nCharacteristics.\nOne of the oddest weapons in the game, the Golden Ritual Spear possesses a very narrow niche and can be very difficult to utilize.\nAs one of the six hybrid catalyst weapons in the game, it is capable of attacking like a spear and casting spells like a &lt;a href=\"Staves%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;staff&lt;/a&gt;. However, what makes this weapon so unusual is that while it casts &lt;a href=\"Sorcery%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Sorceries&lt;/a&gt;, its &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Buff\"&gt;Spell Buff&lt;/a&gt; scales entirely off of &lt;a href=\"Faith%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Faith&lt;/a&gt;. As such, the wielder must level &lt;a href=\"Intelligence%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Intelligence&lt;/a&gt; solely to meet the weapon's wielding requirements and various Sorceries' casting requirements, while also leveling Faith in order to inflict actual damage with those spells. This means that the wielder must invest heavily into multiple stats simply to use this weapon. Ideally, in order to be efficient as possible Intelligence is only leveled up enough to cast moderately small spells like &lt;a href=\"Great%20Soul%20Arrow\"&gt;Great Soul Arrow&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Snap%20Freeze\"&gt;Snap Freeze&lt;/a&gt;, while the remaining levels are put into Faith to increase their potency.\nMoveset.\n&lt;br&gt;\nUpgrades.\n&lt;br&gt;"}
