{"id": "31799", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=31799", "title": "Golden Wing Shield", "text": "The Golden Wing Shield is a &lt;a href=\"Medium%20Shields%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;medium shield&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\n&lt;a href=\"The%20Lost%20Bastille\"&gt;The Lost Bastille&lt;/a&gt; - On a corpse hanging off a ledge above &lt;a href=\"Steady%20Hand%20McDuff\"&gt;Steady Hand McDuff&lt;/a&gt;'s shop. To reach the ledge, start from &lt;a href=\"Straid%27s%20Cell\"&gt;Straid's Cell&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Bonfire%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;bonfire&lt;/a&gt; and go two floors down to the room with breakable pots/statues. Find the &lt;a href=\"Illusory%20Wall%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;illusory wall&lt;/a&gt; that leads to a corridor and another illusory wall that lead outside. Jump over the gap to the corpse and carefully edge along the narrow pathway to reach the platform above McDuff's shop.\nCharacteristics.\nPlayers should disregard using this shield as a means to block any sort of &lt;a href=\"physical\"&gt;physical&lt;/a&gt; attacks as it has extremely poor physical resistance.\nWhere this shield shines however, is its very good &lt;a href=\"Magic%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;magic&lt;/a&gt; resistance, even when not upgraded. Due to this fact, it is recommended to infuse it with Magic to reach its maximum potential. It also has a &lt;a href=\"spell%20parry\"&gt;spell parry&lt;/a&gt; capability which makes it good for players certain of their timings.\nThis shield could be compared to the &lt;a href=\"Spirit%20Tree%20Shield\"&gt;Spirit Tree Shield&lt;/a&gt;, as being a complete upgrade to it. The Golden Wing Shield is just better in terms of stats, with a small &lt;a href=\"weight\"&gt;weight&lt;/a&gt; increase."}
