{"id": "5447", "revid": "56333033", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5447", "title": "Grant", "text": "The Grant is a &lt;a href=\"Great%20Hammers\"&gt;great hammer&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nDropped by the &lt;a href=\"Invaders\"&gt;black phantom&lt;/a&gt; of &lt;a href=\"Paladin%20Leeroy\"&gt;Paladin Leeroy&lt;/a&gt; near the end of the &lt;a href=\"Tomb%20of%20the%20Giants\"&gt;Tomb of the Giants&lt;/a&gt;. As of &lt;a href=\"Patch%20Information\"&gt;patch&lt;/a&gt; 1.04/1.05, the game might glitch when he dies, causing him to not drop his &lt;a href=\"Equipment\"&gt;items&lt;/a&gt;.\nCharacteristics.\nGrant's two-handed\u00a0strong attack\u00a0unleashes a shockwave similar to that of &lt;a href=\"Wrath%20of%20the%20Gods\"&gt;Wrath of the Gods&lt;/a&gt;, dealing damage in all directions and knocking &lt;a href=\"enemies\"&gt;enemies&lt;/a&gt; back. Unlike Wrath of the Gods, Grant's\u00a0strong attack\u00a0knocks all non-&lt;a href=\"boss\"&gt;boss&lt;/a&gt; or large enemies down. Each use of this attack drains 200 &lt;a href=\"durability\"&gt;durability&lt;/a&gt;; at less than 200 durability, Grant cannot use the ability without being given repairs first. Though Grant has high &lt;a href=\"Faith%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;Faith&lt;/a&gt; scaling and decent &lt;a href=\"Strength%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;Strength&lt;/a&gt; scaling, it deals &lt;a href=\"Damage%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;split damage&lt;/a&gt; meaning that it will perform poorly compared with the much lighter and more stat efficient &lt;a href=\"Great%20Club\"&gt;Great Club&lt;/a&gt; at the same stat distribution. \nGrant has a &lt;a href=\"Divine%20%28Auxiliary%20Effect%29\"&gt;Divine&lt;/a&gt; , allowing it to prevent the &lt;a href=\"skeleton\"&gt;skeleton&lt;/a&gt;s in &lt;a href=\"The%20Catacombs\"&gt;The Catacombs&lt;/a&gt; and the &lt;a href=\"Tomb%20of%20the%20Giants\"&gt;Tomb of the Giants&lt;/a&gt; from reanimating.\nNotes.\nPre-Patch 1.04/1.05, Grant scaled with &lt;a href=\"Dexterity%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;Dexterity&lt;/a&gt; instead of &lt;a href=\"Faith%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;Faith&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "6083", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=6083", "title": "Grass Crest Shield", "text": "The Grass Crest Shield is a &lt;a href=\"medium%20shield\"&gt;medium shield&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nThe Grass Crest Shield is found in &lt;a href=\"Darkroot%20Basin\"&gt;Darkroot Basin&lt;/a&gt; guarded by a &lt;a href=\"Black%20Knight\"&gt;Black Knight&lt;/a&gt;.\nCharacteristics.\nThe Grass Crest Shield has medium deflection and normal &lt;a href=\"parry\"&gt;parry&lt;/a&gt; speed.\nIt has the unique and powerful effect of raising &lt;a href=\"stamina\"&gt;stamina&lt;/a&gt; regeneration speed by 10, making it ideal for putting on one's back while two-handing a &lt;a href=\"Weapons%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;weapon&lt;/a&gt;. The regeneration can stack with other stamina regeneration effects, such as those of &lt;a href=\"Green%20Blossom\"&gt;Green Blossom&lt;/a&gt;s or the &lt;a href=\"Mask%20of%20the%20Child\"&gt;Mask of the Child&lt;/a&gt;.\nHowever, it is mediocre when used as an actual &lt;a href=\"shield\"&gt;shield&lt;/a&gt;, and is therefore not a good choice for block-heavy builds, as the lack of stability will cancel out any gains in stamina recovery.\nWhen &lt;a href=\"Weapon%20Modification\"&gt;upgraded&lt;/a&gt; to &lt;a href=\"Crystal%20%28Upgrade%20Path%29\"&gt;crystal&lt;/a&gt; the shield's &lt;a href=\"durability\"&gt;durability&lt;/a&gt; is 20.\nResistance Defense.\nAlong with &lt;a href=\"Physical\"&gt;Physical&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Elemental\"&gt;Elemental&lt;/a&gt; damage reduction, weapons also have hidden stats that reduce the amount of &lt;a href=\"status\"&gt;status&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"build-up\"&gt;build-up&lt;/a&gt; while blocking."}
{"id": "134852", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=134852", "title": "Grass Crest Shield (Dark Souls III)", "text": "The Grass Crest Shield is a &lt;a href=\"Medium%20Shields%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;medium shield&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nFound in the &lt;a href=\"Road%20of%20Sacrifices\"&gt;Road of Sacrifices&lt;/a&gt;, near the &lt;a href=\"Crucifixion%20Woods\"&gt;Crucifixion Woods&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Bonfire%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;bonfire&lt;/a&gt;. The shield can be looted from a corpse lying beside a tree near the first &lt;a href=\"Great%20Crab\"&gt;Great Crab&lt;/a&gt;.\nCharacteristics.\nThe Grass Crest Shield is unremarkable for a medium shield in terms of protection, but having it equipped bestows increased &lt;a href=\"Stamina%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;stamina&lt;/a&gt; regeneration, increasing it by 4 points per second. This effect carries on even if the player has the shield on their back when two-handing a weapon in their main hand. \nThough it is fairly &lt;a href=\"stable\"&gt;stable&lt;/a&gt; for a medium shield, it is more suited to be used as an auxiliary tool by the player, especially if they utilize larger weapons in their arsenal. \nHowever, it is worth noting that the shield is also capable of &lt;a href=\"Parry%20%28skill%29\"&gt;parrying&lt;/a&gt;.\nUpgrades.\n&lt;br&gt;"}
{"id": "172643", "revid": "5064773", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=172643", "title": "Grave Entrance", "text": ""}
{"id": "131491", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=131491", "title": "Grave Key", "text": "The Grave Key is a in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nSold by the &lt;a href=\"Shrine%20Handmaid\"&gt;Shrine Handmaid&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Firelink%20Shrine%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Firelink Shrine&lt;/a&gt; for 1,500 &lt;a href=\"Souls%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;souls&lt;/a&gt;, once she has been given the &lt;a href=\"Mortician%27s%20Ashes\"&gt;Mortician's Ashes&lt;/a&gt;.\nUsage.\nUnlocks the barred door in the sewers of the &lt;a href=\"Undead%20Settlement\"&gt;Undead Settlement&lt;/a&gt; that lead to a tunnel complex which eventually ends in &lt;a href=\"Irina%20of%20Carim\"&gt;Irina&lt;/a&gt;'s cell. Also, this key allows to lock the door it is intended to. To lock this door, user must be standing near it at the side of tunnel catacomb(not the side of bridge and sewers) and open the door with the key. After it, door can be locked from the both sides, but if it is open from the side of sewers once, it cannot be locked anymore. If the door was open from the tunnels and player left current location, took rest near bonfire or left game, door also cannot be locked anymore. This opportunity can be used to lock an &lt;a href=\"Red%20Eye%20Orb%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;invader&lt;/a&gt; in, forcing them to &lt;a href=\"Black%20Separation%20Crystal%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;return to their world&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "63284", "revid": "26269363", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=63284", "title": "Grave Warden", "text": "Grave Wardens are in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\". \nLocation.\nThey are first encountered in the &lt;a href=\"Earthen%20Peak\"&gt;Earthen Peak&lt;/a&gt; and can later be found in the &lt;a href=\"Undead%20Crypt\"&gt;Undead Crypt&lt;/a&gt;.\nDescription.\nGrave Wardens are humanoid warriors that wear ragged robes, including a cloth mask concealing their faces. There are two variants, one that is fully clothed and one missing the torso cloth. They wield spears and sickles that are capable of inflicting dark damage on the player.\nStrategy.\nGrave Wardens have low poise and can be easily &lt;a href=\"stagger\"&gt;stagger&lt;/a&gt;ed by repeated attacks. However they tend to guard a lot and their spear attacks can inflict dark damage even when blocking, so it is advised to evade their lunges rather than guard them. Grave Wardens can heal with &lt;a href=\"Estus%20Flask%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Estus&lt;/a&gt; when injured.\nThe Grave Wardens encountered in the &lt;a href=\"Undead%20Crypt\"&gt;Undead Crypt&lt;/a&gt; are not initially hostile to the player unless they are attacked. They will also become aggressive if the player enters their chamber with a source of light, such as a torch. A player may attack them freely, without &lt;a href=\"Grave%20Warden%20Agdayne\"&gt;Grave Warden Agdayne&lt;/a&gt; intervening, however the two dual-wielding wardens are a force to be reckoned with, and the reward of killing them is a chance to get their &lt;a href=\"Silverblack%20Sickle\"&gt;unique sickle&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "134157", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=134157", "title": "Grave Warden's Ashes", "text": "The Grave Warden's Ashes are a in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\". They are one of several &lt;a href=\"Umbral%20Ash\"&gt;umbral ashes&lt;/a&gt; that can be found throughout the course of the game.\nAvailability.\nFound in the &lt;a href=\"Catacombs%20of%20Carthus\"&gt;Catacombs of Carthus&lt;/a&gt;.\nFrom the &lt;a href=\"Catacombs%20of%20Carthus%23Bonfires\"&gt;Catacombs of Carthus&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Bonfire%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;bonfire&lt;/a&gt;, turn left and go downstairs. Climb up any of the two sets of stairs found on the nearby wall (one of them hidden behind an &lt;a href=\"Illusory%20Wall%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;illusory wall&lt;/a&gt;). The ashes are on a corpse lying at the far end of this area, guarded by three &lt;a href=\"Skeleton%20Swordsman%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Skeleton Swordsmen&lt;/a&gt;.\nUsage.\nExtends the &lt;a href=\"Shrine%20Handmaid\"&gt;Shrine Handmaid&lt;/a&gt;'s inventory to include the following items:"}
{"id": "133639", "revid": "1188343", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=133639", "title": "Grave Warden (Dark Souls III)", "text": "Grave Wardens (\u5893\u5b88\u308a \"Hakamori\", Grave Guardian) are in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nDescription.\nGrave Wardens are servants of the &lt;a href=\"Church%20of%20the%20Deep\"&gt;Church of the Deep&lt;/a&gt; and are tasked with disposing of the ever-rising corpses that infest the &lt;a href=\"Cathedral%20of%20the%20Deep\"&gt;Cathedral&lt;/a&gt;'s grounds. They resemble ragged skeletal humanoids that wield &lt;a href=\"Warden%20Twinblades\"&gt;Warden Twinblades&lt;/a&gt; in combat.\nLocations.\n&lt;a href=\"Cathedral%20of%20the%20Deep\"&gt;Cathedral of the Deep&lt;/a&gt;\n&lt;a href=\"Untended%20Graves\"&gt;Untended Graves&lt;/a&gt;\nStrategy.\nCathedral Grave Wardens have moderate health and are surprisingly durable despite their frail appearance. They are agile and aggressive fighters that will close the distance quickly with either a lunging stab or twirling slash; it is advisable to roll forward to evade this, as they can clip the player if they evade to the side. Their attacks cause rapid &lt;a href=\"Bleed%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Bleed&lt;/a&gt; build-up and they will drain &lt;a href=\"Endurance%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;stamina&lt;/a&gt; very quickly if blocked.\nGrave Wardens are very vulnerable to &lt;a href=\"Critical%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;backstabs&lt;/a&gt; after they have finished their combos, as long as the player moves behind them whilst they are in the attack animation, as they will quickly reposition themselves. They are also very weak to &lt;a href=\"Fire%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;fire&lt;/a&gt; damage and will flail wildly if ignited.\nDrops.\n&lt;tabber&gt; Cathedral of the Deep =\n&lt;/tabber&gt;"}
{"id": "52331", "revid": "53256869", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=52331", "title": "Grave Warden Agdayne", "text": "Grave Warden Agdayne is a &lt;a href=\"Characters%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;character&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Merchants%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;merchant&lt;/a&gt; in\u00a0\"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nHe is voiced by .\nLore.\nAs a &lt;a href=\"Fenito\"&gt;Fenito&lt;/a&gt;, Agdayne watches over the &lt;a href=\"Undead%20Crypt\"&gt;Undead Crypt&lt;/a&gt; and its deceased to make sure they are properly kept in their rest and not disturbed. He was granted this task by &lt;a href=\"Gravelord%20Nito\"&gt;\"the one who gave us the first death\"&lt;/a&gt;. He mentions a \"king of light\" from an age long ago who was afraid humans would create an &lt;a href=\"age%20of%20dark\"&gt;age of dark&lt;/a&gt;. The king he mentions is likely &lt;a href=\"Gwyn%2C%20Lord%20of%20Cinder\"&gt;Gwyn, Lord of Cinder&lt;/a&gt;.\nPlot.\nWhen approached, Agdayne will tell the player that they may not produce light. Wielding a lit &lt;a href=\"torch\"&gt;torch&lt;/a&gt; or using &lt;a href=\"Cast%20Light%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Cast Light&lt;/a&gt; within this room will cause him and his fellow &lt;a href=\"Grave%20Warden\"&gt;Grave Warden&lt;/a&gt;s to attack the player.\nAfter conversing with him, Agdayne will give the player access to his wares, and he will become available as a summon against &lt;a href=\"Velstadt%2C%20the%20Royal%20Aegis\"&gt;Velstadt, the Royal Aegis&lt;/a&gt;."}
