{"id": "2213", "revid": "24958057", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=2213", "title": "Gravelord Servant", "text": "The Gravelord Servant (\u5893\u738b\u306e\u7737\u5c5e) is a &lt;a href=\"PvP\"&gt;PvP&lt;/a&gt;-oriented &lt;a href=\"covenant\"&gt;covenant&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\". Gravelord servants spread misery by using &lt;a href=\"Eyes%20of%20Death\"&gt;Eyes of Death&lt;/a&gt; to spawn black phantoms in other worlds.\nRequirements.\nThere are some Eyes of Death close to where players can access the Gravelord Servant covenant.\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Basilisk\"&gt;Basilisk&lt;/a&gt;s found in the &lt;a href=\"Depths\"&gt;Depths&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"The%20Great%20Hollow\"&gt;The Great Hollow&lt;/a&gt; also drop them, rarely.\nBenefits.\nUpon joining, players receive:\n&lt;a href=\"Eye%20of%20Death\"&gt;Eyes of Death&lt;/a&gt; are offered to &lt;a href=\"Gravelord%20Nito\"&gt;Gravelord Nito&lt;/a&gt; to gain ranks in the Gravelord Servant Covenant.\nAbilities.\nBeing a Gravelord Servant allows players to curse other people's worlds. To do this, an Eye of Death is used. Doing so will cause numerous black phantom NPCs to spawn in up to three other people's worlds, provided the cursed player is in NG+ or higher. This is indicated by a black, fiery aura that is centered around the Gravelord Servant. The curse lasts until the Gravelord Servant either signs off or dies.\nTo invade a Gravelord Servant, infected players must find the Gravelord Servant's\u00a0invasion sign (which will move with the Gravelord Servant on a 10 second delay). Then they can invade as spirits of vengeance. The victor of the battle is awarded an Eye of Death. All three players may invade the Gravelord Servant at once. Using the Eye of Death will increase the odds of being invaded by other phantoms, including Dark Spirits belonging to either the Dark Wraith Covenant or the Forest Hunter Covenant, and Vengeful Spirits belonging to the Darkmoon Covenant. This is caused by the player's world to be in a state of constant high priority. The effect is similar to using a Dried Finger repeatedly for the duration. The maximum number of players invading the Gravelord Servant through their sign at a time is capped at three (four in Remastered when using a dried finger). A Gravelord Servant cannot see summon signs while under the effects of an Eye of Death nor can they use an Eye of Death if there are any phantoms or invaders present in their world.\nOverview.\nGravelord Servant is one of the tougher covenants to master. It is often difficult to get the right people to invade (sometimes agents of the &lt;a href=\"Blade%20of%20the%20Darkmoon\"&gt;Blade of the Darkmoon&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Darkwraith%20%28covenant%29\"&gt;Darkwraith&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"covenant\"&gt;covenant&lt;/a&gt;s will invade anyway, and killing them does NOT yield &lt;a href=\"Eye%20of%20Death\"&gt;Eyes of Death&lt;/a&gt;), and skilled players should have no problem defeating the Black Phantoms Gravelords sent to other worlds.\nGravelord servants also run the risk of being invaded by numerous people at once. It may be faster to simply farm Eyes of Death from &lt;a href=\"Basilisk\"&gt;Basilisk&lt;/a&gt;s in the &lt;a href=\"Depths\"&gt;Depths&lt;/a&gt; than to attempt to farm them by invading as was intended."}
{"id": "5139", "revid": "56333033", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5139", "title": "Gravelord Sword", "text": "The Gravelord Sword is a &lt;a href=\"Curved%20Greatswords\"&gt;curved greatsword&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nAwarded as part of the &lt;a href=\"Gravelord%20Servant\"&gt;Gravelord Servant&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"covenant\"&gt;covenant&lt;/a&gt;, which is accessed through &lt;a href=\"The%20Catacombs\"&gt;The Catacombs&lt;/a&gt; by laying in an open coffin that is in close vicinity to a &lt;a href=\"Titanite%20Demon\"&gt;Titanite Demon&lt;/a&gt;.\nCharacteristics.\nThe Gravelord Sword inflicts &lt;a href=\"Toxic%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;Toxic&lt;/a&gt; buildup, at a rate of 30 points of Toxic per hit, and once the bar is filled, lasts for 10 minutes dealing 5 damage per second. This weapon is one of only two in the game that has the ability to inflict toxic, the other being the &lt;a href=\"Dark%20Silver%20Tracer\"&gt;Dark Silver Tracer&lt;/a&gt;.\nWhen compared to the other &lt;a href=\"Curved%20Greatswords\"&gt;Curved Greatswords&lt;/a&gt;, the Gravelord Sword has the poorest &lt;a href=\"Parameter%20Bonus\"&gt;scaling&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Physical%20Damage%20Types\"&gt;physical&lt;/a&gt; damage coupled with being hard to upgrade. This weapon is decent in the early game but will be outclassed quickly by &lt;a href=\"Murakumo\"&gt;Murakumo&lt;/a&gt;. If a player would like to use Gravelord Sword for an entire run, would not be wise to invest into Physical Damage scaling stats due to low scaling percentages. "}
{"id": "4399", "revid": "51254358", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4399", "title": "Gravelord Sword Dance", "text": "Gravelord Sword Dance (\u5893\u738b\u306e\u5263\u821e) is a &lt;a href=\"Miracle%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;miracle&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nJoin the &lt;a href=\"Gravelord%20Servant\"&gt;Gravelord Servant&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"covenant\"&gt;covenant&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"The%20Catacombs\"&gt;Catacombs&lt;/a&gt;. This miracle may only be obtained once per character, regardless of playthrough.\nGeneral Information.\nIt has a magic attack power equal to 2.5 times the talisman's magic adjust. Each rank within the Gravelord Servant covenant boosts the damage multiplier of the spell by 0.1.\nGravelord Sword Dance has 40 \"use\" per copy. Each cast of Gravelord Sword Dance takes 20 \"uses\", causing 20 spikes to jut out of the ground in the general vicinity of the player, dealing high damage and knockback. If the caster is interrupted, only some of the \"uses\" will be utilized. Gravelord Sword Dance has a notably high starting lag, and players are immobile for the second half of casting it.\nSwords will only poke out of ground locations that the player has line-of-sight to (i.e., it cannot be used to hit enemies behind walls or around corners).\nLeaving the Gravelord Servant covenant does not prevent use of this miracle, but prevents gaining any rank-dependent damage bonus from the covenant.\nDescription.\n&lt;tabber&gt;Official translation=\n&lt;/tabber&gt;"}
