{"id": "133537", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=133537", "title": "Great Chaos Fire Orb", "text": "Great Chaos Fire Orb is a &lt;a href=\"Pyromancy%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;pyromancy&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nSold by &lt;a href=\"Cornyx%20of%20the%20Great%20Swamp\"&gt;Cornyx of the Great Swamp&lt;/a&gt; for 10,000 &lt;a href=\"Soul%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;souls&lt;/a&gt; once he has been given the &lt;a href=\"Izalith%20Pyromancy%20Tome\"&gt;Izalith Pyromancy Tome&lt;/a&gt;.\nEffect.\nHurls a large Chaos-infused fire orb at the target; whether they are hit by the projectile itself or caught by the explosion on impact, targets will take 3.3 times the &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Buff\"&gt;Spell Buff&lt;/a&gt; of the catalyst as &lt;a href=\"Fire%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Fire&lt;/a&gt; damage. A pool of lava will persist at the impact point for 3 seconds, inflicting 1.5 times the Spell Buff of the catalyst as Fire damage for as long as any enemy makes contact with it.\nDue to peculiarities in scaling it doesn't benefit from the &lt;a href=\"Faith%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Faith&lt;/a&gt; scaling of a &lt;a href=\"Pyromancy%20Flames%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Pyromancy Flame&lt;/a&gt; unless a minimum level of &lt;a href=\"Intelligence%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Intelligence&lt;/a&gt; has been reached: starting at 22 Intelligence for a +0 Flame and gradually going down to 18 Intelligence for a +10 Flame.&lt;br&gt;"}
{"id": "3488", "revid": "357111", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3488", "title": "Great Chaos Fireball", "text": "Chaos Great Fireball is a &lt;a href=\"Pyromancy%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;Pyromancy&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nGreat Chaos Fireball is obtained after joining &lt;a href=\"Chaos%20Servant\"&gt;Chaos Servant&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"covenant\"&gt;covenant&lt;/a&gt;. However, unlike most other magic, only one copy may be obtained, and going into &lt;a href=\"New%20Game%20Plus\"&gt;NG+&lt;/a&gt; does not grant additional casts.\nGeneral information.\nThe player hurls a giant fireball, which does a large amount of damage on impact with a good &lt;a href=\"area%20of%20effect\"&gt;area of effect&lt;/a&gt;, identical to &lt;a href=\"Great%20Fireball\"&gt;Great Fireball&lt;/a&gt;. The fireball has a fire attack power of 3.0 times the Pyromancy Flame's magic adjust and the lava pool has a fire attack power of 2.0 times the Pyromancy Flame's magic adjust.\nContrary to what the name suggests, Great Chaos Fireball does not scale with the player's amount of &lt;a href=\"Humanity%20%28gameplay%20mechanic%29\"&gt;humanity&lt;/a&gt; (like &lt;a href=\"Chaos%20%28mechanic%29\"&gt;Chaos weapons&lt;/a&gt; do). It can only be improved by upgrading and ascending the &lt;a href=\"Pyromancy%20Flame\"&gt;Pyromancy Flame&lt;/a&gt; used to cast it.\nOverview.\nThanks to its high damage and large area of effect, Great Chaos Fireball is great against clusters of enemies, as well as single strong enemies. However, as it requires two slots, Great Chaos Fireball does less damage than most other pyromancies in terms of damage per slot, making it unsuitable for long journeys between distant bonfires.\nIn &lt;a href=\"PvP\"&gt;PvP&lt;/a&gt;, Great Chaos Fireball is one of the more popular pyromancies (along with &lt;a href=\"Great%20Combustion\"&gt;Great Combustion&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Fire%20Tempest\"&gt;Fire Tempest&lt;/a&gt;), due its high damage, good area of effect, and lingering lava; however, manual aiming will likely be required to hit experienced players, as they will easily dodge it otherwise. This can be tricky at best; however, the high damage can be well worth it. Players must be cautious when casting this spell as if the enemy is close enough, they will have an opportunity for a &lt;a href=\"backstab\"&gt;backstab&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "56951", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=56951", "title": "Great Chaos Fireball (Dark Souls II)", "text": "Great Chaos Fireball is a &lt;a href=\"Pyromancy%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;pyromancy&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nThis is likely one of the harder spells to obtain in NG and NG+ due to the way advancement works within the &lt;a href=\"Brotherhood%20of%20Blood\"&gt;Brotherhood of Blood&lt;/a&gt;. However, it is also one of the most damaging, if not the most damaging, pyromancies in game.\nGeneral information.\nThe Great Chaos Fireball is very similar to &lt;a href=\"Great%20Fireball%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Great Fireball&lt;/a&gt;;\u00a0it is an arced projectile dealing heavy fire damage. However, the difference between these two spells is that Great Chaos Fireball deals higher initial damage (tested on various enemies in NG++) and leaves a short-lived pool of lava on impact as well.\nAttunement milestones.\nLike all other spells, the amount of casts per slot increases upon reaching certain &lt;a href=\"Attunement%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Attunement&lt;/a&gt; milestones:"}
{"id": "5445", "revid": "56333033", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5445", "title": "Great Club", "text": "The Great Club is a &lt;a href=\"Great%20Hammers\"&gt;great hammer&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nFound in &lt;a href=\"Blighttown\"&gt;Blighttown&lt;/a&gt;, to the left of the entrance to Quelaag's Domain. It is guarded by two &lt;a href=\"Infested%20Barbarian\"&gt;Infested Barbarian&lt;/a&gt;s.\nCharacteristics.\nThe Great Club is a bigger version of the &lt;a href=\"Large%20Club\"&gt;Large Club&lt;/a&gt;, having higher base damage, but with more weight and causing no poison build up.\nWith high staggering power, good Guard Break and high damage, the Great Club is a powerful weapon in the right hands. Its main flaws are the slowness and clumsiness of its strikes. An adversary that can fast roll can easily roll \"into\" the attack of the Great Club and counterattack, thus, fat rolling or over burdening isn't wise should a Great Club be equipped.\nThe Great Club has incredibly high damage for its weight; out-damaging weapons nearly twice as heavy as it. Its Physical Attack Rating and practical damage are only slightly surpassed by the &lt;a href=\"Demon%27s%20Greataxe\"&gt;Demon's Greataxe&lt;/a&gt;, which weighs 10 more units than the Great Club for a negligible damage increase. \nAt 99 Strength and 99 Intelligence, an &lt;a href=\"Enchanted%20%28upgrade%20path%29\"&gt;Enchanted&lt;/a&gt; Great Club has the highest Attack Rating in the game at 824 AR. This should not be confused with it dealing the most damage on elemental upgrade paths, visit the &lt;a href=\"Damage%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;Damage Calculation&lt;/a&gt; page for more information. \nUpgrades.\nScaling Percentage Values.\nThe following chart lists the scaling percentages when this weapon is fully upgraded. Be advised that:"}
{"id": "52470", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=52470", "title": "Great Club (Dark Souls II)", "text": "The Great Club is a &lt;a href=\"Great%20Hammers%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;great hammer&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nAt the very bottom of\u00a0&lt;a href=\"The%20Gutter\"&gt;The Gutter&lt;/a&gt;.\nCharacteristics.\nThe Great Club, like all other &lt;a href=\"Great%20Hammers%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;great hammers&lt;/a&gt; in the game, boast the highest &lt;a href=\"Poise%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;poise&lt;/a&gt; damage out of all the weapon-types, more so when two-handed.\nIts horizontal sweeping attack ( / ) ensures that small enemies grouping together in front of the player will get stun-locked and receive a high amount of damage as well.\nThe two-handed strong attack ( / ) is a massive overhead swing that has the potential to kill almost any standard enemy in one hit. This move can be followed up with a dual circular strike, which will deal even more physical and poise damage. The overhead attack will also nail humanoid enemies to the ground. This is particularly devastating against non-playable characters, which usually do not block or evade attacks. In particular, it is relatively easy to repeatedly hammer characters to the ground, until death occurs. This is particularly relevant against characters with large health pools, such as &lt;a href=\"Licia%20of%20Lindeldt\"&gt;Licia of Lindeldt&lt;/a&gt;. On enemies like the &lt;a href=\"Ruin%20Sentinels\"&gt;Ruin Sentinels&lt;/a&gt;, they won't get knocked down but a few hits with the two-handed strong attack will stun them, leaving them wide open to further attacks."}
{"id": "131359", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=131359", "title": "Great Club (Dark Souls III)", "text": "The Great Club is a &lt;a href=\"Great%20Hammers%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;great hammer&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nGuaranteed drop from the &lt;a href=\"Exile%20Watchdog\"&gt;Exile Watchdog&lt;/a&gt; who wields it in the &lt;a href=\"Road%20of%20Sacrifices\"&gt;Road of Sacrifices&lt;/a&gt;.\nCharacteristics.\nLike previous incarnations, the Great Club is one of the most potent weapons in its class. This is due to several factors: its relatively low weight makes the Great Club significantly lighter than other comparable weapons, and its sheer raw damage and scaling at high upgrade and strength levels, further boosted by the weapon art, grants the Great Club one of the highest damage-to-weight ratios in the game. In comparison, the next available great hammer, the Great Mace, weighs six more units, does only marginally more damage, and lacks the weapon art boost.\nUpgrades.\nReinforced with ."}
{"id": "3760", "revid": "357112", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3760", "title": "Great Combustion", "text": "Great Combustion is a &lt;a href=\"Pyromancy%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;Pyromancy&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\".\nGeneral Information.\nGreat Combustion is a stronger version of &lt;a href=\"Combustion\"&gt;Combustion&lt;/a&gt;, with identical casting time and similar applications, but is less flexible in use due to the halved number of casts. It has a fire attack power of 2.4 times the Pyromancy Flame's magic adjust.\nOverview.\nGreat Combustion is an immensely popular spell, both for PvE and PvP. In PvE, it is great for quickly racking up damage on tough-to-kill enemies such as bosses. In PvP, it is a potent addition to any arsenal due to its high damage through most shields and large hitbox. Eight casts is still very generous for the amount of damage Great Combustion does.\nThe AoTA DLC makes Great Combustion semi-obsolete as &lt;a href=\"Black%20Flame%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;Black Flame&lt;/a&gt; is near-identical but with the added bonus of dealing more stamina drain against targets."}
