{"id": "133544", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=133544", "title": "Great Combustion (Dark Souls III)", "text": "Great Combustion is a &lt;a href=\"Pyromancy%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;pyromancy&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nSold by &lt;a href=\"Cornyx%20of%20the%20Great%20Swamp\"&gt;Cornyx of the Great Swamp&lt;/a&gt; for 3,000 &lt;a href=\"Soul%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;souls&lt;/a&gt;.\nEffect.\nCreates a powerful explosion in front of the caster, inflicting 1.95 times the &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Buff\"&gt;Spell Buff&lt;/a&gt; of the catalyst as &lt;a href=\"Fire%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Fire&lt;/a&gt; damage. If foes catch the lingering flame after the initial explosion, they will take only 1.85 times the Spell Buff of the catalyst as Fire damage."}
{"id": "130432", "revid": "51254358", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=130432", "title": "Great Corvian Scythe", "text": "The Great Corvian Scythe (\u9d09\u4eba\u306e\u5927\u938c) is a &lt;a href=\"Reapers%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;reaper&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nDropped by scythe-wielding &lt;a href=\"Corvian\"&gt;Corvian&lt;/a&gt;s.\nCharacteristics.\nThe Great Corvian Scythe possesses the same moveset as the &lt;a href=\"Great%20Scythe%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Great Scythe&lt;/a&gt;. Its wielding requirements are higher, requiring more &lt;a href=\"Strength%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Strength&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Dexterity%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Dexterity&lt;/a&gt; to wield. However, its higher base damage and superior &lt;a href=\"Parameter%20Bonus%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;scaling&lt;/a&gt; make it a better weapon than the Great Scythe in almost every category that matters, making it especially popular for elemental &lt;a href=\"Infusion%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;infusions&lt;/a&gt;.\nHowever, this comes at the cost of inflicting &lt;a href=\"Bleed%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Bleed&lt;/a&gt; upon the wielder for every attack that successfully increases Bleed build-up upon a foe. This means that when fighting groups of enemies, the Great Corvian Scythe may become a liability as it is highly probable that the wielder will suffer a Blood Loss proc through landing numerous attacks in a short period of time.\nMoveset.\n&lt;br&gt;\nUpgrades.\nReinforced with standard &lt;a href=\"Titanite%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Titanite&lt;/a&gt;.\n&lt;br&gt;\nDescription.\n&lt;tabber&gt;Official translation=\n&lt;/tabber&gt;"}
{"id": "134995", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=134995", "title": "Great Crab", "text": "Great Crabs are &lt;a href=\"Enemies%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;enemies&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nDescription.\nGigantic crustaceans that usually inhabit murky environments where mobility is severely compromised. Some Great Crabs have a very extensive aggro range and may start chasing the player from very long distances. It's not uncommon to find their &lt;a href=\"Lesser%20Crab\"&gt;offspring&lt;/a&gt; in areas where they are encountered.\nGreat Crabs fight by slamming either of their pincers continuously onto the ground or by shooting a stream of a viscous liquid from their mouths, reducing the player's mobility.\nAs expected from a creature of these characteristics, they have a dangerous grab where they will grasp the player with their bigger pincer and attack them furiously, dealing heavy damage. This attack is telegraphed by the sudden appearance of foamy bubbles drooling out from their mouths.\nThe first two crabs, encountered in the &lt;a href=\"Road%20of%20Sacrifices\"&gt;Road of Sacrifices&lt;/a&gt;' marshlands, have a particular ability not seen in their more advanced brethren: they can suddenly disengage from battle and burrow themselves into the ground, appearing moments later in a distant location with all their health restored back.\nLocations.\n&lt;a href=\"Road%20of%20Sacrifices\"&gt;Road of Sacrifices&lt;/a&gt;\n&lt;a href=\"Farron%20Keep\"&gt;Farron Keep&lt;/a&gt;\n&lt;a href=\"Smouldering%20Lake\"&gt;Smouldering Lake&lt;/a&gt;\n&lt;a href=\"Painted%20World%20of%20Ariandel\"&gt;Painted World of Ariandel&lt;/a&gt; (\"&lt;a href=\"Ashes%20of%20Ariandel\"&gt;Ashes of Ariandel&lt;/a&gt;\")\nStrategy.\nMenacing looking and not without a reason, Great Crabs can prove to be formidable foes even in the late game. They have an insane aggro range and will most likely rush at the player from very far distances, however, the crabs in the Road of Sacrifices swamp do not usually follow the player if they retreat onto dry land.\nDefeating the one near the keep in the &lt;a href=\"Road%20of%20Sacrifices\"&gt;Road of Sacrifices&lt;/a&gt; will grant the player the &lt;a href=\"Great%20Swamp%20Ring\"&gt;Great Swamp Ring&lt;/a&gt;, which greatly enhances &lt;a href=\"Pyromancy%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;pyromancies&lt;/a&gt;. This may not be an easy task in the early game, though, as there will be major difference between the damage the player can output, compared to the damage they deal when they are first encountered, which usually ends up with the crab burrowing into the ground in the middle of the fight, only to appear moments later in a distant area with its health completely restored. For this reason, it's recommended to come back to fight them once the player is stronger and has procured better weaponry. Ranged-attacking characters, like sorcerers and pyromancers, may have a better chance of defeating them the first time around, as Great Crabs can usually be lured into getting stuck among the trees, where the player may attack them at will.\nTheir attacks mainly consist in walking toward the player in a sideways manner whilst slamming one of their pincers repeatedly until they catch on. Moving in front of them will make them switch to the rest of their attacks.\nThey will frequently shoot a stream of viscous liquid. If hit, the player will have their mobility reduced for a short period of time. This attack is very easy to evade, however, and the creature will be open to attack afterward.\nIf they have sustained enough punishment and their poise is broken, they will stagger and be open for a &lt;a href=\"Critical%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;critical attack&lt;/a&gt;. Additionally, their attacks can be &lt;a href=\"Parry%20and%20Riposte%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;parried&lt;/a&gt;.\nThey may also suddenly rise both of their pincers and erect their bodies altogether, followed by slamming themselves onto the ground with great force. This attack is amply telegraphed and is easily avoidable by &lt;a href=\"rolling\"&gt;rolling&lt;/a&gt; away, though the crab will be open for a critical attack while it is building up this move. Approach the monster at this moment and attack it, triggering the critical and dealing extreme damage to it.\nTheir grab may result in an instant death if not careful. This attack is telegraphed with the creature suddenly drooling foamy bubbles from its mouth while slowly building up with its larger pincer. The player should prioritize in rolling away as soon as they detect this move.\nIf the player befriended the &lt;a href=\"Giant%20Archer%20of%20the%20Undead%20Settlement\"&gt;giant archer&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"Undead%20Settlement\"&gt;Undead Settlement&lt;/a&gt;, he will aid in killing the Great Crab in the &lt;a href=\"Farron%20Keep\"&gt;Farron Keep&lt;/a&gt;, which guards the &lt;a href=\"Crown%20of%20Dusk%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Crown of Dusk&lt;/a&gt; among other items.\nIf the player wants to fight those encountered in the &lt;a href=\"Smouldering%20Lake\"&gt;Smouldering Lake&lt;/a&gt;, it's recommended to make a detour through the &lt;a href=\"Demon%20Ruins%20%28bonfire%29\"&gt;Demon Ruins&lt;/a&gt; first and turn off the ballista. A series of ledges can be found near it, which the player can drop onto to head back to the lake and near from where the Great Crabs are.\nDrops.\n&lt;tabber&gt;Road of Sacrifices =\n&lt;/tabber&gt;"}
{"id": "133923", "revid": "51254358", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=133923", "title": "Great Deep Soul", "text": "Great Deep Soul (\u5f37\u3044\u6df1\u307f\u306e\u30bd\u30a6\u30eb) is a &lt;a href=\"Sorcery%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;sorcery&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nObtained as a reward for reaching Rank 1 in the &lt;a href=\"Aldrich%20Faithful\"&gt;Aldrich Faithful&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Covenant%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;covenant&lt;/a&gt;. To achieve this, the player must offer 10 &lt;a href=\"Human%20Dregs\"&gt;Human Dregs&lt;/a&gt; to &lt;a href=\"Archdeacon%20McDonnell\"&gt;Archdeacon McDonnell&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"Water%20Reserve\"&gt;Water Reserve&lt;/a&gt;. \nEffect.\nQuickly fires powerful darkened soul dregs that home in on the target, inflicting 1.3 times the &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Buff\"&gt;Spell Buff&lt;/a&gt; of the &lt;a href=\"Catalysts%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;catalyst&lt;/a&gt; as &lt;a href=\"Dark%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Dark&lt;/a&gt; damage upon impact. Has a short cast time similar to &lt;a href=\"Deep%20Soul\"&gt;Deep Soul&lt;/a&gt;, and can benefit from &lt;a href=\"Faith%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Faith&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Parameter%20Bonus%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;scaling&lt;/a&gt; as well as Dark bonus depending on the catalyst used.\nUse.\nSingle player.\nAn upscaled version of Deep Soul, Great Deep Soul serves a similar purpose to Deep Soul, in giving &lt;a href=\"Intelligence%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Intelligence&lt;/a&gt; builds a source of non-&lt;a href=\"Magic%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Magic&lt;/a&gt; damage.\nOnline gameplay.\nLike Deep Soul, the spell travels slowly but costs little &lt;a href=\"Focus%20Points\"&gt;FP&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Stamina%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;stamina&lt;/a&gt; to cast, and homes in on the target. The fast cast animation also allows it to be useful without having to boost casting speed by equipping a &lt;a href=\"Sage%20Ring\"&gt;Sage Ring&lt;/a&gt;.\nAs with Deep Soul, the slow homing nature of the spell makes it powerful for applying pressure against human opponents, who must pay attention to and focus on dodging the projectile for a longer period of time than they would have to against a &lt;a href=\"Soul%20Arrow%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Soul Arrow&lt;/a&gt;-type spell. The slow travel speed also allows the caster to quickly close the distance and bring a melee weapon to bear, using the projectile as a roll-catching mechanism.\n&lt;br&gt;\nDescription.\n&lt;tabber&gt;Official translation=\n&lt;/tabber&gt;"}
{"id": "133922", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=133922", "title": "Great Farron Dart", "text": "Great Farron Dart is a &lt;a href=\"Sorcery%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;sorcery&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nSold by &lt;a href=\"Orbeck%20of%20Vinheim\"&gt;Orbeck of Vinheim&lt;/a&gt; for 2,000 &lt;a href=\"Souls%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;souls&lt;/a&gt; once he has been given the &lt;a href=\"Sage%27s%20Scroll\"&gt;Sage's Scroll&lt;/a&gt;.\nEffect.\nAn upscaled version of &lt;a href=\"Farron%20Dart\"&gt;Farron Dart&lt;/a&gt;. Fires a powerful soul dart at the target, dealing 0.59 times the &lt;a href=\"Catalysts%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;catalyst's&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Buff\"&gt;Spell Buff&lt;/a&gt; as &lt;a href=\"Magic%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Magic&lt;/a&gt; damage. Like Farron Dart, it cannot &lt;a href=\"stagger\"&gt;stagger&lt;/a&gt; enemies hit by the projectiles but casts extremely quickly and costs little &lt;a href=\"Focus%20Points\"&gt;FP&lt;/a&gt;, and like Farron Dart it has special &lt;a href=\"rolling\"&gt;rolling&lt;/a&gt; and running attacks which make it extremely flexible.\nThe spell's larger damage multiplier compared to Farron Dart allows it to break through low values of Magic Defense more easily (such as against players that do not level &lt;a href=\"Intelligence%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Intelligence&lt;/a&gt;). As a result, it inflicts damage that increases roughly in tandem with its FP cost, meaning that it can still deal respectable damage without being as inefficient as the multiplier difference would suggest.\n&lt;br&gt;"}
{"id": "11889", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=11889", "title": "Great Feline", "text": "Great Felines are in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\".\nLocation.\nIn a secluded area of &lt;a href=\"Darkroot%20Garden\"&gt;Darkroot Garden&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0connecting the area with the &lt;a href=\"Mushroom%20Parent\"&gt;Mushroom people&lt;/a&gt; and the bridge leading to the &lt;a href=\"Hydra\"&gt;Hydra&lt;/a&gt; past two ladders; they are perched up on a nearby, inaccessible plateau.\nDescription.\nGreat Felines are large cat-like beasts similar in appearance to &lt;a href=\"Alvina\"&gt;Alvina&lt;/a&gt;. Their size does little to hinder their speed as they can rapidly pin-point their target and perform quick strikes, such as a deadly spinning attack, which allows them to travel great distances very quickly. The slower attacks are more predictable.\nStrategy.\nStaying on the outskirts can allow the player to quickly retreat behind the trees, where the Felines will not venture.\nMoving along the cliff beyond Alvina's structure (when approaching from the sealed door requiring the &lt;a href=\"Crest%20of%20Artorias\"&gt;Crest of Artorias&lt;/a&gt;), will eventually take the player to a ledge overlooking the area containing the Great Felines. From here, it is possible to engage them with ranged attacks or magic. The felines will be unable to pursue the player when attacking from this location.\nAlternatively, if coming from the bridge, the player will be able to see the three felines at a distance before they turn hostile. The player can freely snipe the two that are further back and they won't react. The one on the front, however, will undoubtedly climb down to attack if harmed. Using &lt;a href=\"Poison%20Arrow\"&gt;poison arrows&lt;/a&gt; is recommended. It only takes about three to five arrows to poison them and then the player may add to the damage by using cheaper arrows.\nIt is safer to engage Great Felines one at a time. Venturing too close to where they are can trigger a three-versus-one encounter."}
{"id": "3730", "revid": "357115", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3730", "title": "Great Fireball", "text": "Great Fireball is a &lt;a href=\"Pyromancy%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;Pyromancy&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nSold by &lt;a href=\"Quelana%20of%20Izalith\"&gt;Quelana of Izalith&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Blighttown\"&gt;Blighttown&lt;/a&gt; for 20,000 &lt;a href=\"soul\"&gt;soul&lt;/a&gt;s.\nGeneral information.\nAs with its cousins, Great Fireball has a long windup time that can be shortened through investment in the &lt;a href=\"Dexterity%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;Dexterity&lt;/a&gt; stat. Great Fireball is an upgrade of &lt;a href=\"Fire%20Orb\"&gt;Fire Orb&lt;/a&gt; and an advanced ranged pyromancy. It deals more damage and noticeably larger area of effect. Great Fireball has a fire attack power of 3.0 times the Pyromancy Flame's magic adjust.\nOverview.\nSince it is the strongest ranged pyromancy bar &lt;a href=\"Great%20Chaos%20Fireball\"&gt;Great Chaos Fireball&lt;/a&gt; and requires less attunement, Great Fireball is a very popular pyromancy for use in &lt;a href=\"Player%20versus%20Player\"&gt;PvP&lt;/a&gt;. It is somewhat less common in PvE, where the limited amount of casts per slot limits its utility for long journeys. Great Fireball also boasts impressive poise damage unlike the lesser Fireballs, being able to stun opponents with up to and including 80 poise, allowing it to easily stagger most players in a single hit.\nAs with its lesser cousins, Great Fireball is hindered by its long windup time, arced trajectory, and slow projectile speed, so it is important to plan ahead when using this pyromancy."}
{"id": "56950", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=56950", "title": "Great Fireball (Dark Souls II)", "text": "Great Fireball is a &lt;a href=\"Pyromancy%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;pyromancy&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nGeneral Information.\nThis spell conjures a large fireball which is hurled at the target. The fireball deals good fire damage and has splash damage. This can be considered a pyromancer's bread and butter spell, similar to how &lt;a href=\"Great%20Heavy%20Soul%20Arrow%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Great Heavy Soul Arrow&lt;/a&gt; can be considered the same for a sorcerer, though this spell does have fewer casts per slot. \nAttunement milestones.\nLike all other spells, the amount of casts per slot increases upon reaching certain &lt;a href=\"Attunement%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Attunement&lt;/a&gt; milestones:"}
