{"id": "3147", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3147", "title": "Great Hammers", "text": "Great Hammers are a type of &lt;a href=\"Weapons%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;weapon&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\".\nOverview.\nAll Great Hammers are &lt;a href=\"Strike\"&gt;Strike&lt;/a&gt;-type weapons. They are among the largest weapons, and so their attacks are extremely powerful, but slow. This also means that they produce large amounts of damage and have good &lt;a href=\"stagger\"&gt;stagger&lt;/a&gt;ing power. They are designed for single powerful hits, not quick combos. Their high starting and ending lag can make great hammers tricky to use against nimble opponents. Great Hammers usually need to be wielded with both hands, as they have very high &lt;a href=\"Strength%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;Strength&lt;/a&gt; requirements.\nGreat Hammers.\n&lt;tabber&gt;\nDetailed=\nCondensed=\nUpgraded=\n&lt;/tabber&gt;"}
{"id": "52286", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=52286", "title": "Great Hammers (Dark Souls II)", "text": "Great Hammers are a type of &lt;a href=\"Weapons%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;weapon&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\"."}
{"id": "133826", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=133826", "title": "Great Hammers (Dark Souls III)", "text": "Great Hammers are a type of &lt;a href=\"Weapons%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;weapon&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nThe largest and most powerful class of ultra weapon, great hammers possess the heftiest &lt;a href=\"Poise%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Poise&lt;/a&gt; health and inflict the most Poise damage of all ultra weapons, making them the strongest &lt;a href=\"Hyper%20Armor\"&gt;Hyper Armor&lt;/a&gt; weapons in the game. With the exception of the &lt;a href=\"Pickaxe%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Pickaxe&lt;/a&gt;, all great hammers inflict &lt;a href=\"Strike%20%28damage%20type%29\"&gt;Strike&lt;/a&gt; damage, which is the least-resisted &lt;a href=\"physical\"&gt;physical&lt;/a&gt; damage type on the vast majority of all &lt;a href=\"Armor%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;armor&lt;/a&gt;, allowing these weapons to inflict much more damage than their peers. Like &lt;a href=\"Greataxes%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;greataxes&lt;/a&gt;, great hammers possess very powerful vertical swings that can &lt;a href=\"stagger\"&gt;stagger&lt;/a&gt; foes in an area around the impact point, which can interrupt enemies attempting to outspace the wielder's swings even if they take no damage.\nHowever, they are extremely slow to bring to bear, meaning that they must be used with care due to how vulnerable the wielder becomes between attacks. Their extreme &lt;a href=\"weight\"&gt;weight&lt;/a&gt; and immense &lt;a href=\"Stamina%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;stamina&lt;/a&gt; consumption also means that heavy &lt;a href=\"Endurance%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Endurance&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Vitality%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Vitality&lt;/a&gt; investment is mandatory, and like other ultra weapons they &lt;a href=\"Parameter%20Bonus%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;scale&lt;/a&gt; primarily with &lt;a href=\"Strength%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Strength&lt;/a&gt;.\nWithin the great hammers weapon class, there also exists a sub-class of three Ultra Great Hammers, which possess increased Poise health, making them extremely difficult to interrupt once they are in motion. These weapons, &lt;a href=\"Smough%27s%20Great%20Hammer\"&gt;Smough's Great Hammer&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Morne%27s%20Great%20Hammer\"&gt;Morne's Great Hammer&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Ledo%27s%20Great%20Hammer\"&gt;Ledo's Great Hammer&lt;/a&gt;, are immensely heavy and require copious amounts of Strength to wield, but when used properly can dominate an area around them, becoming monsters on the battlefield.\nLike their &lt;a href=\"Hammers%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;smaller cousins&lt;/a&gt;, the primary &lt;a href=\"skill\"&gt;skill&lt;/a&gt; used by great hammers is &lt;a href=\"Perseverance%20%28skill%29\"&gt;Perseverance&lt;/a&gt;, providing instant Hyper Armor to give the wielder increased survivability.\nGreat Hammers.\n&lt;br&gt;"}
{"id": "3029", "revid": "51254358", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3029", "title": "Great Heal", "text": "Great Heal (\u9650\u3089\u308c\u305f\u5927\u56de\u5fa9) is a &lt;a href=\"Miracle%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;miracle&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nSold by &lt;a href=\"Reah%20of%20Thorolund\"&gt;Reah of Thorolund&lt;/a&gt; for 10,000 &lt;a href=\"Soul%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;soul&lt;/a&gt;s after the player rescues her.\nGeneral information.\nGreat Heal restores a large amount of HP, that is 8x the MagAdjust of the equipped &lt;a href=\"Talismans\"&gt;talisman&lt;/a&gt;. It has an identical casting length as &lt;a href=\"Heal\"&gt;Heal&lt;/a&gt;, but with a more luminous animation.\nGreat Heal benefits from &lt;a href=\"Miracle%20Synergy\"&gt;miracle synergy&lt;/a&gt;. The healing multiplier increases by 0.25 for each level of miracle synergy, granting up to a total of 9x MagAdjust in healing.\nOverview.\nGreat Heal has fewer casts than its counterpart, &lt;a href=\"Heal\"&gt;Heal&lt;/a&gt;. Players may welcome the large amount of extra HP it provides; however, Heal may be a better choice if players rely on the miracles just to top them off in out-of-combat situations due to its higher amount of casts.\nDescription.\n&lt;tabber&gt;Official translation=\n&lt;/tabber&gt;"}
{"id": "52311", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=52311", "title": "Great Heal (Dark Souls II)", "text": "Great Heal is a\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Miracles%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;miracle&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0in\u00a0\"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nGeneral information.\nThis is an advanced form of &lt;a href=\"Heal%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Heal&lt;/a&gt;. It is the strongest of the healing miracles, as it has the most casts and restores the most &lt;a href=\"HP%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;HP&lt;/a&gt; to its caster.\nAttunement milestones.\nLike all other spells, the amount of casts per slot increases upon reaching certain &lt;a href=\"Attunement%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Attunement&lt;/a&gt; milestones:"}
{"id": "133474", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=133474", "title": "Great Heal (Dark Souls III)", "text": "Great Heal is a &lt;a href=\"Miracle%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;miracle&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nFound in &lt;a href=\"Irithyll%20of%20the%20Boreal%20Valley\"&gt;Irithyll of the Boreal Valley&lt;/a&gt;.\nUpon reaching the swamp area below the city, past the dark room filled with &lt;a href=\"Irithyllian%20Slave\"&gt;Irithyllian Slave&lt;/a&gt;s, follow the right side to find the corpse of a &lt;a href=\"Man-grub\"&gt;Man-grub&lt;/a&gt; holding the spell. It is guarded by two &lt;a href=\"Sewer%20Centipede\"&gt;Sewer Centipede&lt;/a&gt;s.\nEffect.\nRestores &lt;a href=\"Hit%20Points%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;HP&lt;/a&gt; for the caster and nearby allies equal to 5.5 times the &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Buff\"&gt;Spell Buff&lt;/a&gt; of the catalyst, and consumes 205 &lt;a href=\"Endurance%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;stamina&lt;/a&gt;. For catalysts that also scale with &lt;a href=\"Intelligence%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Intelligence&lt;/a&gt; such as &lt;a href=\"Crystal%20Chime\"&gt;Crystal Chime&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Sunless%20Talisman\"&gt;Sunless Talisman&lt;/a&gt;, only the Spell Buff from &lt;a href=\"Faith%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Faith&lt;/a&gt; is taken into account.\nDue to the high stamina cost of this spell, action after casting is severely restricted, preventing the caster from rolling or attacking immediately after.\n&lt;br&gt;"}
