{"id": "51828", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=51828", "title": "Great Heal Excerpt (Dark Souls II)", "text": "Great Heal Excerpt is a\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Miracles%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;miracle&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0in\u00a0\"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nPurchased from\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Licia%20of%20Lindeldt\"&gt;Licia of Lindeldt&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0for 4,500 &lt;a href=\"Souls%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;souls&lt;/a&gt;.\nGeneral information.\nWhen cast, Great Heal Excerpt will heal the player for a large amount of health.\nEffectively being a lighter version of &lt;a href=\"Great%20Heal%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Great Heal&lt;/a&gt;, it requires far less &lt;a href=\"Faith%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Faith&lt;/a&gt; to cast, and doesn't force the player to kneel while doing so, although they are still slowed to a walk. However, it has fewer casts and doesn't heal friendly players during &lt;a href=\"Cooperative%20Gameplay%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;co-op&lt;/a&gt;. The &lt;a href=\"Casting%20Speed\"&gt;Casting Speed&lt;/a&gt; is the same for both &lt;a href=\"Miracles%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Miracles&lt;/a&gt;.\nAlthough Great Heal Excerpt can be a great boon in a pinch, it is recommended to replace it with Great Heal once it becomes available, as the ability to move while casting will rarely make up for the reduction in casts, or the inability to heal other players. It may find some use in &lt;a href=\"Player%20versus%20Player%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;PvP&lt;/a&gt; as the standing animation can be mistaken for other spells like &lt;a href=\"Heavenly%20Thunder\"&gt;Heavenly Thunder&lt;/a&gt;.\nAttunement milestones.\nLike all other spells, the amount of casts per slot increases upon reaching certain &lt;a href=\"Attunement%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Attunement&lt;/a&gt; milestones:"}
{"id": "4510", "revid": "357123", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4510", "title": "Great Heavy Soul Arrow", "text": "Great Heavy Soul Arrow (\u5f37\u3044\u30bd\u30a6\u30eb\u306e\u592a\u77e2) is a &lt;a href=\"Sorcery%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;Sorcery&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\".\nGeneral information.\nGreat Heavy Soul Arrow requires 16 intelligence to use and has 8 uses per copy. It has the same slow &lt;a href=\"cast%20time\"&gt;cast time&lt;/a&gt; as &lt;a href=\"Heavy%20Soul%20Arrow\"&gt;Heavy Soul Arrow&lt;/a&gt;, but deals correspondingly the greatest damage per cast out of all the &lt;a href=\"Soul%20Arrow%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;Soul Arrow&lt;/a&gt; variants.\nGreat Heavy Soul Arrow's primary usage is as a high damage first-strike attack against unaware foes, and as a combat spell best deployed against enemies with slow attacks and long recoveries. It has a magic attack power of 2.4 times the catalyst's magic adjust. While it has a relatively low total quantity of damage per &lt;a href=\"Attunement%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;attunement&lt;/a&gt; slot in comparison to the other Soul Arrow spells, its high damage per cast makes it useful at powering through the defenses of highly magic-resistant foes.\nDescription.\n&lt;tabber&gt;Official translation=\n&lt;/tabber&gt;"}
