{"id": "2216", "revid": "56333033", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=2216", "title": "Chaos Servant", "text": "The Chaos Servant (\u6df7\u6c8c\u306e\u5f93\u8005) is a &lt;a href=\"covenant\"&gt;covenant&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\". Chaos Servants dedicate themselves to the &lt;a href=\"Quelaag%27s%20Sister\"&gt;Fair Lady&lt;/a&gt; and provide her with &lt;a href=\"Humanity%20%28mechanic%29\"&gt;humanity&lt;/a&gt;.\nRequirements.\nThe player must not have killed &lt;a href=\"Quelaag%27s%20Sister\"&gt;Quelaag's Sister&lt;/a&gt;.\nHow to join.\nAfter defeating &lt;a href=\"Chaos%20Witch%20Quelaag\"&gt;Chaos Witch Quelaag&lt;/a&gt;, reach the circular room beneath the &lt;a href=\"Bells%20of%20Awakening\"&gt;Bell of Awakening&lt;/a&gt; where there are cobwebs lining eggs on the sides. The wall to the right is &lt;a href=\"Illusory%20Wall\"&gt;illusory&lt;/a&gt;. Inside, there will be an egg-infected man named &lt;a href=\"Eingyi\"&gt;Eingyi&lt;/a&gt;. The player must answer \"Yes\" to his question in order for him to move. If the player has answered \"No\", quitting and reloading will prompt Eingyi to pose his question again. The player may also kill him and join without repercussion. However, this will cost the player his services. Talking to &lt;a href=\"Quelaag%27s%20Sister\"&gt;Quelaag's Sister&lt;/a&gt; will give the option to join the covenant.\nBenefits.\n&lt;a href=\"Humanity%20%28item%29\"&gt;Humanities&lt;/a&gt; are offered to &lt;a href=\"Quelaag%27s%20Sister\"&gt;Quelaag's Sister&lt;/a&gt; to gain ranks in the Chaos Servant Covenant."}
{"id": "53100", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=53100", "title": "Chaos Set", "text": "The Chaos Set\u00a0is a &lt;a href=\"Light%20Armor%20Sets%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;light armor set&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nGifted by\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Royal%20Sorcerer%20Navlaan\"&gt;Royal Sorcerer Navlaan&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0upon speaking to him while in &lt;a href=\"Hollow\"&gt;Hollow&lt;/a&gt; form after completing his assassination quests. Alternatively, it can be acquired by releasing Navlaan, killing him, and purchasing it from\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Merchant%20Hag%20Melentia\"&gt;Merchant Hag Melentia&lt;/a&gt;. (Navlaan drops the hood upon death)\nCharacteristics.\nThe Chaos Set is one of the most balanced &lt;a href=\"Armor%20Sets%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;sets&lt;/a&gt; in the game. It boasts exceptional &lt;a href=\"Fire%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;fire&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Dark%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;dark&lt;/a&gt; defenses, as well as good &lt;a href=\"physical%20defense\"&gt;physical defense&lt;/a&gt;s for its very low &lt;a href=\"weight\"&gt;weight&lt;/a&gt;, and high &lt;a href=\"Magic%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;magic&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Lightning%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;lightning&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"petrification\"&gt;petrification&lt;/a&gt; resistance, as well as &lt;a href=\"Poison%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;poison&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Bleed%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;bleed&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Curse%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;curse&lt;/a&gt; resistance. Its only downsides are that its physical defense will not be enough to protect the wearer from hard-hitting raw physical attacks, so dodging is an absolute must, and it lacks any &lt;a href=\"Poise%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;poise&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "61898", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=61898", "title": "Chaos Shield", "text": "The Chaos Shield is a &lt;a href=\"Medium%20Shields%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;medium shield&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\".\n&lt;tabber&gt; Dark Souls II=\n&lt;/tabber&gt;\nAvailability.\nA rare drop from the caged &lt;a href=\"Enhanced%20Undead\"&gt;Enhanced Undead&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Aldia%27s%20Keep\"&gt;Aldia's Keep&lt;/a&gt;. The drop rate is extremely low, even with a very high amount of &lt;a href=\"Item%20Discovery%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;item discovery&lt;/a&gt;; &lt;a href=\"bonfire%20ascetic\"&gt;bonfire ascetic&lt;/a&gt;s may need to be used.\nIn \"\", it is sold by &lt;a href=\"Felkin%20the%20Outcast\"&gt;Felkin the Outcast&lt;/a&gt; for 7,500 &lt;a href=\"Souls%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;souls&lt;/a&gt;. \nCharacteristics.\nAlong with the transitional update in \"Scholar of the First Sin\", the defensive statistics (namely the &lt;a href=\"Physical%20Damage\"&gt;Physical&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Magic%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Magic&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Lightning%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Lightning&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Dark%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Dark&lt;/a&gt; damage reductions) of the &lt;a href=\"Shields%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;shield&lt;/a&gt; were also buffed, while the &lt;a href=\"stability\"&gt;stability&lt;/a&gt; was significantly reduced from 45 to 30.\nAs of currently, the Chaos Shield stands on a very odd place within the category of standard shields.\nIt has great Magic and Lightning Resistances, excellent Dark Resistance, and yet though it has an innate &lt;a href=\"infusion\"&gt;infusion&lt;/a&gt; in Fire its Fire Reduction is lower than expected. What makes it even stranger is how infusing this shield with certain elements changes it in bizarre instances, the most prominent though are explained in the \"Notes\" section of this page.\nIt is one of the few shields that when infused with &lt;a href=\"Darknight%20Stone\"&gt;Dark&lt;/a&gt; will grant immunity to Dark damage."}
{"id": "3630", "revid": "51254358", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3630", "title": "Chaos Storm", "text": "Chaos Storm (\u6df7\u6c8c\u306e\u5d50) is a &lt;a href=\"Pyromancy%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;Pyromancy&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\".\nGeneral Information.\nChaos Storm requires two attunement slots to use. It is very similar to &lt;a href=\"Firestorm\"&gt;Firestorm&lt;/a&gt;, having twenty \"casts\" (using 17 per full cast, but can vary from 3 to 17 on occasion), dealing slightly stronger initial damage and then leaving pools of lava. The pillars have a fire attack power of 3.6 times the Pyromancy Flame's magic adjust and the lava pools have a fire attack power of 2.0 times the Pyromancy Flame's magic adjust. In terms of initial damage, &lt;a href=\"Firestorm\"&gt;Firestorm&lt;/a&gt; deals the lowest initial damage, then Chaos Storm, followed by &lt;a href=\"Fire%20Tempest\"&gt;Fire Tempest&lt;/a&gt;. However, if the enemy lingers to take the lava damage, the total damage can outdo Fire Tempest, thus giving this pyromancy the highest damage potential Storm spell. This makes it an extremely viable spell for large, slow moving enemies. \nOverview.\nChaos Storm is useful as firestorm when it comes to knockback, dealing damage, and granting players breathing space. In addition, it is also useful for temporary area denial by creating lava around the caster. Like Firestorm it can prove useful against large enemies and bosses such as &lt;a href=\"Seath%20the%20Scaleless\"&gt;Seath the Scaleless&lt;/a&gt; as more than one pillar can hit the enemy.\nDescription.\n&lt;tabber&gt;Official translation=\n&lt;/tabber&gt;"}
{"id": "55797", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=55797", "title": "Chaos Storm (Dark Souls II)", "text": "Chaos Storm is a\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Pyromancy%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;pyromancy&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0in\u00a0\"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nFound in a chest on one of the lava trails in the\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Iron%20Keep\"&gt;Iron Keep&lt;/a&gt;, past the second &lt;a href=\"Bonfire%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;bonfire&lt;/a&gt;. As the item is in a chest which takes time to open, which in itself is fairly far from safe land, very high &lt;a href=\"Fire%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;fire&lt;/a&gt; resistance is necessary to retrieve the pyromancy and survive. The pots near a nearby &lt;a href=\"Mimic\"&gt;Mimic&lt;/a&gt; can be broken to release water and temporarily give the player increased fire resistance; &lt;a href=\"Flash%20Sweat%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Flash Sweat&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Small%20Orange%20Burr\"&gt;Small Orange Burr&lt;/a&gt;s, &lt;a href=\"Great%20Magic%20Barrier%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Great Magic Barrier&lt;/a&gt;, and appropriate armor can help too.\nAnother reliable way of accessing the same resistance buff provided by water is to use a\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Pharros%27%20Lockstone\"&gt;Pharros' Lockstone&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0on one of the contraptions in the area to get a huge fire resistance boost.\nAlso consider chugging an &lt;a href=\"Estus%20Flask%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Estus Flask&lt;/a&gt; before opening the chest, as the animation is lengthy.\nVideo.\n&lt;a href=\"https%3A//www.youtube.com/watch%3Fv%3D8dqfv5c6k6M%26amp%3Blist%3DUU0O7NmsbB_FiasJGO8Quktw\"&gt;Video: location and how to get&lt;/a&gt;\nGeneral information.\nSimilarly to its cousin from \"Dark Souls\", Chaos Storm is essentially a more powerful version of &lt;a href=\"Firestorm%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Firestorm&lt;/a&gt;, creating numerous pillars of fire around the caster. Casting Chaos Storm also leaves behind many short-lived pools of lava, which damage any enemy that steps in them.\nConsidering the higher amount of casts and it requires only one slot to attune, this spell is often more efficient than its more powerful sibling, &lt;a href=\"Outcry\"&gt;Outcry&lt;/a&gt;, as you are ultimately getting more damage for your slot as well as having room for another spell. Furthermore, as this shares the same start up animation as &lt;a href=\"Fire%20Snake\"&gt;Fire Snake&lt;/a&gt;, in &lt;a href=\"PvP%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;PvP&lt;/a&gt; one could constantly switch between these two spells to catch a player off guard.\nAttunement milestones.\nLike all other spells, the amount of casts per slot increases upon reaching certain &lt;a href=\"Attunement%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Attunement&lt;/a&gt; milestones:"}
{"id": "133557", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=133557", "title": "Chaos Storm (Dark Souls III)", "text": "Chaos Storm is a &lt;a href=\"Pyromancy%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;pyromancy&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nSold by &lt;a href=\"Cornyx%20of%20the%20Great%20Swamp\"&gt;Cornyx of the Great Swamp&lt;/a&gt; for 12,000 &lt;a href=\"Soul%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;souls&lt;/a&gt; once he has been given the &lt;a href=\"Izalith%20Pyromancy%20Tome\"&gt;Izalith Pyromancy Tome&lt;/a&gt;.\nEffect.\nThe caster focuses power in the catalyst, and then lays down a sweeping wide blanket of erupting fire pillars. Each pillar will inflict 1.95 times the &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Buff\"&gt;Spell Buff&lt;/a&gt; of the catalyst as &lt;a href=\"Fire%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Fire&lt;/a&gt; damage and knock any targets skyward. After eruption, a lava pool will persist at the eruption point, inflicting 0.9 times the Spell Buff of the catalyst as Fire damage to any enemy that touches it.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Focus%20Points\"&gt;FP&lt;/a&gt; cost of this spell is expressed per-pillar. Upon initial successful cast, the spell will consume 13 FP (11 FP with the &lt;a href=\"Dusk%20Crown%20Ring%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Dusk Crown Ring&lt;/a&gt; equipped), and additional Focus is consumed as each pillar materializes. A maximum of 15 pillars (including the one created by the initial cast) can be conjured in a single cast of this spell, resulting in total consumption of 55 FP (53 FP with Dusk Crown Ring equipped).\n&lt;br&gt;"}
