{"id": "130350", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=130350", "title": "Charcoal Pine Resin (Dark Souls III)", "text": "Charcoal Pine Resins are consumable in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nDescription.\nApplies 85 &lt;a href=\"Fire%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Fire&lt;/a&gt; damage to right-hand weapon. Buff lasts for 60 seconds."}
{"id": "139897", "revid": "5064773", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=139897", "title": "Charge", "text": "Charge is a &lt;a href=\"skill\"&gt;skill&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nUsage.\nOffline gameplay.\nUseful to inflict high damage. Since it consists of a heavy sprint with the weapon set as a lance, it could also be used to cover long distances. And because it hits multiple times, it is proficient at breaking through &lt;a href=\"Shields%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;shields&lt;/a&gt;.\nOnline gameplay.\nSimilar usage as in offline play. Can also be used as a trick to scare the opponent."}
{"id": "47151", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=47151", "title": "Chariot Lance", "text": "The Chariot Lance\u00a0is a &lt;a href=\"Lances\"&gt;lance&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nAcquired by trading the &lt;a href=\"Executioner%20Chariot%20Soul\"&gt;Executioner Chariot Soul&lt;/a&gt; and 1,500 souls to &lt;a href=\"Straid%20of%20Olaphis\"&gt;Straid of Olaphis&lt;/a&gt;.\nCharacteristics.\nThe Chariot Lance's moveset consists mostly of thrusting attacks, the one handed strong attack follow up combination being an exception. What it lacks in a varied moveset it makes up for with its damage and its ability to hit multiple times per input in its strong attack and running attack. Although individual hits deal average damage, multiple hits can quickly prove deadly, as it will simultaneously build up &lt;a href=\"Bleed%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Bleed&lt;/a&gt; quite quickly on an enemy. For this reason, the &lt;a href=\"Crest%20of%20Blood\"&gt;Crest of Blood&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Shadow%20Gauntlets%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Shadow Gauntlets&lt;/a&gt; make this weapon even more effective."}
{"id": "99962", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=99962", "title": "Charred Loyce Armor", "text": "&lt;onlyinclude&gt;&lt;/onlyinclude&gt;\nThe\u00a0Charred Loyce Armor\u00a0is a piece in\u00a0\"&lt;a href=\"Crown%20of%20the%20Ivory%20King%20%28DLC%29\"&gt;Dark Souls II: Crown of the Ivory King&lt;/a&gt;\". It is part of the\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Charred%20Loyce%20Set\"&gt;Charred Loyce Set&lt;/a&gt;.\nAvailability.\nDropped by\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Charred%20Loyce%20Knight\"&gt;Charred Loyce Knight&lt;/a&gt;s\u00a0in &lt;a href=\"the%20Old%20Chaos\"&gt;the Old Chaos&lt;/a&gt;.\nCharacteristics.\nThe Charred Loyce Armor offers very high &lt;a href=\"physical%20defense\"&gt;physical defense&lt;/a&gt;, close to the amount that &lt;a href=\"Havel%27s%20Armor%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Havel's Armor&lt;/a&gt; provides, though with a much reduced &lt;a href=\"weight\"&gt;weight&lt;/a&gt;, only weighing in at 12.8 units, in contrast to Havel's 19.5 units of weight. The Charred Loyce Armor also boasts a considerable amount of &lt;a href=\"Fire%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Fire&lt;/a&gt; defense. Wearing it also grants a &lt;a href=\"Health%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Health&lt;/a&gt; Absorption Bonus, similar to the effect provided by the &lt;a href=\"Butcher%27s%20Knife\"&gt;Butcher's Knife&lt;/a&gt; which can be stacked with another pieces of this armor.\nUpgrades.\nRequires &lt;a href=\"Twinkling%20Titanite%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Twinkling Titanite&lt;/a&gt; per upgrade.\n&lt;onlyinclude&gt;&lt;/onlyinclude&gt;"}
