{"id": "60580", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=60580", "title": "Claws (weapon)", "text": "The Claws are a &lt;a href=\"Claws%20%28weapon%20type%29\"&gt;claw&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nCan be purchased from &lt;a href=\"Laddersmith%20Gilligan\"&gt;Laddersmith Gilligan&lt;/a&gt; for 1,500 &lt;a href=\"Souls%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;souls&lt;/a&gt;.\nCharacteristics.\nAlthough the description states the user attacks with a scratching motion, it uses the standard fist &lt;a href=\"Moveset%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;moveset&lt;/a&gt;.\nWhen fully reinforced and &lt;a href=\"infuse\"&gt;infuse&lt;/a&gt;d with &lt;a href=\"Bleed%20Stone\"&gt;Bleed&lt;/a&gt;, the Claws can easily &lt;a href=\"Bleed%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;bleed&lt;/a&gt; most opponents. The high bleed &lt;a href=\"build-up\"&gt;build-up&lt;/a&gt; can be further augmented by the &lt;a href=\"Crest%20of%20Blood\"&gt;Crest of Blood&lt;/a&gt; as well as the &lt;a href=\"Shadow%20Gauntlets%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Shadow Gauntlets&lt;/a&gt;. When &lt;a href=\"power-stance\"&gt;power-stance&lt;/a&gt;d, these weapons inflict a high amount of bleed very quickly due to their attack speed."}
{"id": "52277", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=52277", "title": "Claws (weapon type)", "text": "Claws are a type of &lt;a href=\"Weapons%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;weapon&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\"."}
{"id": "2047", "revid": "56333033", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=2047", "title": "Claymore", "text": "The Claymore is a &lt;a href=\"Greatswords%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;greatsword&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nThe Claymore is found on a corpse on the bridge in the &lt;a href=\"Undead%20Burg\"&gt;Undead Burg&lt;/a&gt; near the &lt;a href=\"Hellkite%20Dragon\"&gt;Hellkite Drake&lt;/a&gt;.\nCharacteristics.\nClaymore is one of the few true Quality Scaling weapons at 51% &lt;a href=\"Strength%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;Strength&lt;/a&gt; and 51% &lt;a href=\"Dexterity%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;Dexterity&lt;/a&gt; scaling. This makes it a good choice for players opting for a 27 Str 40 Dex Quality Build. This weapon will deal slightly less damage than &lt;a href=\"Bastard%20Sword\"&gt;Bastard Sword&lt;/a&gt; at the same stat investment, but has shorter reach. A more stat efficient version of this Greatsword is &lt;a href=\"Man-serpent%20Greatsword\"&gt;Man Serpent Greatsword&lt;/a&gt; which only requires 27 Strength two-handed to deal the same damage as both Claymore and Bastard Sword at 27 Str and 40 Dex while two-handed. \nUpgrades.\nScaling Percentage Values.\nThe following chart lists the scaling percentages when this weapon is fully upgraded. Be advised that:"}
{"id": "57305", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=57305", "title": "Claymore (Dark Souls II)", "text": "The Claymore is a &lt;a href=\"Greatswords%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;greatsword&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nSold by &lt;a href=\"Vengarl%20of%20Forossa\"&gt;Vengarl&lt;/a&gt; in the fog section of the &lt;a href=\"Shaded%20Woods\"&gt;Shaded Woods&lt;/a&gt; for 4,300 souls, who can be found by clinging to the left hand wall at the start of the Woods.\nCharacteristics.\nThe Claymore is a utilitarian greatsword with a versatile moveset, good reach, fast swing-speed, and solid damage per hit. It has relatively low &lt;a href=\"Strength%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;strength&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Dexterity%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;dexterity&lt;/a&gt; requirements, making it a viable option for infusions, while the C/C scaling makes it a powerful weapon for dedicated quality builds. These traits lets it fill a similar role to the &lt;a href=\"Bastard%20Sword%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Bastard Sword&lt;/a&gt; which performs similarly, but sacrifices the thrusting attack and some damage for lower weight and slightly lower requirements.\nThe main drawback of the Claymore is that many greatswords found later in the game outclass it in terms of damage. With that said, the Claymore remains a dependable weapon throughout the game, and its relatively low requirements makes it an attractive choice if one does not want to invest stats into using the more powerful elemental greatswords."}
{"id": "131074", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=131074", "title": "Claymore (Dark Souls III)", "text": "The Claymore is a &lt;a href=\"Greatswords%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;greatsword&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nCharacteristics.\nLike in the previous games, the Claymore is a reliable and versatile weapon with great damage output. It's balanced scaling between Strength and Dexterity makes it a great candidate for Refined infusion, and it can be buffed with spells and items. This, coupled with its adaptable moveset and early accessibility, makes the Claymore a promising weapon for any melee build.\nThe Claymore is also one of the longest &lt;a href=\"Greatswords%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Greatswords&lt;/a&gt; in the game, giving it a better reach than most swords of its class. This allows certain character builds to perform multiple attacks and roll away with near-impunity, particularly during boss fights. Its Weapon Arts is particularly effective against enemies with weapons no longer than a Spear as it makes full use of the sword's length. As with its previous incarnations, the Claymore remains exceptional at stun-locking enemies with low poise.\nUpgrades.\nReinforced with ."}
