{"id": "2084", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=2084", "title": "Cleric", "text": "The Cleric is one of the &lt;a href=\"Classes%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;classes&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\".\nClerics can use &lt;a href=\"Miracle%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;miracles&lt;/a&gt; to heal, due to their high starting &lt;a href=\"Faith%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;Faith&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Stats%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;stat&lt;/a&gt; and equipped &lt;a href=\"Talismans\"&gt;Talisman&lt;/a&gt;. They also start with a strong melee weapon in the form of the &lt;a href=\"Mace\"&gt;Mace&lt;/a&gt;, but little in the way of defense. Clerics are well suited to heavier weapon types, such as &lt;a href=\"Hammers%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;Hammers&lt;/a&gt;, as taking on enemies directly with slower weapons is offset by their ability to heal more often than other classes.\nAt an initial level of 2, Clerics have the second-lowest starting level (the lowest being &lt;a href=\"Pyromancer\"&gt;Pyromancer&lt;/a&gt;s) of any class. They start the game as a member of the &lt;a href=\"Way%20of%20White\"&gt;Way of White&lt;/a&gt; covenant.\nJoining the &lt;a href=\"Warrior%20of%20Sunlight\"&gt;Warriors of Sunlight&lt;/a&gt; can allow Clerics to become powerful magical attackers early on in the game, giving them the miracle &lt;a href=\"Lightning%20Spear\"&gt;Lightning Spear&lt;/a&gt;. &lt;a href=\"Astora%27s%20Straight%20Sword\"&gt;Astora's Straight Sword&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Dragon%20Crest%20Shield\"&gt;Dragon Crest Shield&lt;/a&gt; are also very useful early game pick-ups for the Cleric, provided they choose the &lt;a href=\"Master%20Key\"&gt;Master Key&lt;/a&gt; as their gift and enter &lt;a href=\"Valley%20of%20Drakes\"&gt;Valley of Drakes&lt;/a&gt; via &lt;a href=\"New%20Londo%20Ruins\"&gt;New Londo Ruins&lt;/a&gt;. The former scales with Faith, allowing the Cleric to focus exclusively on it, while the latter is a far better shield than that which the Cleric starts with."}
{"id": "130978", "revid": "51254358", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=130978", "title": "Cleric's Candlestick", "text": "The Cleric's Candlestick (\u8056\u8005\u306e\u71ed\u53f0) is a &lt;a href=\"Boss%20Soul%20Items%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;soul-transposed&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Straight%20Swords%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;straight sword&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nObtained by transposing the &lt;a href=\"Soul%20of%20the%20Deacons%20of%20the%20Deep\"&gt;Soul of the Deacons of the Deep&lt;/a&gt; with &lt;a href=\"Ludleth%20of%20Courland\"&gt;Ludleth of Courland&lt;/a&gt;.\nCharacteristics.\nA hybrid weapon, the Cleric's Candlestick combines the attacks of a straight sword with the spell-casting of a &lt;a href=\"Staves%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;staff&lt;/a&gt;.\nBecause of its poor &lt;a href=\"Parameter%20Bonus%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;scaling&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Strength%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Strength&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Dexterity%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Dexterity&lt;/a&gt;, this weapon is not built to inflict &lt;a href=\"Physical%20%28damage%20type%29\"&gt;Physical&lt;/a&gt; damage. Rather, it benefits the most from leveling &lt;a href=\"Intelligence%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Intelligence&lt;/a&gt;, both to increase the &lt;a href=\"Magic%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Magic&lt;/a&gt; damage inflicted by the blade and to increase the &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Buff\"&gt;Spell Buff&lt;/a&gt; so that any cast &lt;a href=\"Sorcery%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Sorceries&lt;/a&gt; will inflict more damage. Like most Sorcery catalysts, it will not gain any Spell Buff or increased melee Magic damage until Intelligence has been leveled to at least 18. However, unlike most weapons that inflict Magic damage scaling with Intelligence, the Cleric's Candlestick continues to benefit from Intelligence past 40, and can get meaningful returns on damage up to 60 Intelligence.\nThe weapon's greatest weakness is that it requires a non-negligible amount of &lt;a href=\"Faith%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Faith&lt;/a&gt; investment in order to meet its wielding requirement; not meeting this requirement will drastically reduce its Spell Buff and render any spells cast by the weapon impotent.\nDescription.\n&lt;tabber&gt;Official translation=\n&lt;/tabber&gt;"}
{"id": "57113", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=57113", "title": "Cleric's Parma", "text": "The Cleric's Parma is a &lt;a href=\"Small%20Shields%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;small shield&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nRare drop from the &lt;a href=\"Dark%20Priestess\"&gt;Dark Priestess&lt;/a&gt; located at the &lt;a href=\"Dragon%20Shrine\"&gt;Dragon Shrine&lt;/a&gt;.\nRare drop from the &lt;a href=\"Peculiar%20Kindalur\"&gt;Peculiar Kindalur&lt;/a&gt;, who invades the player shortly after passing the third &lt;a href=\"Bonfire%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;bonfire&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"Shrine%20of%20Amana\"&gt;Shrine of Amana&lt;/a&gt;.\nFound in the &lt;a href=\"Cathedral%20of%20Blue\"&gt;Cathedral of Blue&lt;/a&gt;, in the iron chest just past the &lt;a href=\"Old%20Dragonslayer\"&gt;Old Dragonslayer&lt;/a&gt;.\nCharacteristics.\nBoasts high &lt;a href=\"elemental%20defense\"&gt;elemental defense&lt;/a&gt;s and little else, as it has an exceptionally low &lt;a href=\"physical%20damage\"&gt;physical damage&lt;/a&gt; reduction and &lt;a href=\"stability\"&gt;stability&lt;/a&gt;, and poor resistances to all &lt;a href=\"Negative%20Status%20Effects%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;status effects&lt;/a&gt;. However, the parma is light&lt;a href=\"weight\"&gt;weight&lt;/a&gt; along with being capable of &lt;a href=\"Spell%20parry\"&gt;deflecting spells&lt;/a&gt; with a well-timed parry.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Cleric%27s%20Small%20Shield\"&gt;Cleric's Small Shield&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0is an overall upgrade to the parma variant, by the cost of only having one more unit of weight and having a slight increase in requirement.\nOverall, the parma's main advantage is its ability to spell-parry while having low stat requirements and weight. As such, it excels when used as a secondary &lt;a href=\"Shields%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;shield&lt;/a&gt; to supplement one's main shield."}
{"id": "46378", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=46378", "title": "Cleric's Sacred Chime", "text": "The Cleric's Sacred Chime\u00a0is a &lt;a href=\"Sacred%20Chimes\"&gt;sacred chime&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nCharacteristics.\nThe Cleric's Sacred Chime has the second fastest &lt;a href=\"Casting%20Speed\"&gt;cast time&lt;/a&gt; out of all the chimes in the game, but has overall average scaling bonuses in &lt;a href=\"Lightning%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;lightning&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Dark%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Dark&lt;/a&gt;. It is noticeably stronger when used to cast &lt;a href=\"Miracle%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;miracles&lt;/a&gt;, prior to being fully-upgraded, as the dark scaling will improve by then, going up to B at +10. \nAltogether, this means that while builds focusing on offensive Miracles or Hexes while most likely only use it early one, a build using non-scaling spells such as &lt;a href=\"Sunlight%20Blade%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Sunlight Blade&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Med%20Heal\"&gt;Med Heal&lt;/a&gt; can take advantage of its low Faith requirement and high casting speed while ignoring its mediocre scaling. \nIt upgrades with &lt;a href=\"Titanite%20Shard%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;standard titanite&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "131134", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=131134", "title": "Cleric's Sacred Chime (Dark Souls III)", "text": "The Cleric's Sacred Chime is a &lt;a href=\"Sacred%20Chimes%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;sacred chime&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nCharacteristics.\nThe Cleric's Sacred Chime is a well-balanced chime that is adequate for casting &lt;a href=\"Miracles%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Miracles&lt;/a&gt; at all points in the game, making it the chime analogue to the &lt;a href=\"Talisman%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Talisman&lt;/a&gt;. It shares a similar &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Buff\"&gt;Spell Buff&lt;/a&gt; range with the &lt;a href=\"Priest%27s%20Chime%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Priest's Chime&lt;/a&gt;, though the Priest's Chime is a superior chime for most values of &lt;a href=\"Faith%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Faith&lt;/a&gt; below 45.\nAt around the 45 to 50 Faith range, the Cleric's Sacred Chime possesses the highest Spell Buff of all Miracle catalysts in the game. It is ultimately superseded by the &lt;a href=\"Saint%27s%20Talisman\"&gt;Saint's Talisman&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Yorshka%27s%20Chime\"&gt;Yorshka's Chime&lt;/a&gt; past 50 Faith, however.\nUpgrades.\nReinforced with regular .\nNotes.\n&lt;br&gt;"}
{"id": "57441", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=57441", "title": "Cleric's Small Shield", "text": "The Cleric's Small Shield\u00a0is a &lt;a href=\"Small%20Shields%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;small shield&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nThe Cleric's Small Shield is found on a corpse, after the &lt;a href=\"Prowling%20Magus%20and%20Congregation\"&gt;Prowling Magus and Congregation&lt;/a&gt;, in the room where &lt;a href=\"Cromwell%20the%20Pardoner\"&gt;Cromwell the Pardoner&lt;/a&gt; is found. The corpse is located in the back of the attic-like room. Both the shield and a &lt;a href=\"Fading%20Soul\"&gt;fading soul&lt;/a&gt; can be pillaged from it.\nCharacteristics.\nThe Cleric's Small Shield boasts exceptional elemental defenses, as well as an appreciable amount of physical defense, for a relatively low weight. This makes it a great choice for players who wish to remain mobile, and have a reliable shield that can fend off both physical and elemental punishment. Reinforcing this will improve its stability, making it a suitable choice, even in later parts of the journey.\nAs with all spell-parrying shields, a faint, white aura will be visible around the player during the parry animation. However, since this is a \"small shield\", the parry window is marginally faster.\nIt's performance is comparable to the &lt;a href=\"Watcher%27s%20Shield\"&gt;Watcher's Shield&lt;/a&gt;, which provides better physical and &lt;a href=\"Dark%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Dark&lt;/a&gt; defence along with more stability, but is marginally heavier and lacks a spell parry. The Watcher's Shield also has slightly worse &lt;a href=\"Magic%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Magic&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Fire%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Fire&lt;/a&gt; defence but better &lt;a href=\"Curse%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Curse&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Petrification\"&gt;Petrification&lt;/a&gt; resistance. However, the Cleric's Small Shield is also found much earlier, and is considerably cheaper to reinforce."}
{"id": "13367", "revid": "5064773", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=13367", "title": "Cleric (Class) Set", "text": ""}
{"id": "173167", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=173167", "title": "Cleric (Dark Souls II)", "text": "The Cleric is one of the &lt;a href=\"Classes%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;classes&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%202\"&gt;Dark Souls 2&lt;/a&gt;\".\nThe Cleric is a &lt;a href=\"Faith%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Faith&lt;/a&gt;-based starting class with decent &lt;a href=\"Vigor\"&gt;Vigor&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Attunement%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Attunement&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Strength%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Strength&lt;/a&gt;, making it a good base for any Faith-focused build, such as a pure &lt;a href=\"Miracle%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Miracle&lt;/a&gt;s and Lightning build, or a more mixed &lt;a href=\"Hexes\"&gt;Hexes&lt;/a&gt; build that wants to start with some extra healing spells. It is also a decent base for a more paladin-style build that wants to use heavy weapons but that also wants some extra healing in the beginning. \nTheir &lt;a href=\"Mace%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Mace&lt;/a&gt; is actually a pretty strong weapon as its Strike damage is highly valuable and as a &lt;a href=\"Hammers%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Hammer&lt;/a&gt; it has an above average Counter Strength of 120, meaning it deals extra damage on &lt;a href=\"Counter%20Attack\"&gt;Counter Attack&lt;/a&gt;s. However, it does have one slight disadvantage in that it has a Strength requirement of 12 while the Cleric only starts with 11 Strength and thus needs 1 more point in the stat to deal the weapon one-handed instead of only two-handed. The &lt;a href=\"Cleric%27s%20Sacred%20Chime\"&gt;Cleric's Sacred Chime&lt;/a&gt; is decent for the offensive, &lt;a href=\"Lightning%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Lightning&lt;/a&gt;-based Miracles but is mediocre for chime-based Hexes due to its lower &lt;a href=\"Dark%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Dark&lt;/a&gt;-scaling. However, it does have good casting speed so it is a good alternative for support Miracles since it can be left unupgraded so that all the character's titanite can be used on their other equipment. \nWhile this class may seem to have below average defences with only decent &lt;a href=\"Poise%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Poise&lt;/a&gt;, since all of those stats come from one piece of equipment, the &lt;a href=\"Archdrake%20Robes\"&gt;Archdrake Robes&lt;/a&gt;, those defences can be improved greatly by adding more armor, even if that is just putting back on some pieces from the &lt;a href=\"Imported%20Set\"&gt;Imported Set&lt;/a&gt; from before the character creation. If up to buying armor pieces, the &lt;a href=\"Falconer%20Set\"&gt;Falconer Set&lt;/a&gt; head, hands, and legs pieces provide a good mix of defences and Poise at a relatively low price of roughly 1,000 souls per piece. Be wary that that this will shorten the character's roll distance unless &lt;a href=\"Vitality%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Vitality&lt;/a&gt; is increased, with all the extra Imported Set pieces (head, hands, and legs) increasing defence by about 45% but giving no extra poise and shortening rolls by 10%, wearing the Falconer Helm and Boots increases defence by 85% and poise by 100% at the cost of 2,100 souls and shortening rolls by 10%, and wearing the Falconer Helm, Gloves, and Boots increases defence by 110% and poise by 130% at the cost of 3,150 souls and shortening rolls by 25%. \nThe &lt;a href=\"Heal%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Heal&lt;/a&gt; Miracle equipped by default is quite strong early on. While it isn't as strong as the &lt;a href=\"Soul%20Arrow%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Soul Arrow&lt;/a&gt; of the &lt;a href=\"Sorcerer%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Sorcerer&lt;/a&gt; it can heavily supplement the very few starting charges of the &lt;a href=\"Estus%20Flask%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Estus Flask&lt;/a&gt;, even more so if a second copy is bought of off &lt;a href=\"Merchant%20Hag%20Melentia\"&gt;Merchant Hag Melentia&lt;/a&gt;. \nDespite its decent Attunement, its low &lt;a href=\"Adaptability\"&gt;Adaptability&lt;/a&gt; means it has the worst roll i-frame category at 5, though this can be improved to 8 i-frames with only 2 points in the former stat or 1 point in the latter stat. \nStarting Equipment.\nAs with all starting classes in Dark Souls 2, the &lt;a href=\"Imported%20Set\"&gt;Imported Set&lt;/a&gt; worn before the character creation can be found unequipped in the character's inventory. "}
{"id": "173160", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=173160", "title": "Cleric (Dark Souls III)", "text": "The Cleric is one of the &lt;a href=\"Classes%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;classes&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%203\"&gt;Dark Souls 3&lt;/a&gt;\".\nIt is a &lt;a href=\"Faith%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Faith&lt;/a&gt;-focused class, with decent &lt;a href=\"Attunement%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Attunement&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Strength%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Strength&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Luck\"&gt;Luck&lt;/a&gt;. This makes them well-suited to a &lt;a href=\"Miracle%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Miracle&lt;/a&gt;-heavy build, and to using the many &lt;a href=\"Lightning%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Lightning&lt;/a&gt;-attuned weapons as they are often also have good Strength-scaling. \nWhile it does indeed have spells, in the form of &lt;a href=\"Heal%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Heal&lt;/a&gt; (which heals) and &lt;a href=\"Force%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Force&lt;/a&gt; (which throws enemies away from you), it does not have any that causes damage, with the earliest ones not being found until &lt;a href=\"Cathedral%20of%20the%20Deep\"&gt;Cathedral of the Deep&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Farron%20Keep\"&gt;Farron Keep&lt;/a&gt;. This means the class will have to focus primarily on weapons initially, and will do well to keep them upgraded as offensive Miracles consume a lot of &lt;a href=\"Focus%20Points\"&gt;Focus Points&lt;/a&gt;. \nThe &lt;a href=\"Cleric%27s%20Sacred%20Chime%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Cleric's Sacred Chime&lt;/a&gt; is a fairly good casting tool and is actually the strongest casting tool for Miracles from 45 to 49 Faith. Its Spell Buff (the stat that affects how strong scaling spells are) doesn't actually increase until at least 19 Faith has been reached. Its &lt;a href=\"Skill\"&gt;Weapon Art&lt;/a&gt; is &lt;a href=\"Gentle%20Prayer\"&gt;Gentle Prayer&lt;/a&gt;, a regenerative effect that always restores 360 hp over the course of a minute as long as the Chime is held in an active hand (so replacing it with another item stops it, as does two-handing the item in the other hand). This effect will actually outheal the Heal Miracle by up to 20% until the Chime's Spell Buff reaches 120, and even afterwards it is a strong if slow alternative due to only having about a third the cost in Focus Points. \nThe &lt;a href=\"Mace%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Mace&lt;/a&gt; is an unexpectedly strong weapon for what may at first seem like a spellcasting class, but in reality it is often a Cleric's main armament. This is because Strike damage is often the strongest physical damage type as armored and skeletal enemies are weak to it (most other types have fewer enemies weak to them), strong Strength-scaling for easy damage increases, a fairly good moveset, and has a good Weapon Art for trading hits with opponents. How the Weapon Art works is that &lt;a href=\"Perseverance%20%28skill%29\"&gt;Perseverance&lt;/a&gt; adds a flat 45% extra absorption and causes the attacks of light weapons to bounce off the user, while also granting great &lt;a href=\"Hyper%20Armor\"&gt;Hyper Armor&lt;/a&gt; to prevent being staggered. \nThe &lt;a href=\"Blue%20Wooden%20Shield%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Blue Wooden Shield&lt;/a&gt; is not very good, having only decent physical and magic defence with serviceable &lt;a href=\"Stability\"&gt;Stability&lt;/a&gt;. While it does have &lt;a href=\"Parry%20%28skill%29\"&gt;Parry&lt;/a&gt; (albeit the inferior Medium Shield version), a strong &lt;a href=\"Weapon%20Skill\"&gt;Weapon Skill&lt;/a&gt; shield like the early &lt;a href=\"Silver%20Eagle%20Kite%20Shield%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Silver Eagle Kite Shield&lt;/a&gt; would probably serve as a better replacement. \nThe &lt;a href=\"Cleric%20Set%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Cleric Set&lt;/a&gt; is a light, caster-type armor set and as such has low physical defences and high elemental defences, while also having high &lt;a href=\"Poison%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Poison&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Curse%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Curse&lt;/a&gt; resistances. \nThe first trainer for more Miracles is found in the &lt;a href=\"Undead%20Settlement\"&gt;Undead Settlement&lt;/a&gt; for further development. "}
