{"id": "5240", "revid": "56333033", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5240", "title": "Club", "text": "The Club is a &lt;a href=\"Hammers%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;hammer&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\".\nCharacteristics.\nThe club is an early weapon with a plain but effective &lt;a href=\"moveset\"&gt;moveset&lt;/a&gt;, and is very effective as a starting weapon. Club has the highest Strength scaling out of the hammers but it suffers from low base damage and &lt;a href=\"Poise%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;Poise&lt;/a&gt; damage making other Hammers out perform it rather quickly when upgraded. Unfortunately, the club doesn't grow so well compared to the &lt;a href=\"Mace\"&gt;Mace&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Reinforced%20Club\"&gt;Reinforced Club&lt;/a&gt;. From \"Club\" to \"Club +15\", the damage will be increased from 87 to 182 (110% damage increase). The Mace and Reinforced Club, on the other hand, get a 150% damage increase. Even at lower Strength, the Club will be out damaged starting upgrade level +7. At 40 Strength: +9. This is because Club has its own unique scaling values that diverge from other Hammers when looking into the &lt;a href=\"https%3A//docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1KukblWL61We64-gNIyaAShga9h8RTXYmyFs98eQhY4E/edit%3Fgid%3D853753739%23gid%3D853753739\"&gt;game parameter files&lt;/a&gt;. \nLike all &lt;a href=\"Hammers%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;Hammers&lt;/a&gt;, if an attack doesn't connect with an enemy, the user will stumble and seem to not be able to handle the weight. If the hit connects, the stumble animation does not come into play and the user moves as normal. This animation means that this Hammer gains &lt;a href=\"Damage%20%28Dark%20Souls%29%23Sweet%2520Spot%2520Damage%2520Bonus\"&gt;Sweet Spot&lt;/a&gt; Damage bonus.\nUpgrades.\nScaling Percentage Values.\nThe following chart lists the scaling percentages when this weapon is fully upgraded. Be advised that:"}
{"id": "47128", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=47128", "title": "Club (Dark Souls II)", "text": "The Club is a &lt;a href=\"Hammers%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;hammer&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nCan be purchased from &lt;a href=\"Merchant%20Hag%20Melentia\"&gt;Merchant Hag Melentia&lt;/a&gt; for 800 &lt;a href=\"Souls%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;souls&lt;/a&gt;.\nUncommon drop from &lt;a href=\"Rogue\"&gt;Rogue&lt;/a&gt; (Club Wielder) in &lt;a href=\"Huntsman%27s%20Copse\"&gt;Huntsman's Copse&lt;/a&gt;.\nCharacteristics.\nThe Club is a solid starting weapon for a strength build. It is lightweight, has low stamina cost and excellent strength scaling from base level, allowing for very respectable damage. The club is reliable throughout the game and will often serve as a go-to weapon for strength builds in situations where speed is essential and heavier weapons become impractical."}
{"id": "131120", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=131120", "title": "Club (Dark Souls III)", "text": "The Club is a &lt;a href=\"Hammers%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;hammer&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nCharacteristics.\nThe Club is a fast and hard-hitting &lt;a href=\"Weapons%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;weapon&lt;/a&gt;. This, combined with its relatively low &lt;a href=\"weight\"&gt;weight&lt;/a&gt; and requirements, makes it a formidable weapon that is easily overlooked.\nThe main weakness of the Club is its heavy attacks, which are slow and heavily telegraphed, especially in comparison to the light attacks. However, these attacks will also hit much harder than the average heavy attack.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Warcry\"&gt;Warcry&lt;/a&gt; skill will further increase the Club's damage output, as well as change the normal heavy attack to a four-hit combo. This attack is harder to hit and is far more punishing, should it miss, but it also deals exceptional damage should all four hits connect.\nLike some other weapons, the Club can be used to trivialize major parts of the game, due to its ability to &lt;a href=\"stunlock\"&gt;stunlock&lt;/a&gt; most regular &lt;a href=\"Enemies%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;enemies&lt;/a&gt; with its one-handed weak attack. For this reason, a &lt;a href=\"Strength%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Strength&lt;/a&gt; build (or any build, with enough patience), can comfortably use the club throughout the entire game (including on &lt;a href=\"NG%2B%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;NG+&lt;/a&gt; and onward).\nIts high damage relative to its weight makes the Club a good candidate for use with &lt;a href=\"Flynn%27s%20Ring%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Flynn's Ring&lt;/a&gt;.\nNotes.\nAlthough &lt;a href=\"Raw%20Gem\"&gt;Raw&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Infusion%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;infusions&lt;/a&gt; are optimal at low Strength, it is always worth infusing the Club with a &lt;a href=\"Heavy%20Gem\"&gt;Heavy Gem&lt;/a&gt; over leaving it uninfused, even at the base requirement of 10 Strength.\nUpgrades.\nReinforced with standard &lt;a href=\"Titanite%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Titanite&lt;/a&gt;."}
