{"id": "131671", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=131671", "title": "Coiled Sword Fragment", "text": "The Coiled Sword Fragment is an in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nPicked up from the extinguished &lt;a href=\"Bonfire%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;bonfire&lt;/a&gt; inside of &lt;a href=\"Firelink%20Shrine%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Firelink Shrine&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"Untended%20Graves\"&gt;Untended Graves&lt;/a&gt;. &lt;a href=\"Champion%20Gundyr\"&gt;Champion Gundyr&lt;/a&gt; must be defeated in order to reach the shrine.\nUsage.\nUsing the Coiled Sword Fragment will present the player with the option of teleporting to either &lt;a href=\"Firelink%20Shrine%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Firelink Shrine&lt;/a&gt; or to the last &lt;a href=\"Bonfire%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;bonfire&lt;/a&gt; they rested at. Unlike &lt;a href=\"Homeward%20Bone%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Homeward Bones&lt;/a&gt;, it has unlimited uses."}
{"id": "172903", "revid": "5064773", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=172903", "title": "Collector's Edition", "text": ""}
{"id": "3757", "revid": "357104", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3757", "title": "Combustion", "text": "Combustion is a &lt;a href=\"Pyromancy%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;Pyromancy&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\".\nGeneral information.\nCombustion is a short-range pyromancy. When cast, players emit a burst of flame from their hand, which has a fire attack power of 1.6 times the Pyromancy Flame's magic adjust. The casting time is fast with little ending lag. Combustion deals relatively high fire damage especially when considering the earliness with which it can be obtained. It is surpassed by its more potent cousin, &lt;a href=\"Great%20Combustion\"&gt;Great Combustion&lt;/a&gt;.\nOverview.\nWith 16 casts per slot, combustion grants players a generous portion of fire damage to their arsenal. In many ways, combustion can be seen as another form of melee attack, except that it cannot be parried and has a larger hitbox than most weapons. In PvE, combustion is an excellent supplement to melee attacks, especially against creatures that block with shields as it will usually still deal a high amount of damage to them through shield. Combustion is also popular because it deals damage without burning stamina, while retaining many of the positive aspects of a melee attack. Keeping this in mind, players can quickly deal a high amount of damage to high-HP targets, especially slow-moving bosses, without having to wait for stamina to recharge.\nIn &lt;a href=\"Player%20versus%20Player\"&gt;PvP&lt;/a&gt;, combustion is not very popular due to the prevalence of &lt;a href=\"Great%20Combustion\"&gt;Great Combustion&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Black%20Flame\"&gt;Black Flame&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "50619", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=50619", "title": "Combustion (Dark Souls II)", "text": "Combustion is a\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Pyromancy%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;pyromancy&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0in\u00a0\"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nGeneral information.\nCasts a small burst of flame in front of the player, causing moderate &lt;a href=\"Fire%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;fire damage&lt;/a&gt;. Has a rather long cast time compared to its \"Dark Souls\" counterpart, but is still relatively fast, if short-ranged.\nAttunement milestones.\nLike all other spells, the amount of casts per slot increases upon reaching certain &lt;a href=\"Attunement%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Attunement&lt;/a&gt; milestones:"}
{"id": "140019", "revid": "33084951", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=140019", "title": "Combustion (skill)", "text": "Combustion is a &lt;a href=\"skill\"&gt;skill&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nDescription.\nQuickly creates an explosion from the catalyst, inflicting 0.8 times the Attack Rating of the catalyst as &lt;a href=\"Fire%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Fire&lt;/a&gt; damage. At point blank range, an additional explosion is pre-cast, inflicting 0.45 times the Attack Rating of the catalyst for additional Fire damage.\nUsage.\nSingle player.\nThis skill acts as the Combustion pyromancies from previous games. It consumes a small amount of &lt;a href=\"Focus%20Points\"&gt;FP&lt;/a&gt;, but does not require an &lt;a href=\"Attunement%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Attunement&lt;/a&gt; slot. This makes it useful for dealing with creatures weak to &lt;a href=\"Fire%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Fire&lt;/a&gt;. This is the weakest form of pyromancy, but also one of the fastest.\nOnline gameplay.\nDue to the fast cast time, this skill can be useful for quickly getting in some point-blank damage on an enemy. In particular, its high stamina damage allows it and &lt;a href=\"Great%20Combustion%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;its stronger cousin&lt;/a&gt; to break open weaker &lt;a href=\"Shields%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;shields&lt;/a&gt; with relative ease, opening other players up for an easy &lt;a href=\"Critical%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;riposte&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "54154", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=54154", "title": "Common Fruit", "text": "A Common Fruit is a \u00a0in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nUse.\nBoosts &lt;a href=\"Poison%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Poison&lt;/a&gt; resist by 200 points for 90 seconds."}
{"id": "131214", "revid": "1087082", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=131214", "title": "Company Captain Yorshka", "text": "Company Captain Yorshka is a &lt;a href=\"Characters%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;character&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\". Found in the &lt;a href=\"Anor%20Londo%20%28Dark_Souls_III%29\"&gt;Anor Londo&lt;/a&gt; section of &lt;a href=\"Irithyll%20of%20the%20Boreal%20Valley\"&gt;Irithyll of the Boreal Valley&lt;/a&gt;, atop the Prison Tower that can be reached via an invisible bridge from the rotating elevator, she is the leader of the &lt;a href=\"Blade%20of%20the%20Darkmoon%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Blade of the Darkmoon&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Covenants%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;covenant&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe meek and unknowing younger half-sister of &lt;a href=\"Dark%20Sun%20Gwyndolin\"&gt;Dark Sun Gwyndolin&lt;/a&gt; (through their mother, likely &lt;a href=\"Crossbreed%20Priscilla\"&gt;Crossbreed Priscilla&lt;/a&gt;), she came to live in Irithyll under his protection, and like him came to be seen as a god by their people. Gwyndolin later passed leadership of the Darkmoon Knights to her after he fell ill, an opportunity &lt;a href=\"Pontiff%20Sulyvahn\"&gt;Sulyvahn&lt;/a&gt; used to seize leadership of Irithyll, imprisoning Yorshka atop the tower where she remained, alone and oblivious to outside events; as such, she was kept unaware of &lt;a href=\"Aldrich%2C%20Devourer%20of%20Gods\"&gt;her brother's demise&lt;/a&gt;, and came to believe herself the leader of a covenant without followers, unaware that &lt;a href=\"Sirris%20of%20the%20Sunless%20Realms\"&gt;some remained&lt;/a&gt;.\nShe is voiced by .\nLocation.\nShe can be met in &lt;a href=\"Anor%20Londo%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Anor Londo&lt;/a&gt;, dwelling alone at the top of the &lt;a href=\"Prison%20Tower\"&gt;Prison Tower&lt;/a&gt; that rises high above the &lt;a href=\"Church%20of%20Yorshka\"&gt;Church of Yorshka&lt;/a&gt;. It can be accessed from the rotating elevator located after the Darkmoon Tomb in Anor Londo. The tower can be reached regardless of the position of the elevator. The tower is visible in the distance and requires a step of faith onto open air to reveal an invisible bridge that leads to it.\nDescription.\nCaptain Yorshka is the leader of the &lt;a href=\"Blade%20of%20the%20Darkmoon%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Darkmoon Blades&lt;/a&gt; and accepts the player into their ranks if they have learned the &lt;a href=\"Gestures%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Darkmoon Loyalty gesture&lt;/a&gt;.\nShe is a tall and slim woman, with pale skin, blue eyes with scale-like markings around them, and dark green hair. She also has two pairs of pointy ears, with the larger pair having long and rigid lobes, as well as two long lobe-like tentacles hanging from her upper neck. She wears a white dress and a veil over her hair. She is barefoot and appears to have a tail not unlike that of a dragon. Yorshka talks in an older form of English, and lives in a tower secluded from the rest of &lt;a href=\"Irithyll%20of%20the%20Boreal%20Valley\"&gt;Irithyll of the Boreal Valley&lt;/a&gt;.\nLore.\nYorshka is the younger sister of &lt;a href=\"Dark%20Sun%20Gwyndolin\"&gt;Dark Sun Gwyndolin&lt;/a&gt;, with whom she shares only her mother, as her brother is &lt;a href=\"Gwyn%2C%20Lord%20of%20Cinder\"&gt;Gwyn&lt;/a&gt;'s last born, but she demonstrates the draconic traits of a crossbreed in a more definite way than her brother, implying that the only mother that could have been shared was &lt;a href=\"Crossbreed%20Priscilla\"&gt;Priscilla&lt;/a&gt;. She claims to have little knowledge of the world, to the point of only knowing crows and dragons as beings capable of flight, implying that she comes from a very isolated place. Furthermore, the girl didn't even had a name.\nAt some point, after Gwyndolin had become the \"king of the gods\", Yorshka reached &lt;a href=\"Irithyll%20of%20the%20Boreal%20Valley\"&gt;Irithyll of the Boreal Valley&lt;/a&gt;, the city her brother had built on the ruins of &lt;a href=\"Anor%20Londo%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Anor Londo&lt;/a&gt; to house the &lt;a href=\"Gods%23Irithyllians%20and%20Descendants%20of%20Gods\"&gt;Irithyllians&lt;/a&gt;, hybrids between the race of the gods of Anor Londo and humans. Here she was welcomed by Gwyndolin who formed a relationship of strong affection with his newfound sister, giving her a &lt;a href=\"Yorshka%27s%20Chime\"&gt;sacred chime&lt;/a&gt; and even her own name that she lacked. Eventually even a &lt;a href=\"Church%20of%20Yorshka\"&gt;church&lt;/a&gt; was built in her name inside Irithyll, exactly where the &lt;a href=\"Painted%20World%20of%20Ariamis\"&gt;Painted World of Ariamis&lt;/a&gt; was once kept, in which she was venerated as a goddess by the &lt;a href=\"Irithyllian%20Slave\"&gt;humans&lt;/a&gt; who worked in the city.\nAfter Gwyndolin was \"stricken by illness\" and forced to retreat to the old cathedral of Anor Londo, her brother entrusted her with command of the covenant of the &lt;a href=\"Blade%20of%20the%20Darkmoon%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Blades of the Darkmoon&lt;/a&gt;. The girl thus continued to lead the company by repeating her brother's ritual phrases by heart, leading the knights against the enemies of the gods and to watch over those who linked the &lt;a href=\"First%20Flame\"&gt;First Flame&lt;/a&gt;, accepting the &lt;a href=\"Proof%20of%20a%20Concord%20Kept\"&gt;proofs&lt;/a&gt; of their accomplished duty and rewarding them with the &lt;a href=\"Blade%20of%20the%20Darkmoon%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;miracles of Gwyndolin&lt;/a&gt;, even without knowledge of their meaning\nHowever, &lt;a href=\"Pontiff%20Sulyvahn\"&gt;Sulyvahn&lt;/a&gt; would take advantage of the situation, declaring himself Pontiff and becoming the tyrant of Irihtyll. He managed to imprison Yorshka on the tower of her own church, isolating her from the whole world and holding her hostage. Over time, because they were integrated into the ranks of Sulyvahn's knights, killed or exiled, the Blades of the Darkmoon would lose all their followers, leaving the girl at the head of the covenant with no knights to guide and only its legacy to preserve. Yorshka would have remained alone on the tower, without hearing a thing from her brother and with only the chime that he had given her to console her from the loneliness. Despite her imprisonment, the humans of Irithyll, now enslaved by Pontiff Sulyvahn and subjected to his experiments, would continue to pray to the goddess in secret, worshipping the &lt;a href=\"Yorshka%27s%20Spear\"&gt;sacred spears&lt;/a&gt; that were enchanted with a soporific spell, trying to find comfort and rest from their condition even at the cost of hitting themselves with these weapons."}
{"id": "45044", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=45044", "title": "Company of Champions", "text": "The\u00a0Company of Champions\u00a0is a\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Covenant%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;covenant&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\". This covenant increases the difficulty of the game and is used to provide players with a bigger challenge.\nRequirements.\nThere are no requirements to join the Company of Champions.\nHow to join.\nThe player can join this &lt;a href=\"Covenant%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;covenant&lt;/a&gt; as soon as they\u00a0arrive to &lt;a href=\"Majula\"&gt;Majula&lt;/a&gt;. Going between the houses of &lt;a href=\"Blacksmith%20Lenigrast\"&gt;Lenigrast&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Sweet%20Shalquoir\"&gt;Shalquoir&lt;/a&gt;, a ledge extending from the cliffside can be found which leads to the Victor's Stone. Upon interacting with the stone, the player must confirm multiple times that they are certain about joining the covenant.\nCons.\nPlayer can't have any online interactions.\nRewards.\n&lt;a href=\"Awestone\"&gt;Awestone&lt;/a&gt;s are offered to the Victor's Stone to gain ranks in the Company of Champions."}
{"id": "5291", "revid": "56333033", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5291", "title": "Composite Bow", "text": "The Composite Bow is a &lt;a href=\"Bows\"&gt;bow&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nIn &lt;a href=\"New%20Londo%20Ruins\"&gt;New Londo Ruins&lt;/a&gt;, the Composite Bow can be found on a corpse, along with 16 &lt;a href=\"Large%20Arrow\"&gt;Large Arrow&lt;/a&gt;s, up the steps from where the water is drained; overlooking the &lt;a href=\"Wyvern\"&gt;Wyvern&lt;/a&gt;s in the &lt;a href=\"Valley%20of%20Drakes\"&gt;Valley of Drakes&lt;/a&gt;.\nCharacteristics.\nThe Composite Bow has very poor &lt;a href=\"range\"&gt;range&lt;/a&gt; (the worst range of all the bows in Dark Souls), making it an inferior choice when attempting to snipe enemies. It makes up for this with high attack power at close range. Due to this, it is often best to use &lt;a href=\"Large%20Arrow\"&gt;Large Arrow&lt;/a&gt;s or &lt;a href=\"Poison%20Arrow\"&gt;Poison Arrow&lt;/a&gt;s to maximize the Composite Bow's short range effectiveness, rather than using other arrows to compensate for the lack of range. Classified as a short bow and maintains the shortbow's faster draw and fire time.\nUpgrades.\nScaling Percentage Values.\nThe following chart lists the scaling percentages when this weapon is fully upgraded. Be advised that:"}
{"id": "47566", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=47566", "title": "Composite Bow (Dark Souls II)", "text": "The Composite Bow is a &lt;a href=\"Bows%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;bow&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nSold by &lt;a href=\"Weaponsmith%20Ornifex\"&gt;Weaponsmith Ornifex&lt;/a&gt; for 5,500 &lt;a href=\"Souls%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;souls&lt;/a&gt;.\nCharacteristics.\nThis bow has low &lt;a href=\"range\"&gt;range&lt;/a&gt;, but this is hard to notice in \"Dark Souls II\". It is usually not a problem. It is a very powerful bow for a &lt;a href=\"Strength%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Strength&lt;/a&gt; build, provided the player has enough &lt;a href=\"Dexterity%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Dexterity&lt;/a&gt; to wield it. However, thanks to its C &lt;a href=\"Parameter%20Bonus%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;scaling&lt;/a&gt; in Strength, and its high base damage, it is one of the more powerful bows for players that invest in Strength."}
{"id": "132929", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=132929", "title": "Composite Bow (Dark Souls III)", "text": "The Composite Bow is a &lt;a href=\"Bows%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;bow&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nSold by the &lt;a href=\"Shrine%20Handmaid\"&gt;Shrine Handmaid&lt;/a&gt; for 3,500 &lt;a href=\"Soul%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;souls&lt;/a&gt; once she has been given the &lt;a href=\"Dreamchaser%27s%20Ashes\"&gt;Dreamchaser's Ashes&lt;/a&gt;.\nCharacteristics.\nThe Composite Bow is a specialized short-ranged bow that is adept at firing at targets within lock-on range.\nBecause it has less shot range than bows like the &lt;a href=\"Longbow%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Longbow&lt;/a&gt;, it performs poorly as a sniper weapon. However, its low wielding requirements ensures that most &lt;a href=\"Classes%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;classes&lt;/a&gt; can easily wield it with only a minor investment in &lt;a href=\"Dexterity%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Dexterity&lt;/a&gt; (or &lt;a href=\"Strength%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Strength&lt;/a&gt;, in the case of the Sorcerer class).\nCompared to the &lt;a href=\"Short%20Bow%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Short Bow&lt;/a&gt;, the Composite Bow weighs almost twice as much, has lower base damage and is available later in the game. However, it makes up for this with its superior Strength &lt;a href=\"Parameter%20Bonus%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;scaling&lt;/a&gt;, ensuring that it out-damages the Short Bow with a few upgrades and stat investments.\nBeing a short bow, the Composite Bow is adept at engaging targets at close range, possessing a &lt;a href=\"skill\"&gt;skill&lt;/a&gt; that puts multiple arrows quickly on target. As well, unlike long bows it is capable of performing rolling and running attacks, allowing it to retaliate against melee attacks or to chase down fleeing foes.\nUpgrades.\n&lt;br&gt;"}
