{"id": "130435", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=130435", "title": "Cornyx of the Great Swamp", "text": "Cornyx of the Great Swamp is a &lt;a href=\"Characters%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;character&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Merchant%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;merchant&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\". He sells &lt;a href=\"Pyromancy%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;pyromancies&lt;/a&gt; and reinforces the player's &lt;a href=\"Pyromancy%20Flames%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Pyromancy Flames&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Firelink%20Shrine%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Firelink Shrine&lt;/a&gt; after he has been freed from his cage in the &lt;a href=\"Undead%20Settlement\"&gt;Undead Settlement&lt;/a&gt;.\nHe is voiced by .\nLocation.\nCornyx is first found locked inside of a small cage in the &lt;a href=\"Undead%20Settlement\"&gt;Undead Settlement&lt;/a&gt;, in a scaffolding of the small fortress found near the guillotine and where three &lt;a href=\"Peasant%20Hollow\"&gt;hollows&lt;/a&gt; throw &lt;a href=\"Firebomb%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;firebombs&lt;/a&gt; from above.\nTo reach him, drop from the right side of the bridge nearby and onto a ledge below. Follow the only path available (lighting the &lt;a href=\"Cliff%20Underside\"&gt;Cliff Underside&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Bonfire%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;bonfire&lt;/a&gt; along the way), which leads to a piece of roof and the scaffolding of the structure, and eventually to Cornyx's cage. When asked, agree to become his pupil in the arts of &lt;a href=\"Pyromancy%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;pyromancy&lt;/a&gt;.\nOnce he relocates to &lt;a href=\"Firelink%20Shrine%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Firelink Shrine&lt;/a&gt;, he can be found in the basement, near to the base of the staircase on the east wing, and reside there for the rest of the game."}
{"id": "132593", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=132593", "title": "Corpse Grub", "text": "Corpse Grubs are in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;3\".\nDescription.\nThe evolved form of the parasites residing in &lt;a href=\"Infested%20Corpse\"&gt;Infested Corpse&lt;/a&gt;s, these vile creatures are comprised entirely of maggots. Most of them appear in a waterway in the &lt;a href=\"Cathedral%20of%20the%20Deep\"&gt;cathedral&lt;/a&gt;'s grounds and one is found in a cell in the &lt;a href=\"Irithyll%20Dungeon\"&gt;Irithyll Dungeon&lt;/a&gt; which drops the &lt;a href=\"Great%20Magic%20Shield\"&gt;Great Magic Shield&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Sorcery%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;sorcery&lt;/a&gt;.\nLocations.\n&lt;a href=\"Cathedral%20of%20the%20Deep\"&gt;Cathedral of the Deep&lt;/a&gt;\n&lt;a href=\"Irithyll%20Dungeon\"&gt;Irithyll Dungeon&lt;/a&gt;\nStrategy.\nLike the other maggots enemies, Corpse Grubs inflict the &lt;a href=\"Bleed%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;maggot&lt;/a&gt; status with their attacks, which can be removed with a &lt;a href=\"Torch%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;torch&lt;/a&gt;, or cured with a &lt;a href=\"Bloodred%20Moss%20Clump%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Bloodred Moss Clump&lt;/a&gt;. Although stronger and more aggressive than their infected hosts, they share the same weakness to &lt;a href=\"Fire%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;fire&lt;/a&gt; damage and will writhe in agony if set alight.\nDrops.\n&lt;tabber&gt;Cathedral of the Deep =\n&lt;/tabber&gt;"}
{"id": "93972", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=93972", "title": "Corpse Rat", "text": "Corpse Rats are\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Enemies%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;enemies&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nDescription.\nGiant rodents who loyally serve the &lt;a href=\"Rat%20King%20%28character%29\"&gt;Rat King&lt;/a&gt; and defend their burrows from intruders. They are covered in filth and scabs, and will bite and lunge at the player, causing &lt;a href=\"Petrification\"&gt;Petrification&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"build-up\"&gt;build-up&lt;/a&gt;.\nEncountered only in the &lt;a href=\"Grave%20of%20Saints\"&gt;Grave of Saints&lt;/a&gt;, which they have infested and now call home. Corpse Rats will appear from tombs and holes in the ceiling, usually in groups to attack the player. They are the initial hazard of the &lt;a href=\"Royal%20Rat%20Vanguard\"&gt;Royal Rat Vanguard&lt;/a&gt; boss fight.\nStrategy.\nOne can avoid all of the rats with relative ease simply by rushing to the &lt;a href=\"Grave%20Entrance\"&gt;Grave Entrance&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Bonfire%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;bonfire&lt;/a&gt; located on the second floor. When the player is forced to engage them, they will want to avoid being attacked too much at one time, especially since taking hits from multiple rats will lead to Petrification and an instant &lt;a href=\"death\"&gt;death&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "67381", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=67381", "title": "Corrosive Ant Queen", "text": "The Corrosive Ant Queen is an in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nDescription.\nA gigantic ant found in a cave in &lt;a href=\"The%20Gutter\"&gt;The Gutter&lt;/a&gt;. She will spray a constant mist of corrosive acid which will degrade the &lt;a href=\"durability\"&gt;durability&lt;/a&gt; of equipment over time. This mist will also cure &lt;a href=\"Poison%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;poison&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe Queen is a stationary enemy and will not directly attack the player, apart from damaging their equipment, so it is advisable to use ranged weapons if the player does not wish to risk getting too close. She can also be assaulted from the back or front and does not react. She does not respawn."}
{"id": "172223", "revid": "5064773", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=172223", "title": "Corrosive Bug", "text": ""}
{"id": "116077", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=116077", "title": "Corrosive Egg Insect", "text": "Corrosive Egg Insects are in .\u00a0\nDescription.\nCorrosive Egg Insects\u00a0are commonly found in &lt;a href=\"Shulva%2C%20Sanctum%20City\"&gt;Shulva&lt;/a&gt; and the &lt;a href=\"Dragon%27s%20Sanctum\"&gt;Dragon's Sanctum&lt;/a&gt;. They are capable of creating corrosive acid clouds, hence these enemies are dangerous foes if the player's &lt;a href=\"equipment\"&gt;equipment&lt;/a&gt; is in near-broken state. They can be encountered either in their original state as an egg, or in their hatched state as an insect, which are also capable of flying.\nThey are usually perched on the ceiling of a room in numbers of three or four, out of plain sight, and drop altogether to ambush the player if he or she walks to a certain point in the room or if one is attacked.\nThe rooms where they lurk are generally stuffed with mounds of eggs which release a splash of corrosive acid when destroyed. They can also be found frequently in tight corridors. One must be wary as their physical attacks can deal considerable damage and evading them can be difficult due to the hindrances previously mentioned. Perhaps their most dangerous attack is when they release a corrosive acid cloud around them and start chasing the player relentlessly. This attack lasts for a very lengthy amount of time."}
{"id": "68147", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=68147", "title": "Corrosive Urn", "text": "Corrosive Urns are in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nGeneral information.\nA fast-moving thrown object that is similar to a &lt;a href=\"Firebomb%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;firebomb&lt;/a&gt;, except instead of dealing damage to the enemy's health, it damages their equipment with corrosive acid.\nAlthough most enemies are unaffected by its effect, Acid damage can prove invaluable in &lt;a href=\"Player%20versus%20Player%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;PvP&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "137607", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=137607", "title": "Corvian", "text": "Corvians are in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nDescription.\nHunchbacked, foul medium-sized creatures, hybrids between a &lt;a href=\"hollow\"&gt;hollow&lt;/a&gt; and a crow, and armed with either a &lt;a href=\"Corvian%20Greatknife\"&gt;dagger&lt;/a&gt; or a &lt;a href=\"Great%20Corvian%20Scythe\"&gt;scythe&lt;/a&gt;. Corvians initially stand on their posts and barely attack or move from place until approached. When this happens, however, they will begin a brief transformation in which two pairs of wings extrude from their backs, one at a time. When they finish, they will become extremely aggressive, being able to chase the player for long distances. They will also gain the ability to fly in short bursts and attack with a rapid barrage of claw-swipes with their legs.\nIn some cases, a group of corvians can be found congregated around a &lt;a href=\"Corvian%20Storyteller\"&gt;Corvian Storyteller&lt;/a&gt;. If the storyteller spots the player, it will unleash a shivering shriek that will alert the rest of the flock, making all corvians in the vicinity begin their transformations and then rush toward the player in unison.\nStrategy.\nCorvians are almost completely vulnerable before starting their transformation. However, if they have already started it and are attacked, the transformation will complete immediately, rendering them able to retaliate. They stagger easily, though, and fast weapons like &lt;a href=\"Straight%20Swords%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;straight swords&lt;/a&gt; should leave them with no opportunity to counterattack. If a heavy weapon is used, the player should make sure that the corvian will die in one or two hits.\nIt is not advisable to engage more than one of these creatures at a time due to the constant damage output they can deal and their quick recovery times. If they are found congregated in front of a &lt;a href=\"Corvian%20Storyteller\"&gt;storyteller&lt;/a&gt;, either the latter should be dealt first or each corvian should be drawn in individually with ranged attacks. In some cases, if the storyteller dies, all remaining corvians will become completely oblivious to the player, making for easy kills."}
{"id": "130240", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=130240", "title": "Corvian Greatknife", "text": "The Corvian Greatknife is a &lt;a href=\"Daggers%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;dagger&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nDropped by &lt;a href=\"Corvian\"&gt;Corvian&lt;/a&gt;s in the &lt;a href=\"Road%20of%20Sacrifices\"&gt;Road of Sacrifices&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Farron%20Keep\"&gt;Farron Keep&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Painted%20World%20of%20Ariandel\"&gt;Painted World of Ariandel&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Untended%20Graves\"&gt;Untended Graves&lt;/a&gt;.\nCharacteristics.\nAlthough it has unimpressive stat scaling, the Corvian Greatknife excels at countering defensive opponents. Unlike other daggers, this one has a unique weapon skill that allows it to completely bypass an opponent's shield (be it any shield), and inflict a sizable amount of damage as a result, similar to a shield-splitter skill, but with much more potency. This weapon art cannot be parried.\nBeing a dagger, critical attacks inflict considerably more damage than standard weapons. It is, however, quite heavy for a dagger, at 2.5 units.\nUpgrades.\nUpgrades with standard ."}
{"id": "143006", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=143006", "title": "Corvian Knight", "text": "Corvian Knights are in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;: &lt;a href=\"Ashes%20of%20Ariandel\"&gt;Ashes of Ariandel&lt;/a&gt;\".\nDescription.\nCorvian Knights are tall avian warriors that tower over their lesser brethren and are considerably more intelligent and fearsome. They exist in two variations, one that wears a hooded robe and wields the &lt;a href=\"Crow%20Quills\"&gt;Crow Quills&lt;/a&gt;, and a naked variant that wields the &lt;a href=\"Crow%20Talons\"&gt;Crow Talons&lt;/a&gt;.\nThey can be encountered throughout the &lt;a href=\"Painted%20World%20of%20Ariandel%23Bonfires\"&gt;Corvian Settlement&lt;/a&gt; exterminating other &lt;a href=\"Forlorn%20Corvian%20Settler\"&gt;Forlorn Corvians&lt;/a&gt;, although they will quickly turn their attention to the player.\nLocations.\nFound throughout the Corvian Settlement in the &lt;a href=\"Painted%20World%20of%20Ariandel\"&gt;Painted World of Ariandel&lt;/a&gt;.\nLore.\nCorvian Knights presumably protected the Corvian Settlement and its inhabitants within the Painted World of Ariandel. Whenever a Painting begins to rot, those who settled within it resolve to burn it away in order to give way for the creation of a new one. When the Corvians were faced with this event, they were prepared to burn it. However, after &lt;a href=\"Sister%20Friede\"&gt;Sister Friede&lt;/a&gt; arrived in the Painting, the Corvian Knights became infatuated with her, choosing to loyally serve her and assist in her mission to let the world rot instead. To that end, the Corvian Knights betrayed their brethren, and their loyalty to Friede was so devout that they willingly slaughtered their own kin if they were perceived to be a threat.\nStrategy.\nCorvian Knights are incredibly agile opponents and will regularly backflip away or leap over the player to disorient them, often following up with a lunging stab. This can be punished by dodging and backstabbing. Their flurry of blade attacks can rapidly inflict bleed, even when guarding through a shield, so it's not recommended to attempt to block their strikes. From a distance, they will throw several knives and will often perform this attack if the player attempts to heal or use an item.\nThe robed Corvian Knights will pursue and eliminate the lesser Corvians around the &lt;a href=\"Painted%20World%20of%20Ariandel%23Bonfires\"&gt;settlement&lt;/a&gt;, although they will focus on the player if alerted. The variant wielding &lt;a href=\"Crow%20Talons\"&gt;talons&lt;/a&gt; is often encountered hiding upside down under bridges and ceilings, so it is advisable for the player to be mindful of their surroundings."}
