{"id": "132878", "revid": "1188343", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=132878", "title": "Corvian Storyteller", "text": "Corvian Storytellers are &lt;a href=\"Enemies%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;enemies&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nDescription.\nTall avian humanoids that act as shamans for the lesser &lt;a href=\"Corvian\"&gt;Corvian&lt;/a&gt;s. Storytellers use their &lt;a href=\"Storyteller%27s%20Staff\"&gt;staff's&lt;/a&gt; weapon art and a slow, short ranged wave of fire in combat and are capable of riling up their pack members to make them more aggressive. They are always accompanied by several Corvians.\nStrategy.\nAlthough physically imposing, Storytellers have little vitality and offer little in the way of physical offense. From a distance, they will use their staff's weapon art to prevent the player from reaching them, but there is a long delay before they can cast the spell and they are easily staggered out of it. They may also cast a wave of fire from the tip of their staff, in a semi-circular motion.\nStorytellers will alert any nearby Corvians once they spot the player, which will cause them to begin transforming into their berserk state. It is recommended to eliminate this enemy swiftly before it can draw attention."}
