{"id": "130523", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=130523", "title": "Courland", "text": "Courland is a in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nDescription.\nCourland was a land known for its \"transposition arts\", the process of extracting and coalescing the essence of a soul and in doing so transfer its true power to the user. This art was able to grant powers once thought unattainable but that at one point also left a foul stain upon Courland's honor.\nCourland's craftsmen also managed to create artifacts that exploited this art, stitching together the &lt;a href=\"Titanite%20Scale\"&gt;Titanite Scale&lt;/a&gt;s of the &lt;a href=\"Ravenous%20Crystal%20Lizard\"&gt;Ravenous Crystal Lizard&lt;/a&gt;s. These creatures were in fact Crystal Lizards who, devouring souls, in rare cases grew to monstrous proportion and consequently their scales were connected to their natural ability to manipulate souls. The result were &lt;a href=\"Transposing%20Kiln\"&gt;Transposing Kiln&lt;/a&gt;s capable of transposing souls to craft powerful items with their concentrated essence. However the inappropriate use of them was deemed forbidden.\nAt some point a \"&lt;a href=\"Primordial%20Serpents\"&gt;Soulfeeder&lt;/a&gt;\". arrived in Courland, a beast that insatiably absorbed souls to feed its own power. The creature was finally defeated but, even if its accursed corpse was burned, the pungent stench of souls left the air permanently stained. However, using their transposition arts, the craftsmen of Courland managed to create a &lt;a href=\"Skull%20Ring\"&gt;Skull Ring&lt;/a&gt; from the soul of the creature, an artifact that makes the wearer easier to be detected by enemies.\nAt a certain point the &lt;a href=\"First%20Flame\"&gt;First Flame&lt;/a&gt; began to fade again and the first &lt;a href=\"Fire%20Keeper\"&gt;Fire Keeper&lt;/a&gt; of &lt;a href=\"Lothric\"&gt;Lothric&lt;/a&gt; had a vision of the end of the &lt;a href=\"Age%20of%20Fire\"&gt;Age of Fire&lt;/a&gt; and the beginning of an &lt;a href=\"Age%20of%20Dark\"&gt;Age of Dark&lt;/a&gt;, a barren plane of endless darkness. For this reason, &lt;a href=\"Ludleth%20of%20Courland\"&gt;Ludleth of Courland&lt;/a&gt;, a student of the art of transposition, was called to become a &lt;a href=\"Lords%20of%20Cinder\"&gt;Lord of Cinder&lt;/a&gt;, to link the First Flame again and repel the vision of the Fire Keeper. Despite his apparent lack of strength and his small appearance, Ludleth managed to gain the strength necessary to become a Champion, something for which he himself expresses remorse, asking to be forgiven. Despite his role, Ludleth was then literally exiled from his country and collaborated with Lothric, ensuring that the first Fire Keeper was deprived of her &lt;a href=\"Eyes%20of%20a%20Fire%20Keeper\"&gt;eyes&lt;/a&gt; and that all future maidens like her were deprived of their sight to prevent them from observing the future thanks to the power of their darkness. The original eyes were hidden in a &lt;a href=\"Untended%20Graves\"&gt;version&lt;/a&gt; of the &lt;a href=\"Firelink%20Shrine%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Firelink Shrine&lt;/a&gt; on the verge of sinking into darkness and where the First Flame was an instant away from being extinguished.\nAt some point after Ludleth linked the First Flame, the country of Courland collapsed and the art of transposition and most of its kiln were lost together with the knowledge connected with them, never to be mentioned again in the history of other regions. One of their rare kilns at one point ended up in the &lt;a href=\"Undead%20Settlement\"&gt;Undead Settlement&lt;/a&gt; at the foot of &lt;a href=\"Lothric\"&gt;Lothric&lt;/a&gt; where it was absorbed by the &lt;a href=\"Curse-rotted%20Greatwood\"&gt;Curse-rotted Greatwood&lt;/a&gt;, a once-blessed tree used by the inhabitants to seal away the curses that seeped into their village."}
{"id": "134008", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=134008", "title": "Court Sorcerer", "text": "The Court Sorcerer is an &lt;a href=\"Enemies%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;enemy&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Characters%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;character&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nDescription.\nAn aggressive spellcaster wearing the &lt;a href=\"Court%20Sorcerer%20Set\"&gt;Court Sorcerer Set&lt;/a&gt; and wielding both a &lt;a href=\"Gargoyle%20Flame%20Hammer\"&gt;great hammer&lt;/a&gt; and a &lt;a href=\"Court%20Sorcerer%27s%20Staff\"&gt;staff&lt;/a&gt;. He constantly switches between casting powerful &lt;a href=\"Sorcery%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;sorceries&lt;/a&gt; and melee combat throughout the fight.\nLocation.\nFound in the &lt;a href=\"Profaned%20Capital\"&gt;Profaned Capital&lt;/a&gt;. Awaits on the roof of the ruined chapel in the &lt;a href=\"Toxic%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;toxic&lt;/a&gt; swamp.\nStrategy.\nThe Court Sorcerer is a very aggressive opponent. He awaits on the roof of the ruined chapel in the &lt;a href=\"Profaned%20Capital\"&gt;Profaned Capital&lt;/a&gt;. Due to the area's layout, he will most likely approach from the rear while the player is making their way upstairs; this usually gives him the opportunity to start the battle by casting one of his &lt;a href=\"Sorcery%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;sorceries&lt;/a&gt;. His repertoire includes variations of &lt;a href=\"Soul%20Spear%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Soul Spear&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Soul%20Greatsword%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Soul Greatsword&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Homing%20Soulmass%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Homing Soulmass&lt;/a&gt;.\nHe also comes armed with a &lt;a href=\"Gargoyle%20Flame%20Hammer\"&gt;Gargoyle Flame Hammer&lt;/a&gt; and will quickly switch between casting spells and this weapon, frequently holding it with both hands for increased damage. His melee attacks are very similar to that of &lt;a href=\"Havel%20the%20Rock%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Havel&lt;/a&gt;'s, and thus he is often vulnerable after finishing a combo. Care must be taken, though, as he can quickly inflict a considerable amount of damage in return; more so if the player is taken off-balance due to the different tactics used for dealing with a sorcerer and a warrior.\nFortunately, he is not very resilient and is &lt;a href=\"stagger\"&gt;stagger&lt;/a&gt;ed easily, which allows the player to deal many consecutive hits."}
{"id": "134107", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=134107", "title": "Court Sorcerer's Staff", "text": "The Court Sorcerer's Staff is a &lt;a href=\"Staves%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;staff&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nDropped by a &lt;a href=\"Mimic%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Mimic&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"Profaned%20Capital\"&gt;Profaned Capital&lt;/a&gt;, inside the second floor of the building within the &lt;a href=\"Toxic%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Toxic&lt;/a&gt; swamp. It is guarded by a &lt;a href=\"Monstrosity%20of%20Sin\"&gt;Monstrosity of Sin&lt;/a&gt;.\nCharacteristics.\nThe Court Sorcerer's Staff is renowned as the most powerful &lt;a href=\"Sorcery%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Sorcery&lt;/a&gt; catalyst for builds with high &lt;a href=\"Intelligence%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Intelligence&lt;/a&gt;. This makes it the de-facto go-to catalyst for dedicated Sorcerer builds.\nBelow 25 Intelligence, the Court Sorcerer's Staff possesses rather poor &lt;a href=\"Parameter%20Bonus%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;scaling&lt;/a&gt;, and its &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Buff\"&gt;Spell Buff&lt;/a&gt; is very unremarkable. However, once it exceeds this threshold its scaling will improve drastically, and it will steadily get stronger all the way up to 60 Intelligence. Unlike other staves, it will not slow down after 45 Intelligence, which is what allows it to surpass the competition.\nIn terms of raw Spell Buff, the Court Sorcerer's Staff will become the strongest staff at 50 Intelligence and beyond, claiming the top spot from the &lt;a href=\"Sorcerer%27s%20Staff%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Sorcerer's Staff&lt;/a&gt;. However, care should be taken when using its &lt;a href=\"Steady%20Chant\"&gt;Steady Chant&lt;/a&gt; skill, which costs more than twice as much as that of any other staff except the &lt;a href=\"Sage%27s%20Crystal%20Staff\"&gt;Sage's Crystal Staff&lt;/a&gt;.\nUpgrades.\nReinforced with regular ."}
