{"id": "3218", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3218", "title": "Cracked Round Shield", "text": "The Cracked Round Shield is a &lt;a href=\"Small%20Shields\"&gt;small shield&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nThe Cracked Round Shield is given to the &lt;a href=\"Pyromancer\"&gt;Pyromancer&lt;/a&gt; class at the beginning of the game. It can also be dropped by &lt;a href=\"Hollow%20Warrior\"&gt;Hollow Warrior&lt;/a&gt;s.\nCharacteristics.\nThe Cracked Round Shield is the worst (in terms of stats) of all of the shields in the game, and should be replaced at the soonest possible opportunity. For a Pyromancer, more viable substitutes found early in the game include the &lt;a href=\"Wooden%20Shield\"&gt;Wooden Shield&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Caduceus%20Round%20Shield\"&gt;Caduceus Round Shield&lt;/a&gt;.\nIt has no deflection at all and a long &lt;a href=\"parry\"&gt;parry&lt;/a&gt; window. When &lt;a href=\"Weapon%20Modification\"&gt;upgraded&lt;/a&gt; to &lt;a href=\"Crystal%20%28Upgrade%20Path%29\"&gt;crystal&lt;/a&gt; the &lt;a href=\"durability\"&gt;durability&lt;/a&gt; is 6--low, even for crystal items. It offers the highest resistance to Curse build-up of all the small shields. However, this does not outweigh the cons in practical situations.\nResistance Defense.\nAlong with Physical and Elemental damage reduction, weapons also have hidden stats that reduce the amount of status build-up while blocking."}
