{"id": "8245", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=8245", "title": "Crest Key", "text": "The Crest Key is a in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\". It is only available in the \"&lt;a href=\"Artorias%20of%20the%20Abyss\"&gt;Artorias of the Abyss&lt;/a&gt;\" DLC.\nAvailability.\nDropped by the 2nd &lt;a href=\"Mimic\"&gt;Mimic&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Oolacile%20Township\"&gt;Oolacile Township&lt;/a&gt;, located inside the building full of &lt;a href=\"Bloathead\"&gt;frenzied Bloatheads&lt;/a&gt;. While descending the stairs, a fireplace on the upper floor can be seen. If we ignore the present enemies, hugging the wall to your right you'll find a doorway, ascend the set of stairs to the previously mentioned upper floor, and follow the available path within the structure. You'll reach a sticking-out platform that seems like a vicious circle if you drop off it, on your right is not a dead end (but rather a light-illusory wall), on your left the fireplace is now below you level by a few centimeters, roll or run-jump to access it, deal with the &lt;a href=\"Mimic\"&gt;Mimic&lt;/a&gt; and any &lt;a href=\"Bloathead\"&gt;frenzied Bloatheads&lt;/a&gt; there.\nGeneral Information.\nOpens the door that leads to &lt;a href=\"Hawkeye%20Gough\"&gt;Hawkeye Gough&lt;/a&gt;. The door is located above the arena where the battle with &lt;a href=\"Artorias%20the%20Abysswalker\"&gt;Artorias&lt;/a&gt; takes place."}
{"id": "5168", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5168", "title": "Crest Shield", "text": "The Crest Shield is a &lt;a href=\"Medium%20Shields\"&gt;medium shield&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nThe Crest Shield is dropped by &lt;a href=\"Oscar%2C%20Knight%20of%20Astora\"&gt;Oscar, Knight of Astora&lt;/a&gt; upon revisiting &lt;a href=\"Undead%20Asylum\"&gt;Undead Asylum&lt;/a&gt;. He spawns where the player first left him at the beginning of the game.\nCharacteristics.\nWhat sets the Crest Shield apart from other medium shields is its massive 80% &lt;a href=\"Magic%20%28damage%20type%29\"&gt;magic&lt;/a&gt; reduction. This makes the Crest Shield a powerful asset when facing magic-dealing enemies. When used in conjunction with miracles such as &lt;a href=\"Great%20Magic%20Barrier\"&gt;Great Magic Barrier&lt;/a&gt;, the player can become virtually immune to magic damage.\nThe Crest Shield has medium deflection and a normal &lt;a href=\"Parry%20and%20Riposte\"&gt;parry&lt;/a&gt; speed.\nResistance Defense.\nAlong with Physical and Elemental damage reduction, weapons also have hidden stats that reduce the amount of status build-up while blocking.\nUpgrades.\nRequires: Crest Shield +0, 2000 Souls and &lt;a href=\"Twinkling%20Titanite\"&gt;Twinkling Titanite&lt;/a&gt;"}
{"id": "134849", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=134849", "title": "Crest Shield (Dark Souls III)", "text": "The Crest Shield is a &lt;a href=\"Medium%20Shields%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;medium shield&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nFound in the &lt;a href=\"Cathedral%20of%20the%20Deep\"&gt;Cathedral of the Deep&lt;/a&gt;. From the first &lt;a href=\"Bonfire%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;bonfire&lt;/a&gt;, head towards the stairs but look for a path on the right. Follow it as it leads up the hillside, and the shield will be on a corpse at the top.\nCharacteristics.\nOne of two returning crest shields from \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\" and one of the four enchanted blue shields in \"Dark Souls III\", the Crest Shield specializes in blocking &lt;a href=\"Dark%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Dark&lt;/a&gt; damage.\nBesides its respectable elemental absorptions across the board, it possesses the highest Dark absorption out of all shields in the game, short of &lt;a href=\"Deep%20Gem\"&gt;Deep&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Infusion%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;infusions&lt;/a&gt; on certain shields. As a medium shield, it has a low &lt;a href=\"Strength%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Strength&lt;/a&gt; requirement and possesses moderate weight and stability, as well as blocking 100% of physical damage, making it a good general-purpose shield."}
{"id": "4859", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4859", "title": "Crest of Artorias", "text": "The Crest of Artorias is a in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\".\nGeneral information.\nIt is used to open the magical door in &lt;a href=\"Darkroot%20Garden\"&gt;Darkroot Garden&lt;/a&gt; that leads to the &lt;a href=\"Forest%20Hunter\"&gt;Forest Hunter&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Covenant\"&gt;Covenant&lt;/a&gt; and the &lt;a href=\"Great%20Grey%20Wolf%20Sif\"&gt;Great Grey Wolf Sif&lt;/a&gt;. Though an impression for the crest resides on both sides of the door, unlocking of the door can only be accomplished from the Darkroot Garden side and not the Forest Hunter Covenant side."}
{"id": "31238", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=31238", "title": "Crest of Blood", "text": "The Crest of Blood is a &lt;a href=\"Rings%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;ring&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nGiven to the player by &lt;a href=\"Titchy%20Gren\"&gt;Titchy Gren&lt;/a&gt; after joining the &lt;a href=\"Brotherhood%20of%20Blood\"&gt;Brotherhood of Blood&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Covenant%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;covenant&lt;/a&gt;.\nEffect.\nThe Crest of Blood boosts a weapon's &lt;a href=\"Bleed%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Bleed&lt;/a&gt; attack by 50 points. However, this only affects weapons that deal Bleed build-up, and the ring is thus useless unless the weapon has either innate Bleed build-up, or if it's been infused with a &lt;a href=\"Bleed%20Stone\"&gt;Bleed Stone&lt;/a&gt;.\nTrivia.\nThe mark on the Crest of Blood has some resemblance to the &lt;a href=\"http%3A//berserk.wikia.com/wiki/Brand_of_Sacrifice\"&gt;Brand of Sacrifice&lt;/a&gt; from Beserk. The general shape is somewhat similar, as is their connection to bleeding."}
{"id": "48993", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=48993", "title": "Crest of the Rat", "text": "The Crest of the Rat is a\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Rings%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;ring&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nGiven to the player by the &lt;a href=\"Rat%20King%20%28character%29\"&gt;Rat King&lt;/a&gt; after joining the &lt;a href=\"Rat%20King%20%28covenant%29\"&gt;Rat King&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Covenant%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;covenant&lt;/a&gt;.\nEffect.\nWearing this ring in the &lt;a href=\"Grave%20of%20Saints\"&gt;Grave of Saints&lt;/a&gt; or the &lt;a href=\"Doors%20of%20Pharros\"&gt;Doors of Pharros&lt;/a&gt; will summon other players into the host's world. The player can be &lt;a href=\"hollow\"&gt;hollow&lt;/a&gt; or human for the summoning to work. Once other players are in the host's world when summoned this way, the Crest of the Rat cannot be taken off until they depart.\nIt can also grant a flat bonus to the &lt;a href=\"Poison%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Poison&lt;/a&gt; buildup stat on poison weapons when worn. The bonus granted from these items can vary depending on what type of poison weapon is equipped, be it &lt;a href=\"Poison%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29%23Poison%20Weapons\"&gt;innate&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Poison%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29%23Infusion\"&gt;infused&lt;/a&gt; or both:"}
{"id": "3886", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3886", "title": "Crestfallen Merchant", "text": "The Crestfallen Merchant is a &lt;a href=\"character\"&gt;character&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\". A pessimistic &lt;a href=\"merchant\"&gt;merchant&lt;/a&gt;, he peddles goods at &lt;a href=\"Sen%27s%20Fortress\"&gt;Sen's Fortress&lt;/a&gt;. He is voiced by , who also voices &lt;a href=\"Laurentius%20of%20the%20Great%20Swamp\"&gt;Laurentius of the Great Swamp&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Felkin%20the%20Outcast\"&gt;Felkin the Outcast&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nLore.\nAs a pessimistic and guilt ridden merchant, he will often encourage and praise the players efforts while condemning them as futile. His erratic implications can be taken as signs that he's well into becoming &lt;a href=\"Hollow\"&gt;Hollow&lt;/a&gt;ed himself. \nStrategy.\nThe Crestfallen Merchant is slow and wields a cumbersome weapon. These traits make it fairly easy to strafe and hit him with fast attacks before getting out of the way, as well as making him a good target for ripostes."}
{"id": "173391", "revid": "5064773", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=173391", "title": "Crestfallen Saulden", "text": ""}
{"id": "2967", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=2967", "title": "Crestfallen Warrior", "text": "The Crestfallen Warrior is a in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\". Having lost his will or courage to face more , he sits in the &lt;a href=\"Firelink%20Shrine\"&gt;Firelink Shrine&lt;/a&gt;, brooding and awaiting his &lt;a href=\"Hollow\"&gt;Hollow&lt;/a&gt;ing.\nHe is voiced by , who also voiced &lt;a href=\"Domhnall%20of%20Zena\"&gt;Domhnall of Zena&lt;/a&gt;, the &lt;a href=\"w%3Ac%3Ademonssouls%3ACrestfallen%20Warrior\"&gt;Crestfallen Warrior&lt;/a&gt; from \"&lt;a href=\"Demon%27s%20Souls\"&gt;Demon's Souls&lt;/a&gt;, \"and &lt;a href=\"Saulden%2C%20the%20Crestfallen%20Warrior\"&gt;Saulden&lt;/a&gt;, the Crestfallen Warrior from \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAppearance.\nThe Crestfallen Warrior wears a helm-less &lt;a href=\"Chain%20Set\"&gt;Chain Set&lt;/a&gt;, and wields a &lt;a href=\"Longsword\"&gt;Longsword&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Heater%20Shield\"&gt;Heater Shield&lt;/a&gt;. He is a pale man with dark hair, stubble, and a surly appearance.\nPlot.\nThe Crestfallen Warrior is the second NPC encountered after &lt;a href=\"Oscar%2C%20Knight%20of%20Astora\"&gt;Oscar&lt;/a&gt; and the first encountered at &lt;a href=\"Firelink%20Shrine\"&gt;Firelink Shrine&lt;/a&gt;. He is largely indifferent toward the player's presence and considers their efforts to be a lost cause, citing giving up and going hollow as better alternatives. Despite his lifeless demeanor and discouraging words, he does have interesting dialogue that fleshes out the backstory for \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\", as well as hints on equipment, where to go next, and other characters.\nSpeaking to the Crestfallen Warrior after &lt;a href=\"Kingseeker%20Frampt\"&gt;Kingseeker Frampt&lt;/a&gt; arrives will prompt him to leave Firelink Shrine, complaining of the \"stench\" (presumably given off by Frampt). He is then found &lt;a href=\"Hollow\"&gt;Hollow&lt;/a&gt;ed near the beginning of the New Londo Ruins.\nStrategy.\nPlayers should avoid attacking the Crestfallen Warrior in the early game; he is very tough for a new player to kill and can offer helpful hints and tips. The Crestfallen Warrior is nimble with his &lt;a href=\"Longsword\"&gt;Longsword&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Heater%20Shield\"&gt;Heater Shield&lt;/a&gt;, but with some dodging and blocking he usually poses little threat by the time the player encounters him as a &lt;a href=\"Hollow\"&gt;Hollow&lt;/a&gt;. The one trick up his sleeve is his ability to &lt;a href=\"Parry%20and%20Riposte\"&gt;parry&lt;/a&gt; unexpectedly. The Crestfallen Warrior is one of the only NPCs that does not have a unique parry \"stance\", so players can do little to nothing to predict when he is going to do so."}
