{"id": "52303", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=52303", "title": "Cromwell the Pardoner", "text": "Cromwell the Pardoner is a &lt;a href=\"Characters%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;character&lt;/a&gt; in\u00a0\"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\".He's voiced by\u00a0, who also voices\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Benhart%20of%20Jugo\"&gt;Benhart of Jugo&lt;/a&gt;.\nLocation.\nCromwell is found in &lt;a href=\"Brightstone%20Cove%20Tseldora\"&gt;Brightstone Cove Tseldora&lt;/a&gt; in a room above the chapel where the\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Prowling%20Magus%20and%20Congregation\"&gt;Prowling Magus and Congregation&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0boss is fought. When the player exits the main doorway, head to the left, and there will be a ladder in which you can climb up into an attic-like room. Cromwell will be standing in the middle of the room.\nCharacter information.\nCromwell, as his title implies, can be visited so the players may have their &lt;a href=\"Sin%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;sins&lt;/a&gt; forgiven. This will not remove the current sin title the player has, but it does allow hostile NPCs that the player provoked to become friendly again (the Royal Soldiers found in the Giant's Memories are excluded from this), as well as removing the damage penalty on the &lt;a href=\"Lost%20Sinner%27s%20Sword\"&gt;Lost Sinner's Sword&lt;/a&gt;, and thus reverting it to the normal damage it dealt.\nHe also sells many useful items, such as useful miracles (such as &lt;a href=\"Great%20Heal%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Great Heal&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Perseverance\"&gt;Perseverance&lt;/a&gt;) and the &lt;a href=\"Negative%20Status%20Effects%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;statusbite&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Rings%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;rings&lt;/a&gt;, which can greatly aid the player along the way.\nHe dons the &lt;a href=\"Judgment%20Set\"&gt;Judgment Set&lt;/a&gt;, similarly to how &lt;a href=\"Oswald%20of%20Carim\"&gt;Oswald of Carim&lt;/a&gt; donned the &lt;a href=\"Black%20Set\"&gt;Black Set&lt;/a&gt;, and wields a &lt;a href=\"Great%20Scythe%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Great Scythe&lt;/a&gt;.\nPardoning.\nWhen requesting absolution or being pardoned for your sins Cromwell will absolve you the first time for free, but after which a hefty amount of &lt;a href=\"Souls%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;souls&lt;/a&gt; will be needed:"}
{"id": "5187", "revid": "5064773", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5187", "title": "Crossbow", "text": ""}
{"id": "3142", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3142", "title": "Crossbows", "text": "Crossbows are a type of ranged &lt;a href=\"Weapons%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;weapon&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\".\nOverview.\nCrossbows use bolts for &lt;a href=\"ammunition\"&gt;ammunition&lt;/a&gt; and follow the same general principles as &lt;a href=\"Bows\"&gt;Bows&lt;/a&gt;, but without the ability to enter any kind of aiming mode. This means the wielders have to rely on the lock-on to guide the bolts to their targets, and that they cannot choose to aim for &lt;a href=\"critical\"&gt;critical&lt;/a&gt; head shots. Headshots still do bonus critical damage, but are almost impossible to do in most situations. To make up for lack of a manual aim, Crossbows generally have slightly better attack power than Bows, and have a lower starting lag for their attacks. Because of the nature of how they operate, Crossbows are much better suited to doing some quick damage while advancing on a target before engaging them in melee combat. None of the Crossbows feature any kind of &lt;a href=\"Stats%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;stat&lt;/a&gt; scaling, therefore upgrading them to &lt;a href=\"elemental\"&gt;elemental&lt;/a&gt; variants is often highly effective.\nThe lack of an aiming mode can be partially solved with the use of &lt;a href=\"Binoculars\"&gt;Binoculars&lt;/a&gt; before shooting.\nThe and value of a crossbow attack is additionally dependent on the type of &lt;a href=\"bolts\"&gt;bolts&lt;/a&gt; the player has equipped. If the player dual-wields two crossbows, ammunition is selected individually for each crossbow. This allows each respective crossbow to potentially fire a different kind of bolt.\nWhile crossbows can be two-handed, there is no benefit to doing so. In fact, two-handing crossbows is actually detrimental, as doing so increases the starting lag and thus lowers the player's DPS.\nCrossbows.\n&lt;tabber&gt;\nDetailed=\nCondensed=\nUpgraded=\n&lt;/tabber&gt;"}
{"id": "52278", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=52278", "title": "Crossbows (Dark Souls II)", "text": "Crossbows are a type of &lt;a href=\"Weapons%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;weapon&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nUnlike the &lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;first game&lt;/a&gt;, crossbows in \"Dark Souls II\" can be aimed in the same manner as a normal &lt;a href=\"Bows%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;bow&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "132916", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=132916", "title": "Crossbows (Dark Souls III)", "text": "Crossbows are a type of &lt;a href=\"Weapons%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;weapon&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nCrossbows are a ranged weapon that have rather low &lt;a href=\"Strength%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Strength&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Dexterity%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Dexterity&lt;/a&gt; requirements and offer no &lt;a href=\"Parameter%20Bonus%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;scaling&lt;/a&gt;, making them ideal for builds that do not invest heavily into physical stats. Unlike &lt;a href=\"Bows%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;bows&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Greatbows%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;greatbows&lt;/a&gt;, crossbows can be held and fired in one hand, but require the player to reload between shots as indicated by an arrow head in the top portion of the weapon icon. This makes them ideal ranged weapons for engaging foes within lock-on range.\nCrossbows can be equipped in either the main hand or off hand. When two-handed, all crossbows have a \"zoom\" feature, activated by pressing the off-hand weak attack button (or block), that allows the player to manually aim their shots from a first-person point of view. It should be noted that different types of &lt;a href=\"Ammunition%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Bolts&lt;/a&gt; have varying ranges that add to a specific crossbow's range. This affects the accuracy of the projectile resulting in some shots seeming inaccurate (this does not affect locked-on shots). Range can also be increased by equipping the &lt;a href=\"Hawk%20Ring%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Hawk Ring&lt;/a&gt;.\nCrossbows.\n&lt;br&gt;"}
{"id": "2598", "revid": "51254358", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=2598", "title": "Crossbreed Priscilla", "text": " is an optional &lt;a href=\"boss\"&gt;boss&lt;/a&gt; found in the &lt;a href=\"Painted%20World%20of%20Ariamis\"&gt;Painted World of Ariamis&lt;/a&gt; and a &lt;a href=\"character\"&gt;character&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\". She is initially non-hostile and will ask the player to leave the world without fighting. \n&lt;a href=\"Soul%20of%20Priscilla\"&gt;Her soul&lt;/a&gt; can be used to &lt;a href=\"Weapon%20Modification\"&gt;ascend&lt;/a&gt; a +10 &lt;a href=\"Halberds\"&gt;Halberd&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Whips\"&gt;Whip&lt;/a&gt; into the &lt;a href=\"Lifehunt%20Scythe\"&gt;Lifehunt Scythe&lt;/a&gt;. As with other &lt;a href=\"dragon\"&gt;dragon&lt;/a&gt; bosses, the player can also obtain a special weapon by cutting her tail off during combat, &lt;a href=\"Priscilla%27s%20Dagger\"&gt;Priscilla's Dagger&lt;/a&gt;.\nDescription.\nPriscilla is a humanoid half-dragon roughly five meters tall. Her skin is extremely pale, her hair is stark white and she has a patch of fur beneath her hairline resembling an exaggerated widow's peak. This fur is framed by a row of small white spikes just above her brows. \nShe has a fluffy white articulate tail with draconic proportions that emerges between two layers of her gown, which is of the same furry texture. She is capable of turning invisible and walks barefoot despite the snowy terrain.\nShe speaks very softly, and attempts diplomacy with those who invade her world but prominently carries a large scythe capable of absorbing the life of her opponents for self-defense.\nLore.\n&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;.\nPriscilla is a crossbreed of the dragon &lt;a href=\"Seath%20the%20Scaleless\"&gt;Seath&lt;/a&gt; and a human woman, likely a result of Seath's many experiments in his search for immortality.\nShe was feared by the &lt;a href=\"Gods\"&gt;gods&lt;/a&gt; of &lt;a href=\"Anor%20Londo\"&gt;Anor Londo&lt;/a&gt; and treated as an abomination due to the fact that her own body was naturally infused with the &lt;a href=\"Occult%20%28auxiliary%20effect%29\"&gt;occult power&lt;/a&gt; capable of killing them.. She possessed also &lt;a href=\"Lifehunt%20Scythe\"&gt;life-hunting&lt;/a&gt; powers and her lineage identified her as completely antithetical to the order and life of the gods. \nEventually Priscilla was sealed away from the world because she was considered \"taboo\" into the cold and lonely &lt;a href=\"Painted%20World%20of%20Ariamis\"&gt;Painted World of Ariamis&lt;/a&gt;, created by &lt;a href=\"Ariamis\"&gt;Ariamis&lt;/a&gt; with the purpose of leaving her alone. The Painted World came to be protected by a specific order of &lt;a href=\"Painting%20Guardian\"&gt;Painting Guardian&lt;/a&gt;s, such was the perceived threat she posed to the reigning Gods. The Gods continued to use the Painted World as a prison, a place to seal away &lt;a href=\"Dark%20Ember\"&gt;dangerous artifacts&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Engorged%20Hollow\"&gt;abominations&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Crow%20Demon\"&gt;sinners&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Hollow\"&gt;Hollow&lt;/a&gt;s. Eventually, &lt;a href=\"Velka%2C%20Goddess%20of%20Sin\"&gt;Velka&lt;/a&gt; spread her influence inside the painted world, as she was the Goddess of Sin. Dozens of &lt;a href=\"Crow%20Demon\"&gt;her cultist followers&lt;/a&gt; found refuge there, and potentially endeavored to protect Priscilla from the other Gods.\nWhen the &lt;a href=\"Chosen%20Undead\"&gt;Chosen Undead&lt;/a&gt; encounters Priscilla, she has come to see herself as a guardian of the Painted World, which she characterizes as \"peaceful,\" and its \"kind\" inhabitants. She pities those trapped within the painting, as the outside world has treated them with hate and locked them away, like herself. She is not hostile to visitors from the outside world, unless provoked, and will only ask them to leave in peace because they don't belong in there, and she will also deny anyone interested in her.\n&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;.\nAt some point Priscilla would become the \"Lady\" of the Painted World and its inhabitants by extension, continuing to welcome the forlorns led into the cold world by the tales of the heretical, corvian storytellers and gifting them &lt;a href=\"Great%20Corvian%20Scythe\"&gt;great scythes&lt;/a&gt;. At some point her &lt;a href=\"Lifehunt%20Scythe\"&gt;Lifehunt Scythe&lt;/a&gt; becoming the symbol of a distant nostalgia. The &lt;a href=\"Corvian\"&gt;humanoid corvians&lt;/a&gt; who continued to find refuge in the painting would then form a &lt;a href=\"Corvian%20Settlement\"&gt;small village&lt;/a&gt;, complete with a library and &lt;a href=\"Corvian%20Knight\"&gt;knights&lt;/a&gt;, developing a high understanding of the &lt;a href=\"First%20Flame\"&gt;First Flame&lt;/a&gt; and the &lt;a href=\"Dark%20Soul\"&gt;Dark Soul&lt;/a&gt;, using the Flame to \"restore\" the Painted World when it was corrupted from time, to avoid the fate of the stagnating outside world. For this purpose, a \"&lt;a href=\"Father%20Ariandel\"&gt;Father&lt;/a&gt;\" was chosen among the corvians who would have to tend to the Flame present in the Painted World to burn it when the time was right and prepare the next one by restoring the painting.\nPriscilla would also have a &lt;a href=\"The%20Painter\"&gt;daughter&lt;/a&gt; who would inherit her draconic traits, along with her high levels of knowledge about the First Flame and the Dark Soul, becoming a \"painter\" with the abilities to harness the two forces and paint Painted Worlds.\nBoss information.\nAttacks.\nSingle Slash.\nThis is a single attack that has good forward range and tracks quite well to both sides. While it is fairly damaging, it can be blocked but not [[parried]]. This attack also causes [[Bleed (Dark Souls)|Bleed]] upon hitting or being blocked.\nDouble Slash.\nVirtually the same as the Single Slash, but with two slashes instead, once from right to left and then left to right. There is a large gap between attacks, and can also track the player.\nFairy Dust.\nAfter a short delay, Priscilla blows a concentrated cloud of blue particles directly in front of her or in a sweeping motion. The resulting cloud lingers for a few seconds afterward. This attack deals a large amount of damage and is difficult to block.\nInvisibility.\nPriscilla turns invisible, whilst still being able to attack the player. Leaves large footprints in the snow.\nMusic.\n&lt;embedvideo service=\"youtube\" alignment=\"center\" description=\"Dark Souls \u2014 Crossbreed Priscilla by [[imdb:nm1245713|Motoi Sakuraba]]\"&gt;https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=6XSbn5EOLdE&lt;/embedvideo&gt;\nFootnotes.\n[[Category:Dark Souls: Characters]]\n[[Category:Dark Souls: Optional Bosses]]\n[[Category:Dragons]]\n[[es:Priscilla la Mestiza]]\n[[pl:P\u00f3\u0142smoczyca Priscilla]]\n[[ru:\u041f\u0440\u0438\u0441\u0446\u0438\u043b\u043b\u0430 \u041f\u043e\u043b\u0443\u043a\u0440\u043e\u0432\u043a\u0430]]"}
{"id": "145740", "revid": "5064773", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=145740", "title": "Crow", "text": ""}
{"id": "6357", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=6357", "title": "Crow Demon", "text": "Crow Demons, also known as Harpies and Crow People of Velka, are in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\".\nLocation.\nCrow Demons are encountered in the &lt;a href=\"Painted%20World%20of%20Ariamis\"&gt;Painted World of Ariamis&lt;/a&gt;.\nDescription.\nCrow Demons are lanky and slightly taller than the player, with pale skin and black feathers. They are a combination of a &lt;a href=\"hollow\"&gt;hollow&lt;/a&gt;'s torso and legs, and a crow's dishevelled wings and head.\nStrategy.\nCrow Demons perform fairly simple attacks for the most part. However, they can fly across short distances, and are able to close gaps very quickly with a potentially fatal grab-attack. This can be easily avoided by staggering them, rolling, or by constantly moving. As soon as they have reached the height at which they dive from, they will cease to track the target's location much like throwing a &lt;a href=\"Fireball\"&gt;Fireball&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Firebomb\"&gt;Firebomb&lt;/a&gt;. Try not to roll too late, as invincibility frames will not prevent being grabbed. Moving closer to them as they ready their attack will also work, as their flight angle is too high.\nCrow Demons are easier engaged one by one, although certain areas make it difficult to lure a single Crow Demon. Players can manipulate the spiral staircase inside the tower where several Crow Demons spawn to force them over the edge, netting easy kills."}
{"id": "143020", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=143020", "title": "Crow Quills", "text": "The Crow Quills is a &lt;a href=\"Thrusting%20Swords%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;thrusting sword&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;: &lt;a href=\"Ashes%20of%20Ariandel\"&gt;Ashes of Ariandel&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nFrom the &lt;a href=\"Corvian%20Settlement\"&gt;Corvian Settlement&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Bonfire%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;bonfire&lt;/a&gt;, head out and across the bridge. Follow the wall of the house on your left until you see a smaller bridge. Go across and follow the path to the left. On your left you will see two entrances across a small gap. Jump it and go into the house on your right. Barrels will be blocking a platform that you need to run and leap off of and land on the elevated platform with the Crow Quills.\nCharacteristics.\nA special thrusting sword, the Crow Quills are specially suited for aggressive playstyles and can be a force to be reckoned with in the right hands.\n&lt;a href=\"Parameter%20Bonus%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Scaling&lt;/a&gt; primarily with &lt;a href=\"Dexterity%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Dexterity&lt;/a&gt;, this weapon's one-handed attacks are the same as that of normal thrusting swords. However, when two-handed, rather than holding the weapon in both hands, the wielder will brandish a set of blades in the off-hand and use them to perform combination attacks. Whereas most thrusting swords have narrow poking attacks that are aimed forward, the Crow Quills allows the wielder to use the blades for slashing attacks, providing wider horizontal coverage than a thrusting sword is normally capable of. This gives the Crow Quills a rather versatile &lt;a href=\"moveset\"&gt;moveset&lt;/a&gt; in which the left-handed blades can cover for the right-handed sword's weaknesses. Of special note, the two-handed running attack provides &lt;a href=\"Hyper%20Armor\"&gt;Hyper Armor&lt;/a&gt; to the wielder, something that no other thrusting sword is capable of doing.\nThe Crow Quills also possesses a unique &lt;a href=\"skill\"&gt;skill&lt;/a&gt; in that the off-hand blades can be thrown in a fan-shaped pattern while leaping in the air. This grants the wielder a form of ranged damage while performing an evasive maneuver, which can be a useful tool in the hands of crafty players."}
{"id": "143021", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=143021", "title": "Crow Talons", "text": "TheCrow Talons is a &lt;a href=\"Claws%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;claw&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;: &lt;a href=\"Ashes%20of%20Ariandel\"&gt;Ashes of Ariandel&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nFound on the rooftops in the &lt;a href=\"Corvian%20Settlement\"&gt;Corvian Settlement&lt;/a&gt;, guarded by two magic-wielding &lt;a href=\"Corvian\"&gt;Corvian&lt;/a&gt;s.\nCharacteristics.\nThe Crow Talons have the same &lt;a href=\"Moveset%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;moveset&lt;/a&gt; as the &lt;a href=\"Claw%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Claws&lt;/a&gt;, with the exception of the two-handed &lt;a href=\"rolling\"&gt;rolling&lt;/a&gt; and running attacks. The running attack is comparable to the weapon art &lt;a href=\"Onislayer\"&gt;Onislayer&lt;/a&gt;, being a jump and cross slash. If used while running off a ledge, it will automatically transition into a &lt;a href=\"plunging%20attack\"&gt;plunging attack&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe main feature of the Crow Talons, however, is their &lt;a href=\"weapon%20art\"&gt;weapon art&lt;/a&gt;, \"&lt;a href=\"Raptor%20Flurry\"&gt;Raptor Flurry&lt;/a&gt;\". When triggered, the wielder will spread their arms before launching forward, gaining &lt;a href=\"Hyper%20Armor\"&gt;Hyper Armor&lt;/a&gt; and rapidly unleashing 6 high stagger attacks with high &lt;a href=\"Bleed%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Bleed&lt;/a&gt; buildup."}
{"id": "7244", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=7244", "title": "Crown of Dusk", "text": "&lt;onlyinclude&gt;&lt;/onlyinclude&gt;\nThe Crown of Dusk is a &lt;a href=\"head%20armor\"&gt;head armor&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\". It is part of the &lt;a href=\"Antiquated%20Set\"&gt;Antiquated Set&lt;/a&gt;.\nAvailability.\nTo be able to obtain this item one needs to firstly defeat the hydra in &lt;a href=\"Darkroot%20Basin\"&gt;Darkroot Basin&lt;/a&gt; and afterwards defeat the golden golem on the leftmost edge of the hydra lake (It is necessary to relog or return to a bonfire for the Golden Golem to appear). The Crown of Dusk is only obtainable after summoning and talking to &lt;a href=\"Dusk%20of%20Oolacile\"&gt;Dusk of Oolacile&lt;/a&gt; at the closest tree to the hydras original spot. It is then found on a corpse in &lt;a href=\"Darkroot%20Basin\"&gt;Darkroot Basin&lt;/a&gt;, near where the &lt;a href=\"Golden%20Crystal%20Golem\"&gt;Golden Crystal Golem&lt;/a&gt; had spawned, along with the rest of the Antiquated Set.\nCharacteristics.\nThe Crown of Dusk boosts the damage of most &lt;a href=\"Sorcery%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;Sorceries&lt;/a&gt;,\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Miracle%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;Miracles&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Pyromancy%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;Pyromancies&lt;/a&gt; by 20%, but lowers &lt;a href=\"Magic%20defense\"&gt;Magic defense&lt;/a&gt; by 30%. It is an inferior choice defensively despite its low &lt;a href=\"weight\"&gt;weight&lt;/a&gt;.\nTrivia.\nThe Crown of Dusk is worn by &lt;a href=\"Dusk%20of%20Oolacile\"&gt;Dusk of Oolacile&lt;/a&gt;.\nUpgrades.\nCannot be &lt;a href=\"Armor%20Modification\"&gt;reinforced&lt;/a&gt;.\n&lt;onlyinclude&gt;&lt;/onlyinclude&gt;"}
{"id": "131363", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=131363", "title": "Crown of Dusk (Dark Souls III)", "text": "The Crown of Dusk is a piece in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\". It is part of the &lt;a href=\"Antiquated%20Set%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Antiquated Set&lt;/a&gt;.\nAvailability.\nFound in &lt;a href=\"Farron%20Keep\"&gt;Farron Keep&lt;/a&gt;, on a corpse lying under a white birch in a stretch of murky water to the left of the main gate and the &lt;a href=\"Keep%20Ruins\"&gt;Keep Ruins&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Bonfire%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;bonfire&lt;/a&gt;. The area is guarded by a &lt;a href=\"Great%20Crab\"&gt;Great Crab&lt;/a&gt;.\nIf the player befriended the &lt;a href=\"Giant%20Archer%20of%20the%20Undead%20Settlement\"&gt;Giant Archer of the Undead Settlement&lt;/a&gt;, he will fire greatarrows at any enemies near the birch, including the Great Crab. Each arrow will automatically &lt;a href=\"stagger\"&gt;stagger&lt;/a&gt; the crab for a free &lt;a href=\"Riposte%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;riposte&lt;/a&gt;, making it significantly easier to deal with."}
{"id": "8162", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=8162", "title": "Crown of the Dark Sun", "text": "&lt;onlyinclude&gt;&lt;/onlyinclude&gt;\nThe Crown of the Dark Sun (\u9670\u306e\u592a\u967d\u306e\u738b\u51a0) is a &lt;a href=\"head%20armor\"&gt;head armor&lt;/a&gt; piece in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\". It is part of the &lt;a href=\"Moonlight%20Set\"&gt;Moonlight Set&lt;/a&gt;.\nCharacteristics.\nThe Crown of the Dark Sun offers average &lt;a href=\"defense\"&gt;defense&lt;/a&gt;s but high &lt;a href=\"Curse%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;Curse&lt;/a&gt; resistance. It boosts the damage of all &lt;a href=\"spells\"&gt;spells&lt;/a&gt;, except for &lt;a href=\"Weapon%20Augmentation\"&gt;weapon augments&lt;/a&gt;, by 10%.\nThe Crown of the Dark Sun does not have a negative effect on &lt;a href=\"magic%20defense\"&gt;magic defense&lt;/a&gt;, unlike the &lt;a href=\"Crown%20of%20Dusk\"&gt;Crown of Dusk&lt;/a&gt;. This makes it a lower-risk, but also lower-reward, alternative to the Crown of Dusk.\nUpgrades.\nThe Crown of the Dark Sun cannot be reinforced.\n&lt;onlyinclude&gt;&lt;/onlyinclude&gt;\nDescription.\n&lt;tabber&gt;Official translation=\n&lt;/tabber&gt;"}
{"id": "8099", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=8099", "title": "Crown of the Great Lord", "text": "&lt;onlyinclude&gt;&lt;/onlyinclude&gt;\nThe Crown of the Great Lord (\u5927\u738b\u306e\u738b\u51a0) is a piece in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\". It is part of the &lt;a href=\"Great%20Lord%20Set\"&gt;Great Lord Set&lt;/a&gt;.\nCharacteristics.\nThe Crown of the Great Lord offers mediocre stats and no &lt;a href=\"Poise%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;Poise&lt;/a&gt;. The &lt;a href=\"Gargoyle%20Helm\"&gt;Gargoyle Helm&lt;/a&gt; (heavier by only 0.5) has about the same characteristics as The Crown of the Great Lord, but once fully &lt;a href=\"Armor%20Modification\"&gt;upgraded&lt;/a&gt;, the Gargoyle Helm beats the Crown of the Great Lord in almost every regard.\nThe Crown of the Great Lord's only redeeming aspect is its very high &lt;a href=\"Curse%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;Curse&lt;/a&gt; resist (20, the Gargoyle Helmet has none). That said, if the player is really looking to max out Curse resistance, they may consider instead using the heavier &lt;a href=\"Xanthous%20Crown\"&gt;Xanthous Crown&lt;/a&gt;, that will offer nearly double the curse protection and slightly better stats.\nUpgrades.\nCannot be reinforced.\n&lt;onlyinclude&gt;&lt;/onlyinclude&gt;\nDescription.\n&lt;tabber&gt;Official translation=\n&lt;/tabber&gt;"}
{"id": "88022", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=88022", "title": "Crown of the Ivory King", "text": "The Crown of the Ivory King is the third episode of the \"&lt;a href=\"The%20Lost%20Crowns\"&gt;The Lost Crowns&lt;/a&gt;\" downloadable content pack for \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\". It was released on September 30th, 2014 for Steam and Xbox Live and on October 1st, 2014 for the PSN.\u00a0\nAccess.\nTo access the content, use the altar inside the &lt;a href=\"Shrine%20of%20Winter\"&gt;Shrine of Winter&lt;/a&gt; to travel to the starting area. The &lt;a href=\"Frozen%20Flower\"&gt;Frozen Flower&lt;/a&gt; is granted upon loading and is required to open the door to &lt;a href=\"Frozen%20Eleum%20Loyce\"&gt;Frozen Eleum Loyce&lt;/a&gt;. In the -edition, the Frozen Flower is also found in &lt;a href=\"Drangleic%20Castle\"&gt;Drangleic Castle&lt;/a&gt;."}
