{"id": "150113", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=150113", "title": "Crucifix of the Mad King", "text": "The Crucifix of the Mad King is a &lt;a href=\"Halberds%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;halberd&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;: &lt;a href=\"The%20Ringed%20City\"&gt;The Ringed City&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nDropped by &lt;a href=\"Shira%2C%20Knight%20of%20Filianore\"&gt;Shira, Knight of Filianore&lt;/a&gt; when she invades the player at &lt;a href=\"Pygmy%27s%20Throne\"&gt;Pygmy's Throne&lt;/a&gt;.\nCharacteristics.\nOne of the strongest and most unique weapons in the game, the Crucifix of the Mad King has many unique characteristics and can be extremely powerful when utilized properly.\nAs a halberd, the Crucifix possesses respectable range and a moderate swing speed on its attacks. It is a split-damage weapon, inflicting both physical and &lt;a href=\"Dark%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Dark&lt;/a&gt; damage with its attacks. This damage &lt;a href=\"Parameter%20Bonus%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;scales&lt;/a&gt; primarily with &lt;a href=\"Strength%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Strength&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Faith%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Faith&lt;/a&gt;, with Faith being the more important component as it governs both damage types. Along with its non-negligible &lt;a href=\"Intelligence%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Intelligence&lt;/a&gt; wielding requirement, this means that any build that wishes to use this weapon must be specifically tailored to use it.\nUnlike other halberds, the Crucifix possesses the &lt;a href=\"Poise%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Poise&lt;/a&gt; health and Poise damage of a &lt;a href=\"Greatswords%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;greatsword&lt;/a&gt;, giving it extremely powerful &lt;a href=\"Hyper%20Armor\"&gt;Hyper Armor&lt;/a&gt; attacks and allowing it to more easily break the Poise of opponents. As well, rather than the standard spinning sweep attacks of most halberds, the Crucifix borrows its strong attacks from the &lt;a href=\"Great%20Club%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Great Club&lt;/a&gt;, and as a result its strong attacks cannot be &lt;a href=\"Parry%20and%20Riposte%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;parried&lt;/a&gt; under any circumstance, even when one-handed.\nDespite upgrading with &lt;a href=\"Twinkling%20Titanite%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Twinkling Titanite&lt;/a&gt;, the Crucifix can still be buffed, and this attribute is what makes it one of the most powerful weapons in the game. As its innate Dark damage scales with Faith, this component of its damage output can be further increased by buffing it with additional Dark damage, particularly by casting &lt;a href=\"Dark%20Blade\"&gt;Dark Blade&lt;/a&gt; on it, which also increases in strength with Faith investment. When wielded in this manner, a Crucifix of the Mad King can inflict damage that rivals that dealt by &lt;a href=\"Ultra%20Greatswords%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;ultra greatswords&lt;/a&gt;.\nPerhaps the most unique aspect of the Crucifix is its skill, &lt;a href=\"Mad%20King%27s%20Folly\"&gt;Mad King's Folly&lt;/a&gt;. The starting attack possesses extremely powerful &lt;a href=\"Hyper%20Armor\"&gt;Hyper Armor&lt;/a&gt; and inflicts high Poise damage, but following up with the pygmy king's various enchantments can allow the wielder to bring additional power to the weapon, albeit in an unpredictable manner.\nAll of these strengths do not come without drawbacks, however. Despite being a halberd, it is one of the shortest in its class, with many &lt;a href=\"Spears%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;spears&lt;/a&gt; and even &lt;a href=\"Reapers%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;reapers&lt;/a&gt; being able to easily out-range it. Additionally, it is a ravenous consumer of stamina, with many of its attacks costing more than the same attacks by its cousins, thus requiring its wielder to invest more in &lt;a href=\"Endurance%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Endurance&lt;/a&gt;.\nOverall, despite these shortcomings, the Crucifix of the Mad King is still a very formidable weapon, one that is capable of inflicting tremendous amounts of damage against its foes.\nMoveset.\n&lt;br&gt;&lt;a href=\"https%3A//youtu.be/gIGh1SzTsPw%3Ft%3D183\"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;\nUpgrades.\n&lt;br&gt;"}
