{"id": "49406", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=49406", "title": "Crushed Eye Orb", "text": " is an &lt;a href=\"Miscellaneous%20Items%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;item&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nThe Crushed Eye Orb is located in a chest in the &lt;a href=\"Undead%20Crypt\"&gt;Undead Crypt&lt;/a&gt;. The chest is located within the room directly after meeting &lt;a href=\"Grave%20Warden%20Agdayne\"&gt;Agdayne&lt;/a&gt;.\u00a0By the bridge with the two &lt;a href=\"Syan%20Knight\"&gt;Syan Knight&lt;/a&gt;s there is a ladder. To reach the ladder the player must jump off of the ledge to the lower platform. To the left of the door is easiest. There will be the bottom of the ladder and then climb it to get to the chest.\nGeneral information.\nThe Crushed Eye Orb is used to invade the world of the traitor &lt;a href=\"Licia%20of%20Lindeldt\"&gt;Licia of Lindeldt&lt;/a&gt;. In order to do so, the player must go to Licia by the contraption which requires the\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Rotunda%20Lockstone\"&gt;Rotunda Lockstone&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0in between\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Majula\"&gt;Majula&lt;/a&gt;,\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Heide%27s%20Tower%20of%20Flame\"&gt;Heide's Tower of Flame&lt;/a&gt;,\u00a0and\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Huntsman%27s%20Copse\"&gt;Huntsman's Copse&lt;/a&gt;.\u00a0Once there, a message telling the player that the Crushed Eye Orb is shivering will pop up, and the player will be allowed to invade the world of Licia of Lindeldt using the Crushed Eye Orb."}
{"id": "51446", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=51446", "title": "Crypt Blacksword", "text": "The Crypt Blacksword is an &lt;a href=\"Ultra%20Greatswords%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;ultra greatsword&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nAcquired from\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Weaponsmith%20Ornifex\"&gt;Weaponsmith Ornifex&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0in\u00a0exchange for\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Old%20Dead%20One%20Soul\"&gt;Old Dead One Soul&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0and 10,000 souls.\nCharacteristics.\nThis is a very interesting &lt;a href=\"Ultra%20Greatswords%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Ultra Greatsword&lt;/a&gt;, and easily stands out for a variety of different reasons, for instance, rather than swinging like other Ultra Greatswords, the Crypt Blacksword possesses a &lt;a href=\"Greataxe%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Greataxe&lt;/a&gt;'s moveset, and it deals a very large amount of &lt;a href=\"Dark%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Dark&lt;/a&gt; damage, as well as having a superior scaling in said element. It is also amongst the weapons that deal the most &lt;a href=\"Poise%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Poise&lt;/a&gt; damage, at a value of 60.\nUpgrades on this weapon will only raise its damage value, and it will raise its D in Strength up to a C, which will only provide a very minute damage increase. However, should a player have good values of &lt;a href=\"Faith%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Faith&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Intelligence%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Intelligence&lt;/a&gt;, it is suggested that they infuse this weapon with Dark, as it will instead turn the A value of Dark into S. This is an outstanding upgrade as it will vastly increase the Dark damage by a considerable amount, turning this weapon into almost a Dark damage version of the &lt;a href=\"Moonlight%20Greatsword%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Moonlight Greatsword&lt;/a&gt;. This is useful because should an enemy block a player's attack with a shield that has little to no Dark resistance, then most of the damage dealt will go through it and damage the enemy. Using either the &lt;a href=\"Resonant%20Weapon\"&gt;Resonant Weapon&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Dark%20Weapon\"&gt;Dark Weapon&lt;/a&gt; Hex is also a very good idea in order to further boost the Dark damage. \nThis weapon counts as a &lt;a href=\"Greataxes%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Greataxe&lt;/a&gt; for the purposes of &lt;a href=\"Power%20Stance\"&gt;Powerstancing&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "155531", "revid": "5064773", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=155531", "title": "Crystal", "text": ""}
{"id": "133989", "revid": "5064773", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=133989", "title": "Crystal (Upgrade Path)", "text": ""}
{"id": "162365", "revid": "33084951", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=162365", "title": "Crystal (disambiguation)", "text": ""}
{"id": "6975", "revid": "44712929", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=6975", "title": "Crystal (upgrade path)", "text": "Crystal is an &lt;a href=\"upgrade%20path\"&gt;upgrade path&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Giant%20Blacksmith\"&gt;Giant Blacksmith&lt;/a&gt; gains the ability to &lt;a href=\"Weapon%20Modification\"&gt;ascend&lt;/a&gt; weapons down the Crystal path after receiving the &lt;a href=\"Crystal%20Ember\"&gt;Crystal Ember&lt;/a&gt;. Creation of a Crystal weapon requires a &lt;a href=\"standard%20weapon\"&gt;standard weapon&lt;/a&gt; +10, &lt;a href=\"Titanite%20Chunk\"&gt;Titanite Chunk&lt;/a&gt;s for upgrading to +4, and a &lt;a href=\"Titanite%20Slab\"&gt;Titanite Slab&lt;/a&gt; for upgrading to +5, as well as the requisite &lt;a href=\"souls\"&gt;souls&lt;/a&gt;.\nAditionally, a Crystal &lt;a href=\"Halberd\"&gt;Halberd&lt;/a&gt; and a Crystal &lt;a href=\"Knight%20Shield\"&gt;Knight Shield&lt;/a&gt; can be found inside &lt;a href=\"Mimic\"&gt;Mimics&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Anor%20Londo\"&gt;Anor Londo&lt;/a&gt; and in &lt;a href=\"The%20Duke%27s%20Archives\"&gt;The Duke's Archives&lt;/a&gt;, respectively. The former is found in the room to the left coming from the first bonfire, to the right guarded by two &lt;a href=\"Sentinel\"&gt;Sentinels&lt;/a&gt;. The latter is found in the room of the elevator that takes you to &lt;a href=\"Seath%20the%20Scaleless\"&gt;Seath&lt;/a&gt; for the first time, towards the right half of the front of the room when you go up the stairs.\nGeneral information.\nCrystal weapons are functionally very similar to weapons upgraded down the &lt;a href=\"Standard%20%28upgrade%20path%29\"&gt;Standard&lt;/a&gt; path: they deal only &lt;a href=\"physical%20damage\"&gt;physical damage&lt;/a&gt;, can be &lt;a href=\"Weapon%20Augmentation\"&gt;augmented&lt;/a&gt;, and gain increased scaling with &lt;a href=\"Strength%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;Strength&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Dexterity%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;Dexterity&lt;/a&gt; at +0 and +4.\u00a0\nHowever, Crystal weapons have some important characteristics that set them apart from Standard weapons. Crystal weapons deal higher damage than Standard weapons, making them the most powerful choice for Dexterity and Strength builds. On the other hand, Crystal weapons cannot be repaired, and their durability is reduced to a tenth of its original value. For example, a weapon which has an original durability of 200 will have a durability of 20 as a Crystal item.\nAs a consequence of upgrading weapons and\u00a0shields down the Crystal path, once the item's durability runs out, it can only be restored by upgrading. Once a +5 Crystal weapon breaks, it is permanently broken. Thus, the Crystal upgrade path is most suitable for weapons which can be re-obtained in the same play-through. Unlike other upgrade paths, Crystal weapons cannot be &lt;a href=\"Weapon%20Modification%23Downgrading\"&gt;reverted&lt;/a&gt; to their standard state.\nNotes.\nFurther reinforcing Crystal weapons restores their durability.\u00a0\nUsing the &lt;a href=\"East%20Wood%20Grain%20Ring\"&gt;East Wood Grain Ring&lt;/a&gt; can extend the life of Crystal weapons by slowing the degradation of the weapon."}
{"id": "150316", "revid": "33084951", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=150316", "title": "Crystal Blade", "text": "Crystal Blade is a &lt;a href=\"skill\"&gt;skill&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nDescription.\nThe wielder flourishes the weapon, forming a blade of crystal around the dagger and holding it ready. This transformation costs no &lt;a href=\"Focus%20Point\"&gt;Focus Point&lt;/a&gt;s, and reduces the wielder to walking speed while it is active.\nThe skill is also context-sensitive, and activating it while running, rolling or immediately after any regular attack will perform a unique transforming attack, each of them costing 8 FP (6 FP with the &lt;a href=\"Farron%20Ring\"&gt;Farron Ring&lt;/a&gt; equipped):\nOnce in its transformed mode, the weapon can perform a chain of two weak attacks or two strong attacks:\nUsage.\nSingle player.\nBecause this skill augments the weapon's Magic damage while also slightly weakening its Physical damage, this skill is most optimally used should the wielder have high &lt;a href=\"Intelligence%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Intelligence&lt;/a&gt;. However, as Focus Points are a precious resource, it is ideal to try to limit the use of this skill unless a &lt;a href=\"Simple%20Gem\"&gt;Simple&lt;/a&gt;-infused tool is being carried in the off-hand.\nOnline gameplay.\nThe different timings, animations and reach on all of the trick attacks make the Aquamarine Dagger an extremely hard weapon to predict. In the hands of an aggressive player, it becomes a monster of a weapon, able to dance around foes and catch them no matter how they attempt to evade it. The lunging trick attacks can be used to chase down foes that try to roll away, and the combination weak attacks can catch people trying to outspace it.\nFor best results, it is ideal to combine the trick and transformation attacks with standard attacks using the dagger itself. As well, one should be very mindful of &lt;a href=\"Endurance%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;stamina&lt;/a&gt; consumption while using this skill, as it consumes copious amounts of stamina."}
