{"id": "11191", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=11191", "title": "Crystal Golem", "text": "Crystal Golems are in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\".\nDescription.\nThey are large masses of faceless and vaguely humanoid crystal, animated by unknown means.\nStrategy.\nDue to their slow speed, it is fairly easy to stay behind them. This will cause them to attempt to turn to face the player most of the time.\nCrystal Golems are \"phenomenally\" resistant to magic damage. Trying to bring them down with sorceries, or weapons that do primarily magical damage (such as the &lt;a href=\"Moonlight%20Butterfly%20Horn\"&gt;Moonlight Butterfly Horn&lt;/a&gt;) is incredibly inefficient."}
{"id": "5108", "revid": "56333033", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5108", "title": "Crystal Greatsword", "text": "The Crystal Greatsword is a &lt;a href=\"Greatswords%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;greatsword&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nSold by &lt;a href=\"Domhnall%20of%20Zena\"&gt;Domhnall of Zena&lt;/a&gt; for 6,000\u00a0&lt;a href=\"souls\"&gt;souls&lt;/a&gt;.\nCharacteristics.\nThe Crystal Greatsword's high base damage means that at the point where it first can be bought, it will be quite powerful and effective in both the &lt;a href=\"Depths\"&gt;Depths&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Blighttown\"&gt;Blighttown&lt;/a&gt;, being about equal to a &lt;a href=\"Bastard%20Sword\"&gt;Bastard Sword&lt;/a&gt; +8 in terms of attack power and moveset. However, it can't be &lt;a href=\"Weapon%20Modification\"&gt;upgraded&lt;/a&gt; or repaired, making it unsuitable for sustained use or high level play.\nUpgrades.\nCannot be reinforced."}
{"id": "131199", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=131199", "title": "Crystal Hail", "text": "Crystal Hail is a &lt;a href=\"Boss%20Soul%20Items%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;soul-transposed&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Sorcery%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Sorcery&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nObtained by transposing the &lt;a href=\"Soul%20of%20a%20Crystal%20Sage\"&gt;Soul of a Crystal Sage&lt;/a&gt; and 1,500 &lt;a href=\"Soul%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;souls&lt;/a&gt; with &lt;a href=\"Ludleth%20of%20Courland\"&gt;Ludleth of Courland&lt;/a&gt;.\nEffect.\nConjures a large crystal mass, which rises skyward. After a short delay, the crystal mass sequentially launches numerous crystal soulmasses, 22 in total, which rain down on the general &lt;a href=\"Area%20of%20effect\"&gt;area&lt;/a&gt;. Each soulmass has minor tracking capability, homing in on targets within the area and inflicting 0.62 times the &lt;a href=\"Catalysts%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;catalyst's&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Buff\"&gt;Spell Buff&lt;/a&gt; as &lt;a href=\"Magic%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Magic&lt;/a&gt; damage upon impact, as well as minor &lt;a href=\"stagger\"&gt;stagger&lt;/a&gt;.\n&lt;br&gt;"}
