{"id": "11184", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=11184", "title": "Crystal Lizard", "text": "Crystal Lizards are non-respawning in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\". They can be found in numerous throughout the game.\nDescription.\nCrystal Lizards are unique in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\" in that they do not attack. Instead, they run away once the player approaches them and will soon disappear in a vanishing animation, in which they bob their head up and down. Once killed they will not respawn. They are a primary source of &lt;a href=\"Twinkling%20Titanite\"&gt;Twinkling Titanite&lt;/a&gt; until later in the game.\nEnemy information.\nCharacteristics\nDrops.\n&lt;tabber&gt;\nUndead Burg/Darkroot=\n&lt;a href=\"Undead%20Burg\"&gt;Undead Burg&lt;/a&gt;/&lt;a href=\"Darkroot%20Basin\"&gt;Darkroot Basin&lt;/a&gt;\nCatacombs/Tomb=\n&lt;a href=\"The%20Catacombs\"&gt;The Catacombs&lt;/a&gt;/&lt;a href=\"Tomb%20of%20the%20Giants\"&gt;Tomb of the Giants&lt;/a&gt;\nDuke's Archives/Crystal Cave=\n&lt;a href=\"The%20Duke%27s%20Archives\"&gt;The Duke's Archives&lt;/a&gt;/&lt;a href=\"Crystal%20Cave\"&gt;Crystal Cave&lt;/a&gt;\nLost Izalith=\n&lt;a href=\"Lost%20Izalith\"&gt;Lost Izalith&lt;/a&gt;\nGreat Hollow=\n&lt;a href=\"The%20Great%20Hollow\"&gt;The Great Hollow&lt;/a&gt;\n&lt;/tabber&gt;"}
{"id": "60991", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=60991", "title": "Crystal Lizard (Dark Souls II)", "text": "Crystal Lizards are a non-hostile &lt;a href=\"Enemies%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;enemies&lt;/a&gt; in\u00a0\"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\".\u00a0They act similarly to their &lt;a href=\"Crystal%20Lizard\"&gt;counterparts&lt;/a&gt; from the &lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;previous game&lt;/a&gt;. If the player approaches a lizard, it will attempt to escape by any means, even by jumping off ledges and vanishing. They drop different forms of &lt;a href=\"Upgrade%20Materials%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;upgrade materials&lt;/a&gt; upon death and do not respawn.\nGeneral information.\nUnlike their &lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;previous game&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Crystal%20Lizard\"&gt;counterparts&lt;/a&gt;, whose loot was randomly selected from a set of drops, each Crystal Lizard in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\" has a single fixed drop. These drops most of the time include two or three types of and may have different quantities of each one. Furthermore, if a lizard manages to escape, they can be reset by resting at a &lt;a href=\"Bonfire%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;bonfire&lt;/a&gt;, making it easier for the player to get all possible loot from them in areas where enemies abound (like in &lt;a href=\"Dragon%20Aerie\"&gt;Dragon Aerie&lt;/a&gt;). Once slain, they won't respawn until the next &lt;a href=\"New%20Game%20Plus%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;New Game cycle&lt;/a&gt;, or when an &lt;a href=\"Bonfire%20Ascetic\"&gt;ascetic&lt;/a&gt; is burned in the bonfire that governs them. However, if using a Bonfire Ascetic, they will not drop their loot again; only a New Game cycle will reset the loot.\nStrategy.\nCrystal Lizards usually have high amounts of HP and sometimes may require more than one hit to kill. They usually dwell at plain sight, however, allowing players to plan a strategy before attempting to hunt them. Approaching them from the rear is not recommended, as the lizard will just start moving in the direction it's already facing, most likely outrunning the player and succeeding in their escape. If there's no other option than to approach them from behind, though, the player should try to make them either run into a wall or a dead end if possible.\nOn the other hand, if approached from the front, the lizard will first have to slowly turn around before attempting to escape, giving the player ample time to slay it.\nIf a lizard is far away but already facing at the player's direction, thus giving it enough time to turn around and escape before the player can even make it to their location, a good strategy is to shoot them with a ranged attack (e.g.: an arrow); this will make the lizard to start running forward and toward the player's location, making it easier to finish it.\nRed Crystal Lizards.\nUnlike their blue counterparts, &lt;a href=\"Red%20Crystal%20Lizard\"&gt;Red Crystal Lizard&lt;/a&gt;s may explode when approached or attacked. They don't drop any items upon death and only appear as minor hindrances to the player. They won't respawn once slain and the player may opt to kill them as soon as possible to remove the threat they impose from the map.\nGuide.\nThis guide refers to the version of \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\". It lists all Crystal Lizards appearing in the game and the loot dropped by each one. Some locations may differ from the &lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;original game&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "134766", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=134766", "title": "Crystal Lizard (Dark Souls III)", "text": "Crystal Lizards are non-hostile in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nDescription.\nCrystal Lizards are small titanite reptiles found throughout the \"Dark Souls\" universe. Once killed, they will drop a variety of different types of . The type of titanite they drop is dependent on the location the lizard is encountered at. These enemies are non-hostile, in fact quite the opposite as they will attempt to run away if the player approaches them.\nStrategy.\nCrystal Lizards can be ran up on quick enough to deliver a heavy blow with either a heavy or medium weapon, toppling them and allowing for another successful hit. This is also possible with other lighter weapons, although subsequent attacks become much less likely to connect.\nThe player can steer a lizard's direction of movement by running around them opposite to the direction they want them to face. Using this strategy to push them into walls and away from danger can make them much easier to deal with in situations where killing them can be difficult or risky.\nAdditionally, if the player missed a lizard on their first try, they can make them respawn by quitting and reloading the game. This process can be repeated indefinitely (Crystal Lizards will not respawn if the player only rests at a &lt;a href=\"Bonfire%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;bonfire&lt;/a&gt;, the area needs to be reloaded)."}
{"id": "4535", "revid": "357118", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4535", "title": "Crystal Magic Weapon", "text": "Crystal Magic Weapon (\u7d50\u6676\u9b54\u6cd5\u306e\u6b66\u5668) is a &lt;a href=\"Sorcery%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;Sorcery&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nSold by &lt;a href=\"Big%20Hat%20Logan\"&gt;Big Hat Logan&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"The%20Duke%27s%20Archives\"&gt;The Duke's Archives&lt;/a&gt; for 20,000 &lt;a href=\"soul\"&gt;soul&lt;/a&gt;s after he has been freed the second time.\nGeneral information.\nCrystal Magic Weapon may only be used on &lt;a href=\"enchant\"&gt;enchant&lt;/a&gt;able &lt;a href=\"Weapons%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;weapons&lt;/a&gt;, which are those that are upgraded down the &lt;a href=\"Standard%20%28upgrade%20path%29\"&gt;Standard&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Raw%20%28upgrade%20path%29\"&gt;Raw&lt;/a&gt;, or &lt;a href=\"Crystal%20%28upgrade%20path%29\"&gt;Crystal&lt;/a&gt; paths, as well as a limited amount of &lt;a href=\"Weapon%20Augmentation%23Non-standard%20weapons\"&gt;exceptions&lt;/a&gt;.\nThis spell adds a flat amount of magic attack power to the equipped melee weapon equal to \u00d71.4 the magic adjust of the equipped &lt;a href=\"Catalysts\"&gt;catalyst&lt;/a&gt; and lasts for a duration of one minute. As with other sorcery-based weapon buffs, Crystal Magic Weapon does not receive damage benefits from the &lt;a href=\"Bellowing%20Dragoncrest%20Ring\"&gt;Bellowing Dragoncrest Ring&lt;/a&gt;, but does receive duration-lengthening benefits of the &lt;a href=\"Lingering%20Dragoncrest%20Ring\"&gt;Lingering Dragoncrest Ring&lt;/a&gt;.\nAs the buff reaches closer to the end of its duration, the number of crystal present on the weapon diminishes. When all the crystals have disappeared the buff expires.\nOverview.\nCrystal Magic Weapon is the strongest sorcery-based &lt;a href=\"weapon%20augmentation\"&gt;weapon augmentation&lt;/a&gt; in the game. This makes it the magical enchantment of choice for &lt;a href=\"PvP\"&gt;PvP&lt;/a&gt;.\nWhile Crystal Magic Weapon is not as strong as the miracle-based weapon buffs &lt;a href=\"Darkmoon%20Blade\"&gt;Darkmoon Blade&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Sunlight%20Blade\"&gt;Sunlight Blade&lt;/a&gt;, it does hold several key advantages over them. It has a lower &lt;a href=\"Intelligence%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;Intelligence&lt;/a&gt; requirement than the &lt;a href=\"Faith%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;Faith&lt;/a&gt; requirement for either Darkmoon Blade or Sunlight Blade, and it has more casts than either of them. Finally, while Crystal Magic Weapon benefits from the &lt;a href=\"Lingering%20Dragoncrest%20Ring\"&gt;Lingering Dragoncrest Ring&lt;/a&gt;, Darkmoon Blade and Sunlight Blade do not.\nWhile Darkmoon Blade and Sunlight Blade scale better with a &lt;a href=\"Talismans\"&gt;Talisman&lt;/a&gt;'s magic adjust, the &lt;a href=\"Tin%20Crystallization%20Catalyst\"&gt;Tin Crystallization Catalyst&lt;/a&gt; is able to provide higher magic adjust than any other talisman, making the Crystal Magic Weapon comparatively more powerful for the same amount of casts. However, if at +1 or higher in the &lt;a href=\"Blade%20of%20the%20Darkmoon\"&gt;Blade of the Darkmoon&lt;/a&gt; covenant, the Darkmoon Blade augment gains even higher Faith scaling. Which allows it to outperform Crystal Magic Weapon, even when using the Tin Crystallization Catalyst at max Intelligence (assuming an equivalent level of Faith and use of the &lt;a href=\"Darkmoon%20Talisman\"&gt;Darkmoon Talisman&lt;/a&gt;, the strongest available at high Faith).\nDescription.\n&lt;tabber&gt;Official translation=\n&lt;/tabber&gt;"}
{"id": "73934", "revid": "56333033", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=73934", "title": "Crystal Magic Weapon (Dark Souls II)", "text": "Crystal Magic Weapon is a &lt;a href=\"Sorcery%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;sorcery&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nEffect.\nApplies a &lt;a href=\"Magic%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Magic&lt;/a&gt; buff to the weapon in the hand opposite the &lt;a href=\"Staves\"&gt;staff&lt;/a&gt; used to cast the spell. Though it is stronger than the &lt;a href=\"Magic%20Weapon%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Magic&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Great%20Magic%20Weapon%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Great&lt;/a&gt; variants, Crystal Magic Weapon's low amount of casts, moderate at best duration, and fairly high requirements means it is best reserved for fights against strong foes such as bosses.\nThe total bonus is difficult to calculate, but is roughly 30% of the sum (15 + weapon's Magic scaling * character's Magic bonus + weapon's Base damage), with a small additional damage bonus on &lt;a href=\"Faintstone\"&gt;Magic&lt;/a&gt; infused weapons.\nThe duration scales with Intelligence, starting at 27 seconds at 10 Intelligence when this spell is spiced down going all the way up to 99 seconds when the duration scaling is capped at 42 Intelligence. \nAttunement milestones.\nLike all other spells, the amount of casts per slot increases upon reaching certain &lt;a href=\"Attunement%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Attunement&lt;/a&gt; milestones:\nDuration Scaling Information.\nDuration values are listed in seconds. Base duration of this spell only depends on Intelligence. Base duration shown as well as values with the &lt;a href=\"Lingering%20Dragoncrest%20Ring%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Lingering Dragoncrest&lt;/a&gt; variants applied and pieces of &lt;a href=\"Northwarder%20Set\"&gt;Northwarder Set&lt;/a&gt; applied. "}
{"id": "133929", "revid": "51254358", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=133929", "title": "Crystal Magic Weapon (Dark Souls III)", "text": "Crystal Magic Weapon (\u7d50\u6676\u9b54\u529b\u306e\u6b66\u5668) is a &lt;a href=\"Sorcery%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;sorcery&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nSold by &lt;a href=\"Orbeck%20of%20Vinheim\"&gt;Orbeck of Vinheim&lt;/a&gt; for 10,000 &lt;a href=\"Soul%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;souls&lt;/a&gt; once he has been given the &lt;a href=\"Crystal%20Scroll\"&gt;Crystal Scroll&lt;/a&gt;.\nEffect.\nReinforces right-hand weapon with &lt;a href=\"Magic%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Magic&lt;/a&gt;, adding 95% of the &lt;a href=\"Catalysts%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;catalyst's&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Buff\"&gt;Spell Buff&lt;/a&gt; as Magic damage for 60 seconds. The duration of the buff can be extended by equipping the &lt;a href=\"Lingering%20Dragoncrest%20Ring%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Lingering Dragoncrest Ring&lt;/a&gt;.\nFor catalysts that &lt;a href=\"Scaling%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;scale&lt;/a&gt; with both &lt;a href=\"Intelligence%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Intelligence&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Faith%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Faith&lt;/a&gt;, only the Intelligence portion of the Spell Buff is counted. Special catalysts such as the &lt;a href=\"Archdeacon%27s%20Great%20Staff\"&gt;Archdeacon's Great Staff&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Man-grub%27s%20Staff\"&gt;Man-grub's Staff&lt;/a&gt; are treated as having the base 100 Spell Buff.\nDescription.\n&lt;tabber&gt;Official translation=\n&lt;/tabber&gt;"}
