{"id": "6008", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=6008", "title": "Crystal Ring Shield", "text": "The Crystal Ring Shield is a &lt;a href=\"small%20shield\"&gt;small shield&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nThe Crystal Ring Shield can be created at the &lt;a href=\"Giant%20Blacksmith\"&gt;Giant Blacksmith&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Anor%20Londo\"&gt;Anor Londo&lt;/a&gt; with a +10 &lt;a href=\"Shields\"&gt;Shield&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Weapon%20Modification\"&gt;upgraded&lt;/a&gt; down the &lt;a href=\"Standard%20%28upgrade%20path%29\"&gt;Standard path&lt;/a&gt;, the &lt;a href=\"Soul%20of%20the%20Moonlight%20Butterfly\"&gt;Soul of the Moonlight Butterfly&lt;/a&gt; and 5,000 &lt;a href=\"Soul%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;souls&lt;/a&gt;.\nCharacteristics.\nThe Crystal Ring Shield is a unique small shield because its &lt;a href=\"parry\"&gt;parry&lt;/a&gt; is replaced by an action that uses a ranged &lt;a href=\"Magic%20%28damage%20type%29\"&gt;magic&lt;/a&gt; attack. The attack uses 4 &lt;a href=\"durability\"&gt;durability&lt;/a&gt; points and ignores the &lt;a href=\"East%20Wood%20Grain%20Ring\"&gt;East Wood Grain Ring&lt;/a&gt;. It has a very high magic defense but has the second lowest &lt;a href=\"Physical%20defense\"&gt;Physical defense&lt;/a&gt;, as well as the lowest &lt;a href=\"lightning%20defense\"&gt;lightning defense&lt;/a&gt;, of any small shield. It ties with the &lt;a href=\"Effigy%20Shield\"&gt;Effigy Shield&lt;/a&gt; for the highest &lt;a href=\"fire%20defense\"&gt;fire defense&lt;/a&gt; of any small shield and has light deflection.\nResistance Defense.\nAlong with &lt;a href=\"Physical\"&gt;Physical&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Elemental\"&gt;Elemental&lt;/a&gt; damage reduction, weapons also have hidden stats that reduce the amount of status build-up while blocking.\nUpgrades.\nRequires: Crystal Ring Shield +0, 5000 Souls and &lt;a href=\"Demon%20Titanite\"&gt;Demon Titanite&lt;/a&gt;"}
{"id": "130202", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=130202", "title": "Crystal Sage", "text": "The Crystal Sage is a &lt;a href=\"Boss%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;boss&lt;/a&gt; and later a &lt;a href=\"Boss%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29%23Minibosses\"&gt;miniboss&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nDescription.\nBoth Sages are towering figures that have billowing, long robes that obscure most of their bodies. True to their pedigree, they wear enormous hats that obscure their faces, though they also wear bone masks that look like beaks, with glass-eyed lenses. Instead of sorcery staves, they utilize crystal spheres as catalysts (likely used similarly to crystal balls). The &lt;a href=\"Abyss%20Watchers\"&gt;Legion&lt;/a&gt;'s Sage uses a floral lavender sphere, while the &lt;a href=\"Grand%20Archives\"&gt;Archives&lt;/a&gt;' Sage uses a bluish white sphere. They also wield &lt;a href=\"Crystal%20Sage%27s%20Rapier\"&gt;rapiers&lt;/a&gt; for defense.\nLocations.\n&lt;a href=\"Road%20of%20Sacrifices\"&gt;Road of Sacrifices&lt;/a&gt;\n&lt;a href=\"Grand%20Archives\"&gt;Grand Archives&lt;/a&gt; \nLore.\nThe two scholars are spiritual successors of the legendary &lt;a href=\"Big%20Hat%20Logan\"&gt;grand sage Logan&lt;/a&gt;, wearing &lt;a href=\"Sage%27s%20Big%20Hat\"&gt;hats similar to that of the legendary sorcerer&lt;/a&gt; as a symbol of their pedigree, and possessed a &lt;a href=\"Crystal%20Scroll\"&gt;scroll&lt;/a&gt; containing the sorceries and research of &lt;a href=\"Seath\"&gt;Seath&lt;/a&gt; which lead to Logan's records of Crystal Sorcery,\n, a branch of sorcery that the two sages had carried on allowing them to replicate Logan's sorceries that utilize the power of crystals to their fullest as a medium for souls.\nAt some point the &lt;a href=\"Crystal%20Sage\"&gt;Crystal Sage&lt;/a&gt;s reached Lothric and became the spiritual guides of the scholars of the Grand Archives. The Crystal Sages introduced to Lothric not only &lt;a href=\"Crystal%20Gem\"&gt;crystal gems&lt;/a&gt; but also the heretical belief in the pale dragon Seath and his mad knowledge. The sages would thus continue to work on their research within the Grand Archives, even taking &lt;a href=\"Daughter%20of%20Crystal%20Kriemhild\"&gt;Daughter of Crystal Kriemhild&lt;/a&gt; as their pupil and crafting &lt;a href=\"Crystal%20Sage%27s%20Rapier\"&gt;weapons&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Sage%27s%20Crystal%20Staff\"&gt;casting tools&lt;/a&gt; that used the power of crystals to enhance their magical power, representing how the fruits of the lifetime of research had advanced to an impressive level.\nEventually, in a pact of uncertain terms, one of the Sages joined the &lt;a href=\"Abyss%20Watchers\"&gt;Undead Legion of Farron&lt;/a&gt; to teach them sorceries. As the Legion believed in speed over power, the Crystal Sage created spells that were practical and could be used relatively faster than other sorceries, but required and encouraged the development of specific talent. The daughter of the Legion's lead acolyte, a xanthous scholar named &lt;a href=\"Yellowfinger%20Heysel\"&gt;Heysel&lt;/a&gt;, appeared to have had some of her own sorceries tailored in such a way.\nStrategy.\nThe Crystal Sage spends the first half of the fight teleporting and casting spells. Its spells include Homing Soul Arrow, Heavy Soul Arrow, a homing crystal ball, a rapid fire soul dart, and a mortar-style bombardment. Once down to half health, the Sage will spawn clones each time it teleports. These clones seem to cast the same spells. The clones disappear upon taking any damage and damaging them does not affect the boss' health bar. To tell the clones apart from the boss look at the color of their spells, spells cast by the clones are blue in color whereas those cast by the boss are purple. It is not advisable to block any of the spells, as the stamina drain is large.\nFor melee players, running up to the sage and hitting rapidly is a good strategy. This should interrupt any spells and cause the Sage to teleport. Once the Sage gets to half health and clones, you must either take out the clones very quickly or identify the real Sage to deal damage. The clones only take a single hit to dispatch.\nIt is advisable for melee players to pack &lt;a href=\"Throwing%20Knife%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;throwing knives&lt;/a&gt;, as the clones can be quickly dispatched with single knives. The Crystal Sage is also highly susceptible to &lt;a href=\"Bleed%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;bleed&lt;/a&gt; damage.\nIt is possible to stagger the sage by using a large weapon (e.g.: ultra greatswords) to stun-lock and take them out before they enters the second phase.\nIt is also possible to use poison or toxic against him. Usually the &lt;a href=\"Storyteller%27s%20Staff\"&gt;Storyteller's Staff&lt;/a&gt; can do the job easily. Simply Use the weapon art, toxic the boss and go sit at the top of the little hill at the right of the arena. Slow way to kill the boss but surely a safe approach on higher NG or when melee is a tricky approach.\nAs the Crystal Sage is vulnerable to &lt;a href=\"Parry%20and%20Riposte%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;parries&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Sacred%20Flame\"&gt;Sacred Flame&lt;/a&gt; can be used to immediately interrupt its movements. This can be particularly useful for interrupting the Sage's teleporting attempts.\nSummons.\n&lt;a href=\"Eygon%20of%20Carim\"&gt;Eygon of Carim&lt;/a&gt;: If the player speaks to Eygon in the &lt;a href=\"Undead%20Settlement\"&gt;Undead Settlement&lt;/a&gt; after rescuing &lt;a href=\"Irina%20of%20Carim\"&gt;Irina of Carim&lt;/a&gt;, he can be summoned for this fight. In the pillar chamber leading to the arena, his summon sign can be found behind the third pillar on the left."}
{"id": "131203", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=131203", "title": "Crystal Sage's Rapier", "text": "The Crystal Sage's Rapier is a &lt;a href=\"Boss%20Soul%20Items%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;soul-transposed&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Thrusting%20Swords%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;thrusting sword&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nObtained by transposing the &lt;a href=\"Soul%20of%20a%20Crystal%20Sage\"&gt;Soul of a Crystal Sage&lt;/a&gt; with &lt;a href=\"Ludleth%20of%20Courland\"&gt;Ludleth of Courland&lt;/a&gt;.\nCharacteristics.\nThe Crystal Sage's Rapier is an unorthodox thrusting sword that has moderate &lt;a href=\"Dexterity%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Dexterity&lt;/a&gt; requirements but scales almost entirely with &lt;a href=\"Intelligence%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Intelligence&lt;/a&gt;, making it ideal for mage builds. It is the longest thrusting sword in the game, providing its wielder with good reach. However, because it deals little &lt;a href=\"physical\"&gt;physical&lt;/a&gt; damage, it is largely incapable of taking advantage of the &lt;a href=\"Thrust%20%28damage%20type%29\"&gt;Thrust&lt;/a&gt; damage that is the signature of thrusting swords, and thus cannot greatly benefit from counter-hits or from equipping a &lt;a href=\"Leo%20Ring%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Leo Ring&lt;/a&gt;.\nOne quirk of the Crystal Sage's Rapier is that equipping it will increase the wielder's &lt;a href=\"Item%20Discovery%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Item Discovery&lt;/a&gt; by 50 points. Thus it sees common use as a farming aid, improving the odds of getting desired loot through enemy drops."}
{"id": "173175", "revid": "5064773", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=173175", "title": "Crystal Sage (bonfire)", "text": ""}
{"id": "133982", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=133982", "title": "Crystal Scroll", "text": "The Crystal Scroll (\u7d50\u6676\u306e\u30b9\u30af\u30ed\u30fc\u30eb) is a in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\". It is required to learn crystal &lt;a href=\"Sorcery%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;sorceries&lt;/a&gt;.\nAvailability.\nDropped by the &lt;a href=\"Crystal%20Sage\"&gt;Crystal Sage&lt;/a&gt; found in the &lt;a href=\"Grand%20Archives\"&gt;Grand Archives&lt;/a&gt;.\nUsage.\nGive to &lt;a href=\"Orbeck%20of%20Vinheim\"&gt;Orbeck of Vinheim&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Firelink%20Shrine%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Firelink Shrine&lt;/a&gt; to upgrade his stock of &lt;a href=\"Sorcery%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;sorceries&lt;/a&gt;:\nDescription.\n&lt;tabber&gt;Official translation=\n&lt;/tabber&gt;"}
{"id": "6088", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=6088", "title": "Crystal Shield", "text": "The Crystal Shield is a &lt;a href=\"medium%20shield\"&gt;medium shield&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nThe Crystal Shield can be purchased in unlimited amounts from &lt;a href=\"Domhnall%20of%20Zena\"&gt;Domhnall of Zena&lt;/a&gt; for 4,000 &lt;a href=\"Soul%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;souls&lt;/a&gt;. He is first found in the sewers area of the &lt;a href=\"Depths\"&gt;Depths&lt;/a&gt;, and after slaying the &lt;a href=\"Gaping%20Dragon\"&gt;Gaping Dragon&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0or ringing both bells of awakening,\u00a0he will relocate to &lt;a href=\"Firelink%20Shrine\"&gt;Firelink Shrine&lt;/a&gt; on the bridge next to the corpse where the &lt;a href=\"Ring%20of%20Sacrifice\"&gt;Ring of Sacrifice&lt;/a&gt; is found.\nCharacteristics.\nThe Crystal Shield has light deflection and a bash instead of a &lt;a href=\"parry\"&gt;parry&lt;/a&gt;. It is one of three &lt;a href=\"standard%20shields\"&gt;standard shields&lt;/a&gt; that cannot parry, the other two being the &lt;a href=\"Pierce%20Shield\"&gt;Pierce Shield&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Spiked%20Shield\"&gt;Spiked Shield&lt;/a&gt;.\nUnlike most \"&lt;a href=\"Crystal%20%28upgrade%20path%29\"&gt;crystal&lt;/a&gt;\" weapons, the Crystal Shield's &lt;a href=\"durability\"&gt;durability&lt;/a&gt; is quite high; even though it cannot be repaired, it will not break for a long time. It is very effective in defending against &lt;a href=\"elemental\"&gt;elemental&lt;/a&gt; attacks, including one of the highest &lt;a href=\"Lightning%20defense\"&gt;Lightning defense&lt;/a&gt;s of any &lt;a href=\"shield\"&gt;shield&lt;/a&gt;, but its &lt;a href=\"Stability\"&gt;Stability&lt;/a&gt; is outclassed by almost any &lt;a href=\"Weapon%20Modification\"&gt;upgraded&lt;/a&gt; metal shield, with a set 60 &lt;a href=\"stability\"&gt;stability&lt;/a&gt; that cannot be boosted.\nResistance defense.\nAlong with &lt;a href=\"Physical\"&gt;Physical&lt;/a&gt; and Elemental damage reduction, weapons also have hidden stats that reduce the amount of status &lt;a href=\"build-up\"&gt;build-up&lt;/a&gt; while blocking.\nUpgrades.\nCannot be upgraded."}
{"id": "161064", "revid": "5064773", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=161064", "title": "Crystal Soul Spear", "text": ""}
{"id": "4514", "revid": "357119", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4514", "title": "Crystal Soul Spear (Dark Souls)", "text": "Crystal Soul Spear (\u30bd\u30a6\u30eb\u306e\u7d50\u6676\u69cd) is a &lt;a href=\"Sorcery%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;Sorcery&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\".\nGeneral information.\nCrystal Soul Spear has the same number of casts and takes up the same number of &lt;a href=\"Attunement%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;Attunement&lt;/a&gt; slots as the regular &lt;a href=\"Soul%20Spear%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;Soul Spear&lt;/a&gt;, while being significantly more powerful, has a magic attack power of 3.6 times the catalyst's magic adjust. The downside is that it can only be obtained once per playthrough, instead of two, and requires 8 more &lt;a href=\"Intelligence%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;Intelligence&lt;/a&gt; than the regular Soul Spear.\nAs with most projectile sorceries, Crystal Soul Spear also has limited homing abilities and will often hit enemies even if they attempt to dodge it. As with the regular Soul Spear, it can pierce through enemies and deal damage to multiple targets in a straight line until the projectile eventually hits the ground or some other obstacle.\nDescription.\n&lt;tabber&gt;Official translation=\n&lt;/tabber&gt;"}
{"id": "60574", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=60574", "title": "Crystal Soul Spear (Dark Souls II)", "text": "Crystal Soul Spear is a &lt;a href=\"Sorcery%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;sorcery&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nReceived by trading the &lt;a href=\"Old%20Paledrake%20Soul\"&gt;Old Paledrake Soul&lt;/a&gt; and 10,000 &lt;a href=\"Souls%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;souls&lt;/a&gt; with &lt;a href=\"Straid%20of%20Olaphis\"&gt;Straid of Olaphis&lt;/a&gt;.\nGeneral information.\nA stronger form of &lt;a href=\"Soul%20Spear%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Soul Spear&lt;/a&gt;, this spell shoots forward in a relatively quick cast, doing massive damage to any enemies caught in its path. Unlike Soul Spear, this sorcery requires 2 &lt;a href=\"Attunement%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;attunement&lt;/a&gt; slots, as well as a high amount of &lt;a href=\"Intelligence%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Intelligence&lt;/a&gt;.\nHowever having 2 slots with &lt;a href=\"Soul%20Spear%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Soul Spear&lt;/a&gt; is more effective as Crystal Soul Spear is about 30% stronger than the original.\nInterestingly, it also consumes less stamina per cast than its normal, non-crystallized variant.\nAttunement milestones.\nLike all other spells, the amount of casts per slot increases upon reaching certain &lt;a href=\"Attunement%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Attunement&lt;/a&gt; milestones:"}
{"id": "133928", "revid": "51254358", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=133928", "title": "Crystal Soul Spear (Dark Souls III)", "text": "Crystal Soul Spear (\u30bd\u30a6\u30eb\u306e\u7d50\u6676\u69cd) is a &lt;a href=\"Sorcery%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;sorcery&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nSold by &lt;a href=\"Orbeck%20of%20Vinheim\"&gt;Orbeck of Vinheim&lt;/a&gt; for 15,000 &lt;a href=\"Soul%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;souls&lt;/a&gt; once he has been given the &lt;a href=\"Crystal%20Scroll\"&gt;Crystal Scroll&lt;/a&gt;.\nEffect.\nAn enhanced version of &lt;a href=\"Soul%20Spear%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Soul Spear&lt;/a&gt;, and one of the most devastating Sorceries in the game. Fires a piercing crystal soul spear that can go through a line of enemies, inflicting 3.05 times the &lt;a href=\"Catalysts%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;catalyst's&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Buff\"&gt;Spell Buff&lt;/a&gt; as &lt;a href=\"Magic%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Magic&lt;/a&gt; damage upon any enemies struck. The spear has long range and fast travel speed, but requires a longer &lt;a href=\"cast%20time\"&gt;cast time&lt;/a&gt;.\nAlongside Soul Spear, this spell has the longest range among all Sorceries.\nUse.\nSingle player.\nCrystal Soul Spear is one of the most powerful burst-damage spells in the game, but also has the second-most expensive cost in &lt;a href=\"Focus%20Points\"&gt;FP&lt;/a&gt; of all offensive spells, beat only by &lt;a href=\"Soul%20Stream\"&gt;Soul Stream&lt;/a&gt;. It shares many characteristics with Soul Spear, but grants the caster more damage output at the cost of a longer cast time.\nOnline gameplay.\nOn a fully optimized build, a single cast of Crystal Soul Spear is capable of shaving off more than half of the HP bar of another player of equal Soul Level, provided that no defensive buffs like &lt;a href=\"Blue%20Bug%20Pellet\"&gt;Blue Bug Pellet&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Great%20Magic%20Barrier%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;(Great)&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Magic%20Barrier%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Magic Barrier&lt;/a&gt; are active. This means that, under the most optimal circumstances, it is possible to kill an opponent in just two casts, or even one if they have low &lt;a href=\"Vigor%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Vigor&lt;/a&gt;. However, the spell's long casting time means that it is very difficult to hit a target that can see it coming, and as such it is only recommended to use this spell when targeting a distracted player (such as during &lt;a href=\"Dark%20Spirit%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;invasions&lt;/a&gt;) or to combine it with &lt;a href=\"Homing%20Soulmass%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Homing Soulmass&lt;/a&gt; as a &lt;a href=\"roll\"&gt;roll&lt;/a&gt;-catching mechanism.\nDescription.\n&lt;tabber&gt;Official translation=\n&lt;/tabber&gt;"}
{"id": "3348", "revid": "56333033", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3348", "title": "Crystal Straight Sword", "text": "The Crystal Straight Sword is a &lt;a href=\"Straight%20Swords%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;straight sword&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\".\nCharacteristics.\nThe Crystal Straight Sword's high base damage means that at the point where it first can be bought, it will be quite powerful and effective in both the &lt;a href=\"Depths\"&gt;Depths&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Blighttown\"&gt;Blighttown&lt;/a&gt;, being about equal to a &lt;a href=\"Longsword\"&gt;Longsword&lt;/a&gt; +8 in terms of attack power and &lt;a href=\"moveset\"&gt;moveset&lt;/a&gt;. However, it can't be &lt;a href=\"Weapon%20Modification\"&gt;upgraded&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"repair\"&gt;repair&lt;/a&gt;ed, making it unsuitable for sustained use or high level play. Though it cannot be upgraded it does still have physical damage scaling. "}
