{"id": "134865", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=134865", "title": "Curse Ward Greatshield", "text": "The Curse Ward Greatshield is a &lt;a href=\"Greatshields%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;greatshield&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nFound in the &lt;a href=\"Cathedral%20of%20the%20Deep\"&gt;Cathedral of the Deep&lt;/a&gt;, on a corpse lying in the mausoleum located in front of the pair of large doors at the end of the graveyard on the upper level, and above the shortcut ladder that leads down to the stream with the &lt;a href=\"Corpse%20Grub\"&gt;Corpse Grub&lt;/a&gt;s.\nCharacteristics.\nThe Curse Ward Greatshield is a fairly standard greatshield that boasts respectable all-around elemental resistance. It is also the first available greatshield with 100% physical damage block that does not drop randomly from enemies, meaning that it can be obtained without farming.\nTrue to its name, the Curse Ward Greatshield is adept at deflecting &lt;a href=\"Dark%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Dark&lt;/a&gt; damage, and is equally resistant against &lt;a href=\"Magic%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Magic&lt;/a&gt; damage as well. However, its weight to stability ratio is inferior to other greatshields that also provide complete defense against physical damage, and in particular its stability does not improve appreciably when upgraded. This makes the Curse Ward Greatshield a good all-around shield for defending against physical and elemental damage, though inferior when put against more specialized greatshields that have higher individual resistances or increased stability-to-weight ratios.\nThe best property of this shield is that it is one of the few greatshields to allow use of the main hand weapon's &lt;a href=\"skill\"&gt;skill&lt;/a&gt;. It is also one of only two greatshields to have such a trait and also block 100% of physical damage, the other being the &lt;a href=\"Wolf%20Knight%27s%20Greatshield\"&gt;Wolf Knight's Greatshield&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "8081", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=8081", "title": "Dingy Robe", "text": "&lt;onlyinclude&gt;&lt;/onlyinclude&gt;\nThe Dingy Robe is a &lt;a href=\"chest%20armor\"&gt;chest armor&lt;/a&gt; piece in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\". It is part of the &lt;a href=\"Dingy%20Set\"&gt;Dingy Set&lt;/a&gt;.\nAvailability.\nFound in &lt;a href=\"Anastacia%20of%20Astora\"&gt;Anastacia of Astora&lt;/a&gt;'s cage after she is killed by &lt;a href=\"Knight%20Lautrec%20of%20Carim\"&gt;Lautrec&lt;/a&gt;.\nCharacteristics.\nThe Dingy Robe has the highest &lt;a href=\"Magic%20Defense\"&gt;Magic&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Lightning%20Defense\"&gt;Lightning&lt;/a&gt; defenses of any chest piece when &lt;a href=\"Armor%20Modification\"&gt;fully upgraded&lt;/a&gt;. It also has high &lt;a href=\"Curse%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;Curse&lt;/a&gt; resistance, even when non-upgraded, and decent &lt;a href=\"Bleed%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;Bleed&lt;/a&gt;/&lt;a href=\"Poison%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;Poison&lt;/a&gt; resistances. While its &lt;a href=\"physical%20defense\"&gt;physical defense&lt;/a&gt;s are mediocre, they are decent for its &lt;a href=\"weight\"&gt;weight&lt;/a&gt; when upgraded, and the piece is unusually more effective against &lt;a href=\"Strike\"&gt;Strike&lt;/a&gt;-type attacks when compared to its other physical defense stats.\nUpgrades.\nRequires 200 &lt;a href=\"Soul%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;souls&lt;/a&gt; per upgrade.\n&lt;onlyinclude&gt;&lt;/onlyinclude&gt;"}
{"id": "67529", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=67529", "title": "Dingy Robe (Dark Souls II)", "text": "The Dingy Robe is a in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\". It is part of the &lt;a href=\"Dingy%20Set%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Dingy Set&lt;/a&gt;.\nAvailability.\nThe set can be acquired from a &lt;a href=\"Dark%20Spirit\"&gt;dark spirit&lt;/a&gt; at the bottom of the &lt;a href=\"Grave%20of%20Saints\"&gt;Grave of Saints&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"New%20Game%20Plus%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;NG+&lt;/a&gt;. They will not appear with the use of a\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Bonfire%20Ascetic\"&gt;Bonfire Ascetic&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe red phantom that drops the set is in the same location where &lt;a href=\"Great%20Heal%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Great Heal&lt;/a&gt; is found.\nThe set will be +5 when acquired. The stats shown in the armor box are those the set possesses at +5."}
{"id": "8079", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=8079", "title": "Dingy Set", "text": "The Dingy Set is a &lt;a href=\"Light%20Armor%20Sets%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;light armor set&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nFound in &lt;a href=\"Anastacia%20of%20Astora\"&gt;Anastacia of Astora&lt;/a&gt;'s cell after she is killed by &lt;a href=\"Lautrec\"&gt;Lautrec&lt;/a&gt;.\nPlot.\nWorn by Anastacia of Astora. The skirt's description hints that she may have been wounded in the legs to prevent her from escaping her duties.\nCharacteristics.\nThis set offers little &lt;a href=\"physical%20defense\"&gt;physical defense&lt;/a&gt;s and no &lt;a href=\"Poise%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;Poise&lt;/a&gt;, but it is light &lt;a href=\"weight\"&gt;weight&lt;/a&gt; and has high &lt;a href=\"Curse%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;Curse&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Bleed%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;Bleed&lt;/a&gt; Resistances. When fully upgraded it possesses the highest &lt;a href=\"Magic%20%28damage%20type%29\"&gt;Magic&lt;/a&gt; Defense and &lt;a href=\"Lightning%20%28damage%20type%29\"&gt;Lightning&lt;/a&gt; Defense of any &lt;a href=\"armor%20set\"&gt;armor set&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe chest piece is the only known chest piece to not roll up its sleeves when it uses the \"Dingy Gloves\" for obvious reasons, but also to have its sleeves rolled up through use of the &lt;a href=\"Leather%20Gloves\"&gt;Leather Gloves&lt;/a&gt; (tested on female)."}
{"id": "67508", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=67508", "title": "Dingy Set (Dark Souls II)", "text": "The Dingy Set is a &lt;a href=\"Light%20Armor%20Sets%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;light armor set&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nThe set can be acquired from a red phantom at the bottom of the &lt;a href=\"Grave%20of%20Saints\"&gt;Grave of Saints&lt;/a&gt; in NG+. They will not appear with the use of a\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Bonfire%20Ascetic\"&gt;Bonfire Ascetic&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe red phantom that drops the set is in the same location where you find the &lt;a href=\"Great%20Heal%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Great Heal&lt;/a&gt; miracle.\nCharacteristics.\nWhile providing decent overall &lt;a href=\"physical\"&gt;physical&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"elemental\"&gt;elemental&lt;/a&gt; defenses, as well as moderate &lt;a href=\"Poison%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Poison&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Bleed%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Bleed&lt;/a&gt; resistance, for its &lt;a href=\"weight\"&gt;weight&lt;/a&gt;, the Dingy Set truly shines in its &lt;a href=\"Curse%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Curse&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Petrification%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Petrification&lt;/a&gt; Resistance.\nBoth the Robes and Skirt will grant the highest amount of Petrification Res. in the game, while being about the second best for Curse Res., the Hood and Cuffs are not the best in their category, but they are above most others.\nCheck the notes on how to attain both Curse and Petrification immunity."}
