{"id": "16829", "revid": "5064773", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=16829", "title": "Dragon (upgrade path)", "text": "Dragon is an &lt;a href=\"upgrade%20path\"&gt;upgrade path&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;.\"\nAvailability.\n&lt;a href=\"Dragon%20Weapons\"&gt;Dragon&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Weapons%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;weapons&lt;/a&gt; can be &lt;a href=\"Weapon%20Modification\"&gt;upgraded&lt;/a&gt; by any\u00a0&lt;a href=\"blacksmith\"&gt;blacksmith&lt;/a&gt; with the required materials, these being\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Dragon%20Scale\"&gt;Dragon Scale&lt;/a&gt;s and\u00a0&lt;a href=\"souls\"&gt;souls&lt;/a&gt;.\nGeneral information.\nDragon weapons may be upgraded to +5, increasing the weapon's damage with every upgrade. On half of these weapons, it will only increase the base damage, as some do not &lt;a href=\"Scaling\"&gt;scale&lt;/a&gt; with any stats.\u00a0The Dragon weapons that have scaling are the &lt;a href=\"Dragon%20Bone%20Fist\"&gt;Dragon Bone Fist&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Dragon%20Tooth\"&gt;Dragon Tooth&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Moonlight%20Greatsword%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;Moonlight Greatsword&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Priscilla%27s%20Dagger\"&gt;Priscilla's Dagger&lt;/a&gt;.\nFour of the dragon weapons can be &lt;a href=\"Weapon%20Augmentation\"&gt;augmented&lt;/a&gt;.\u00a0These are the &lt;a href=\"Dragon%20Bone%20Fist\"&gt;Dragon Bone Fist&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Dragon%20King%20Greataxe\"&gt;Dragon King Greataxe&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Dragon%20Tooth\"&gt;Dragon Tooth&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Obsidian%20Greatsword\"&gt;Obsidian Greatsword&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "73051", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=73051", "title": "Dragon Acolyte", "text": "Dragon Acolytes are &lt;a href=\"Enemies%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;enemies&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAppearance.\nDragon Acolytes were responsible for assisting &lt;a href=\"Aldia%2C%20Scholar%20of%20the%20First%20Sin\"&gt;Aldia, Scholar of the First Sin&lt;/a&gt; in the mysterious rituals and experiments conducted at his manor. The goal of this highly secret research is unknown, however it is rumored that the Acolytes were unknowingly manipulated by a mysterious force that led to the creation of the hideous creatures that now roam the manor.\nAcolytes wear bloodied robes and wield ceremonial hammers that can inflict &lt;a href=\"magic%20damage\"&gt;magic damage&lt;/a&gt;.\nStrategy.\nDragon Acolytes have low &lt;a href=\"Poise%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;poise&lt;/a&gt; and can be easily slain if the player attacks aggressively. However their hammer swings inflict a lot of damage and will kill the player very quickly if they are not blocked or evaded. Acolytes will toss magic urns at a distance and will heal with &lt;a href=\"lifegem\"&gt;lifegem&lt;/a&gt;s if they are injured.\nDue to their small stature, Acolytes often hide behind doors or even paintings. It is advisable to move slowly through the manor to avoid them sneaking up on the player."}
