{"id": "6082", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=6082", "title": "Dragon Crest Shield", "text": "The Dragon Crest Shield is a &lt;a href=\"medium%20shield\"&gt;medium shield&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nThe Dragon Crest Shield is found on a corpse in the &lt;a href=\"Valley%20of%20Drakes\"&gt;Valley of Drakes&lt;/a&gt;. It is on a narrow cliff in front of a passive &lt;a href=\"Undead%20Dragon\"&gt;Undead Dragon&lt;/a&gt;, alongside &lt;a href=\"Astora%27s%20Straight%20Sword\"&gt;Astora's Straight Sword&lt;/a&gt; and a nearby &lt;a href=\"Soul%20of%20a%20Proud%20Knight\"&gt;Soul of a Proud Knight&lt;/a&gt;. While it is possible to loot the other items without awakening the dragon, the shield is in an area where it will become aggressive.\nTo acquire it without fighting the Undead Dragon, quickly make a break for the shield, loot it, and immediately flee. With a well-timed &lt;a href=\"roll\"&gt;roll&lt;/a&gt; it is possible to escape with the shield unscathed.\nCharacteristics.\nThe Dragon Crest Shield has the third best &lt;a href=\"fire%20resistance\"&gt;fire resistance&lt;/a&gt; (the first being the &lt;a href=\"Black%20Knight%20Shield\"&gt;Black Knight Shield&lt;/a&gt; and the second being the &lt;a href=\"Black%20Iron%20Greatshield\"&gt;Black Iron Greatshield&lt;/a&gt;) of any shield in the game. This shield can be quickly acquired by beginners if they chose the &lt;a href=\"Master%20Key\"&gt;Master Key&lt;/a&gt; as their starting gift, potentially making the bosses &lt;a href=\"Bell%20Gargoyles\"&gt;Bell Gargoyles&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Chaos%20Witch%20Quelaag\"&gt;Chaos Witch Quelaag&lt;/a&gt; significantly easier. It has medium deflection and normal &lt;a href=\"parry\"&gt;parry&lt;/a&gt; speed.\nResistance defense.\nAlong with &lt;a href=\"Physical\"&gt;Physical&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Elemental\"&gt;Elemental&lt;/a&gt; damage reduction, weapons also have hidden stats that reduce the amount of status &lt;a href=\"build-up\"&gt;build-up&lt;/a&gt; while blocking.\nUpgrades.\nRequires: Dragon Crest Shield +0, 2000 &lt;a href=\"Souls\"&gt;Souls&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Twinkling%20Titanite\"&gt;Twinkling Titanite&lt;/a&gt;"}
{"id": "134850", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=134850", "title": "Dragon Crest Shield (Dark Souls III)", "text": "The Dragon Crest Shield is a &lt;a href=\"Medium%20Shields%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;medium shield&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nFound in &lt;a href=\"Farron%20Keep\"&gt;Farron Keep&lt;/a&gt;. On the bridge above the &lt;a href=\"Farron%20Keep%23Bonfires\"&gt;Old Wolf of Farron&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Bonfire%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;bonfire&lt;/a&gt;, turn right and head towards the closed gate, then drop off the destroyed railing to the right. Navigate the platforms to reach the other side, the shield will be found on a corpse near the dead wyvern, amongst scattered &lt;a href=\"Crystal%20Lizard%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Crystal Lizards&lt;/a&gt;.\nCharacteristics.\nOne of two returning crest shields from \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\" and one of the four enchanted blue shields in \"Dark Souls III\", the Dragon Crest Shield specializes in blocking &lt;a href=\"Fire%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Fire&lt;/a&gt; damage.\nWhile it serves as a good general-purpose medium shield due to its moderate weight and stability, all-round elemental defense and 100% physical damage block, it is generally outclassed by the &lt;a href=\"Black%20Knight%20Shield%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Black Knight Shield&lt;/a&gt;, which possesses significantly more stability while still having comparable Fire absorption. The only advantage that the Dragon Crest Shield holds over the Black Knight Shield is that it requires 4 less points in &lt;a href=\"Strength%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Strength&lt;/a&gt; to wield and weights 2.5 units less, making it useful for builds that do not invest heavily in Strength or &lt;a href=\"Vitality%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Vitality&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "7680", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=7680", "title": "Dragon Eye", "text": "The Dragon Eye is an in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nObtained after joining the &lt;a href=\"Path%20of%20the%20Dragon\"&gt;Path of the Dragon&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"covenants\"&gt;covenant&lt;/a&gt;.\nGeneral information.\nUsage of the Dragon Eye is limited to players who are members of the Path of the Dragon covenant.\nUsing the Dragon Eye causes the player's sign to appear in the worlds of other players, allowing them to summon the user to their world to duel. The player does not need to be in human form. However, the host must be in human form (reverse-&lt;a href=\"hollow\"&gt;hollow&lt;/a&gt;ed), but does not need to possess a &lt;a href=\"Dragon%20Scale\"&gt;Dragon Scale&lt;/a&gt; (contrary to the in-game description), and the area &lt;a href=\"boss\"&gt;boss&lt;/a&gt; does not need to be alive to interact with the summon sign; users of the dragon eye have no such restrictions as to where and when they can place their signs. Players can summon others that are within their soul level +/-(10+10%) of their level; for example, a level 100 player can be summoned by anyone between level 80 and 120.\nThe winner of the duel is granted a Dragon Scale and &lt;a href=\"souls\"&gt;souls&lt;/a&gt; proportional to the defeated player's soul level. In the event of a tie (where both players die), both players are awarded a Dragon Scale. Despite the nature of dragon dueling, the host may &lt;a href=\"indict\"&gt;indict&lt;/a&gt; the Dragon Eye user if they are defeated."}
{"id": "66873", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=66873", "title": "Dragon Eye (Dark Souls II)", "text": "The Dragon Eye is an in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nReceived upon joining the\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Dragon%20Remnants\"&gt;Dragon Remnants&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0covenant.\nDescription.\nWhen used, the player will kneel and place a dragon sign on the ground. This sign, similar to the\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Red%20Sign%20Soapstone%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Red Sign Soapstone&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0or the\u00a0&lt;a href=\"White%20Sign%20Soapstone%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;White Sign Soapstone&lt;/a&gt;, will be seen in other player's worlds. If activated, both players will duel, and the winner will gain a\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Dragon%20Scale%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Dragon Scale&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "5063", "revid": "56333033", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5063", "title": "Dragon Greatsword", "text": "The Dragon Greatsword is an &lt;a href=\"ultra%20greatsword\"&gt;ultra greatsword&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nObtained by cutting off the &lt;a href=\"Stone%20Dragon\"&gt;Stone Dragon&lt;/a&gt;'s tail in &lt;a href=\"Ash%20Lake\"&gt;Ash Lake&lt;/a&gt;. Doing so does not count as a betrayal to the &lt;a href=\"Path%20of%20the%20Dragon\"&gt;Path of the Dragon&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"covenant\"&gt;covenant&lt;/a&gt;,\u00a0as the Stone Dragon is invulnerable and will always remain passive. Players will need to deal 459 damage to the tail in order to cut it in the base game cycle. \nCharacteristics.\nGrants 20 points of\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Fire%20Defense\"&gt;fire&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0and\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Magic%20Defense\"&gt;magic&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0resistance when wielded.\u00a0Its two-handed strong attack is a ranged vertical cleave. Using this attack reduces &lt;a href=\"durability\"&gt;durability&lt;/a&gt; of the weapon by 50 per use.\nEven though this weapon doesn't have any scaling, it has the highest base damage of any weapon in the game. Because of this, the Dragon Greatsword can do comparable amounts of damage to other Ultra Greatswords, but is out-classed easily by &lt;a href=\"Demon%20Great%20Machete\"&gt;Demon Great Machete&lt;/a&gt;. This weapon is not &lt;a href=\"Weapon%20Augmentation\"&gt;Enchantable&lt;/a&gt;, and as such has less damage potential than other large weapons that are on the &lt;a href=\"Standard%20%28upgrade%20path%29\"&gt;Standard&lt;/a&gt; upgrade path. Its high 24 unit weight and its high Strength requirement make this weapon less than ideal for a normal playthrough. "}
