{"id": "6096", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=6096", "title": "Dragon Head Stone", "text": "The Dragon Head Stone is an in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nThe Dragon Head Stone is obtained by joining the &lt;a href=\"Path%20of%20the%20Dragon\"&gt;Path of the Dragon&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"covenant\"&gt;covenant&lt;/a&gt;.\nDescription.\nPlayers must not be wearing headgear in order to use the Dragon Head Stone. In addition, they must not be suffering the &lt;a href=\"egghead\"&gt;egghead&lt;/a&gt; status effect. Once used, the player's head takes on the appearance of a dragon. The effect is permanent until the player's &lt;a href=\"death\"&gt;death&lt;/a&gt;.\nPressing and holding the [USE] button while the stone is in the current belt slot (X for Xbox 360, Square for PS3) emits &lt;a href=\"Fire%20%28damage%20type%29\"&gt;fire&lt;/a&gt; breath at the cost of 50 &lt;a href=\"stamina\"&gt;stamina&lt;/a&gt; \"regen\" per second squared. The direction the stream of fire travels in is perpendicular to the player's body, rather than the direction their head is actually facing. This means that unlike other ranged attacks, when using lock-on, the player must continue to move to update their direction in order to hit moving targets. The base damage the fire breath deals per tick increases along with the player's rank in the &lt;a href=\"Path%20of%20the%20Dragon\"&gt;Path of the Dragon&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"covenant\"&gt;covenant&lt;/a&gt;\u2014120 at +0, 125 at +1, 130 at +2, and 140 at +3.\nUnlike most other covenant-related items, the Dragon Head Stone does not require membership of its parent &lt;a href=\"covenant\"&gt;covenant&lt;/a&gt; to use. Leaving the &lt;a href=\"Path%20of%20the%20Dragon\"&gt;Path of the Dragon&lt;/a&gt; covenant does not affect usage of the head stone in any way, though the player will lose any covenant rank-dependent benefits (the increased &lt;a href=\"Fire%20%28damage%20type%29\"&gt;fire&lt;/a&gt; damage from the head stone, as well as the increased buff power and roar range of the &lt;a href=\"Dragon%20Torso%20Stone\"&gt;Dragon Torso Stone&lt;/a&gt;)."}
{"id": "75266", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=75266", "title": "Dragon Head Stone (Dark Souls II)", "text": "The Dragon Head Stone is an offensive item in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nGiven by &lt;a href=\"Magerold%20of%20Lanafir\"&gt;Magerold of Lanafir&lt;/a&gt; upon reaching Rank 1 in the &lt;a href=\"Dragon%20Remnants\"&gt;Dragon Remnants&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Covenant%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;covenant&lt;/a&gt;.\nUsage.\nThe Dragon Head Stone serves the same purpose as it did in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\"; the player is able to turn their head into that of a dragon and is granted the ability to breathe &lt;a href=\"Fire%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;fire&lt;/a&gt; from it. When equipped in an item slot, the player may use the item button to breathe fire. For however long the player holds the item button, they will breathe fire continuously, steadily decreasing &lt;a href=\"Endurance%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;stamina&lt;/a&gt;. Moving around in any direction will not cancel the fire breath and the player may aim the fire breath elsewhere."}
{"id": "131937", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=131937", "title": "Dragon Head Stone (Dark Souls III)", "text": "The Dragon Head Stone is an in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nObtained upon defeating the &lt;a href=\"Ancient%20Wyvern\"&gt;Ancient Wyvern&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Archdragon%20Peak\"&gt;Archdragon Peak&lt;/a&gt;.\nUsage.\nUpon activation, the player gains the head of a dragon and is able to breathe fire. This transformation is irreversible until &lt;a href=\"death\"&gt;death&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe absorption values for the head piece are as follows:\nPhysical absorption remains at 0%, and all flat defenses remain penalized for the empty armor slot."}
