{"id": "2497", "revid": "56333033", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=2497", "title": "Dragon King Greataxe", "text": "The Dragon King Greataxe is a &lt;a href=\"Greataxes\"&gt;greataxe&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nThe Dragon King Greataxe is obtained from cutting off the tail of the &lt;a href=\"Gaping%20Dragon\"&gt;Gaping Dragon&lt;/a&gt;, located in the lowest section of the &lt;a href=\"Depths\"&gt;Depths&lt;/a&gt;.\nCharacteristics.\nThe Dragon King Greataxe boasts impressive base damage but does not &lt;a href=\"Parameter%20Bonus\"&gt;scale&lt;/a&gt; with any &lt;a href=\"Stats%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;stat&lt;/a&gt;, has an excessively high strength requirement, and is quite heavy. This weapon will be out damaged easily but much lighter weapons that have good Strength scaling. Though players could perform one-shots with this weapon when built around appropriately, it boils down to a gimmick. \nWhen held with both hands, the Dragon King Greataxe can execute a special attack by using the strong-attack. The player slams the axe in the ground, creating a shockwave all around them. This special attack burns 50 &lt;a href=\"durability\"&gt;durability&lt;/a&gt; with each use and hits twice. Unusual for a unique weapon, the Dragon King Greataxe can be augmented and buffing this weapon adds damage to the AOE of the special 2H strong attack. It grants 20 points of fire and magic resistance when wielded."}
{"id": "69287", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=69287", "title": "Dragon Knight", "text": "Dragon Knights are in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nDescription.\nDragon Knights are found defending the &lt;a href=\"Ancient%20Dragon\"&gt;Ancient Dragon&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"Dragon%20Shrine\"&gt;Dragon Shrine&lt;/a&gt;. They don the golden version of the &lt;a href=\"Black%20Dragon%20Set\"&gt;Black Dragon Set&lt;/a&gt;.\nLore.\nThe Dragon Knights were a seclusive syndicate of warriors that donned armor inspired by the &lt;a href=\"Dragon\"&gt;Dragon&lt;/a&gt;s, who they held a great esteem towards. Some knights used the scales and tail of the \"Black Dragon,\" which might be the deceased &lt;a href=\"Black%20Dragon%20Kalameet\"&gt;Black Dragon Kalameet&lt;/a&gt;, to forge their armor and weapons.\nStrategy.\nThese foes can dual wield, though their attack speed isn't that impressive. They can perform guard breaks on the player and will take an &lt;a href=\"Estus%20Flask%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Estus&lt;/a&gt; when injured. The player can exploit their distance by using ranged attacks such as &lt;a href=\"Poison%20Arrow%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Poison Arrows&lt;/a&gt;. Sweeping weapons with high &lt;a href=\"Poise%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29%23Poise%20Damage\"&gt;poise&lt;/a&gt; damage, such as the &lt;a href=\"Greatsword%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Greatsword&lt;/a&gt;, are also effective, allowing the player to stun-lock them with several strikes before moving back, completely avoiding damage. Due to their large health pool, it's best to lure them out one at a time to avoid being overwhelmed.\nThey are very weak to &lt;a href=\"Lightning%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;lightning&lt;/a&gt; based miracles such as\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Lightning%20Spear%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Lightning Spear&lt;/a&gt;.\nScholar of the First Sin.\nIn \"\", a total of twenty-two Dragon Knights are found.\nAll but two Dragon Knights are passive, and will perform the &lt;a href=\"Gestures%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Duel Bow&lt;/a&gt; gesture upon seeing the player. Only Dragonfang Villard and the dual greatsword-wielding Dragon Knight are inherently aggressive. Neither will respawn after being defeated once.\nThe Dragon Knights will remain passive if the player defeats their accompanying challenger in solo combat (either the Drakekeeper, or the dual greatsword-wielder), allowing the player to pass unmolested. However, they will become hostile if the player attempts to run past them without defeating the challenger, or by attacking the Dragon Knights themselves (this also applies to beneficial spells like &lt;a href=\"Warmth\"&gt;Warmth&lt;/a&gt;). Only the Dragon Knights in the local area will become aggressive(e.g., each pair accompanying the Drakekeepers, or the entire group of eleven prior to the Ancient Dragon), previous or subsequent knights will not aggro on the player unless provoked."}
