{"id": "150642", "revid": "51254358", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=150642", "title": "Dragonhead Greatshield", "text": "The Dragonhead Greatshield (\u7adc\u9996\u306e\u5927\u76fe) is a &lt;a href=\"Greatshields%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;greatshield&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;: &lt;a href=\"The%20Ringed%20City\"&gt;The Ringed City&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nFound in &lt;a href=\"The%20Ringed%20City%20%28location%29\"&gt;The Ringed City&lt;/a&gt;. Located beneath the bridge where &lt;a href=\"Darkeater%20Midir\"&gt;Darkeater Midir&lt;/a&gt; is first encountered near the &lt;a href=\"The%20Ringed%20City%20%28location%29%23Bonfires\"&gt;Ringed City Streets&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Bonfire%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;bonfire&lt;/a&gt;. The shield is guarded by a &lt;a href=\"Ringed%20Knight\"&gt;Ringed Knight&lt;/a&gt;.\nCharacteristics.\nA very unique greatshield, the Dragonhead Greatshield boasts a set of characteristics that encourage its wielder to play offensively rather than passively.\nDespite being on the higher end of the weight scale among greatshields, it has very disappointing stability, beating only the &lt;a href=\"Ancient%20Dragon%20Greatshield\"&gt;Ancient Dragon Greatshield&lt;/a&gt; when fully upgraded. As well, being made from the head of an archdragon, it is exceedingly weak to &lt;a href=\"Lightning%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Lightning&lt;/a&gt;, and is only mediocre at warding off &lt;a href=\"Magic%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Magic&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Dark%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Dark&lt;/a&gt; damage. However, it boasts extremely high &lt;a href=\"Fire%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Fire&lt;/a&gt; absorption at a whopping 90%, beating even the &lt;a href=\"Black%20Iron%20Greatshield%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Black Iron Greatshield&lt;/a&gt; (83%) and &lt;a href=\"Black%20Knight%20Shield%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Black Knight Shield&lt;/a&gt; (85%).\nThe Dragonhead Greatshield's defining characteristic, however, is its &lt;a href=\"skill\"&gt;skill&lt;/a&gt;. Upon activating &lt;a href=\"Dragon%20Roar\"&gt;Dragon Roar&lt;/a&gt;, the player raises the greatshield and an afterimage from the shield will emit a roar. This will knock back any opponents and grant the wielder an effect similar to &lt;a href=\"Perseverance%20%28skill%29\"&gt;Perseverance&lt;/a&gt;. This grants many weapons that do not have &lt;a href=\"Hyper%20Armor\"&gt;Hyper Armor&lt;/a&gt; frames a much-needed advantage against heavier weapons by preventing staggering and reducing damage taken.\nMaking use of this greatshield and a weapon with thrust attacks, plus the &lt;a href=\"Leo%20Ring%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Leo Ring&lt;/a&gt;, is sure to deal great damage against players with slower weapons.\nDescription.\n&lt;tabber&gt;Official translation=\n&lt;/tabber&gt;"}
{"id": "150633", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=150633", "title": "Dragonhead Shield", "text": "The Dragonhead Shield is a &lt;a href=\"Small%20Shields%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;small shield&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;: &lt;a href=\"The%20Ringed%20City\"&gt;The Ringed City&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nFound in &lt;a href=\"The%20Ringed%20City%20%28location%29\"&gt;The Ringed City&lt;/a&gt;. Past the \"Show your humanity\" puzzle near the &lt;a href=\"Ringed%20City%20Streets\"&gt;Ringed City Streets&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Bonfire%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;bonfire&lt;/a&gt;, proceed past the &lt;a href=\"Judicator%20Giant\"&gt;Judicator Giant&lt;/a&gt; and two &lt;a href=\"Ringed%20Knight\"&gt;Ringed Knight&lt;/a&gt;s. After climbing down the ladder towards the &lt;a href=\"Purging%20Monument\"&gt;Purging Monument&lt;/a&gt;, make a hard right before the bridge to the monument, and follow the path to a dead end where the shield can be found.\nCharacteristics.\nDespite being classified as a shield, the Dragonhead Shield should be wielded as an offensive tool rather than a defensive one.\nDefensively, it has moderately high &lt;a href=\"Physical%20%28damage%20type%29\"&gt;Physical&lt;/a&gt; resistance, and extremely good &lt;a href=\"Fire%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Fire&lt;/a&gt; absorption that allows it to be used to block &lt;a href=\"Pyromancy%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Pyromancies&lt;/a&gt; quite reliably. However, owing to being fashioned from the head of an Archdragon, it is particularly vulnerable to &lt;a href=\"Lightning%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Lightning&lt;/a&gt; damage, and it weighs more than any other small shield in the game while lacking the stability of a proper shield.\nThe shield should instead be treated purely as an offensive off-hand weapon that deals &lt;a href=\"Fire%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Fire&lt;/a&gt; damage with its &lt;a href=\"skill\"&gt;skill&lt;/a&gt;, with the ability to hits opponents twice if they stand close enough. Because of its odd wielding requirements, this shield is best used in the hands of a Pyromancer build."}
