{"id": "44605", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=44605", "title": "Dragonrider Soul", "text": "The Dragonrider Soul is a &lt;a href=\"Boss%20Souls%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;boss soul&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nPlayers may receive a maximum of two Dragonrider Souls per playthrough, outside of the use of a &lt;a href=\"Bonfire%20Ascetic\"&gt;Bonfire Ascetic&lt;/a&gt;.\nUsage.\nConsume for 6,000 &lt;a href=\"Souls%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;souls&lt;/a&gt;, or &lt;a href=\"Boss%20Soul%20Items%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;trade&lt;/a&gt; with &lt;a href=\"Straid%20of%20Olaphis\"&gt;Straid of Olaphis&lt;/a&gt; for one of the following:"}
{"id": "47517", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=47517", "title": "Dragonrider Twinblade", "text": "The Dragonrider Twinblade\u00a0is a &lt;a href=\"Twinblades\"&gt;twinblade&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nThe Dragonrider Twinblade can be obtained from &lt;a href=\"Straid%20of%20Olaphis\"&gt;Straid of Olaphis&lt;/a&gt; by trading a &lt;a href=\"Dragonrider%20Soul\"&gt;Dragonrider Soul&lt;/a&gt; and 1,500 &lt;a href=\"Souls%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;souls&lt;/a&gt;.\nCharacteristics.\nWhile the &lt;a href=\"Stone%20Twinblade\"&gt;Stone Twinblade&lt;/a&gt; has a much higher &lt;a href=\"physical%20damage\"&gt;physical damage&lt;/a&gt; output due to not inflicting another damage type prior to &lt;a href=\"infusion\"&gt;infusion&lt;/a&gt;, this twinblade has some characteristics that would appeal to &lt;a href=\"Sorcery%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;mage&lt;/a&gt;-based builds. Its pseudo-low requirements (can be two-handed with 22 &lt;a href=\"Dexterity%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Dexterity&lt;/a&gt; and as little as 10 &lt;a href=\"Strength%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Strength&lt;/a&gt;), as well as respectable &lt;a href=\"Magic%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;magical&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Scaling%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;scaling&lt;/a&gt; bonus coupled with an appreciable amount of &lt;a href=\"Poise%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;poise&lt;/a&gt; damage, make it quite powerful in the right hands.\nMuch like the &lt;a href=\"Red%20Iron%20Twinblade\"&gt;Red Iron Twinblade&lt;/a&gt; and the Stone Twinblade, the Dragonrider Twinblade is one of the stronger twinblades obtainable in the game; the attribute scaling is unremarkable at first, but it later performs much better once it is fully-reinforced, especially with high investments in Dexterity and &lt;a href=\"Intelligence%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Intelligence&lt;/a&gt;. Infusing the Dragonrider Twinblade with a &lt;a href=\"faintstone\"&gt;faintstone&lt;/a&gt; is highly recommended, as this will allow mages to inflict more magic damage against ill-protected &lt;a href=\"Enemies%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;enemies&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe two fatal drawbacks of this weapon are the heavily spread out scaling, and its very high &lt;a href=\"weight\"&gt;weight&lt;/a&gt;, on par with some &lt;a href=\"Ultra%20Greatswords%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;ultra greatswords&lt;/a&gt;.\nIt upgrades with &lt;a href=\"Petrified%20Dragon%20Bone\"&gt;Petrified Dragon Bone&lt;/a&gt;s."}
