{"id": "131819", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=131819", "title": "Dragonslayer Greataxe", "text": "The Dragonslayer Greataxe is a &lt;a href=\"Boss%20Soul%20Items%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;soul-transposed&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Greataxes%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;greataxe&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nObtained by transposing the &lt;a href=\"Soul%20of%20Dragonslayer%20Armour\"&gt;Soul of Dragonslayer Armour&lt;/a&gt; with &lt;a href=\"Ludleth%20of%20Courland\"&gt;Ludleth of Courland&lt;/a&gt;.\nCharacteristics.\nA devastating weapon specifically designed for players who rely on sheer force, the Dragonslayer Greataxe primarily &lt;a href=\"Parameter%20Bonus%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;scales&lt;/a&gt; with &lt;a href=\"Strength%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Strength&lt;/a&gt;, requiring a heavy investment in this stat to be wielded effectively. It also comes natively imbued with &lt;a href=\"Lightning%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Lightning&lt;/a&gt; to provide the player with an &lt;a href=\"elemental\"&gt;elemental&lt;/a&gt; offensive alternative. However, the &lt;a href=\"Faith%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Faith&lt;/a&gt; scaling is relatively sub-par, so the weapon is still best utilized on pure Strength builds.\nThe Dragonslayer's Greataxe has very impressive damage output, making it a powerful weapon for felling normal enemies and &lt;a href=\"Boss%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;bosses&lt;/a&gt; alike. As a weapon in the greataxe class, it can deal significant &lt;a href=\"Poise%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Poise&lt;/a&gt; damage to foes, ensuring that any hit that does not kill will still have a high chance of &lt;a href=\"stagger\"&gt;stagger&lt;/a&gt;ing.\nIf this wasn't enough, the Dragonslayer Greataxe's unique &lt;a href=\"skill\"&gt;skill&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Falling%20Bolt%20%28Dragonslayer%20Greataxe%29\"&gt;Falling Bolt&lt;/a&gt;, is also one of the most destructive ones in the game. It focuses an immense amount of power into a single strike, capable of devastating any enemy it hits, while its wide impact radius also makes it strong for wiping out crowds."}
{"id": "5290", "revid": "56333033", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5290", "title": "Dragonslayer Greatbow", "text": "The Dragonslayer Greatbow is a &lt;a href=\"Bows\"&gt;bow&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nIn the hall before &lt;a href=\"Ornstein%20and%20Smough\"&gt;Ornstein and Smough&lt;/a&gt;, enter the broken glass window on the upper levels. The Dragonslayer Greatbow can be reached by &lt;a href=\"rolling\"&gt;rolling&lt;/a&gt; or jumping from the end of that path. Players can exit through a hole in the fence, leading to a location close to the &lt;a href=\"Giant%20Blacksmith\"&gt;Giant Blacksmith&lt;/a&gt;.\nCharacteristics.\nThe Dragonslayer Greatbow\u00a0requires deploying before it can shoot, meaning total starting lag (particularly for the first shot) is much longer than that of other bows; it has a longer draw time to boot. The Dragonslayer Greatbow requires a significant amount of &lt;a href=\"stamina\"&gt;stamina&lt;/a&gt; to shoot each arrow, too; at lower levels, it will deplete the entire stamina bar per shot, requiring a brief moment of rest between each shot. The Dragonslayer Greatbow may only use &lt;a href=\"Dragonslayer%20Arrow\"&gt;Dragonslayer Arrow&lt;/a&gt;s or &lt;a href=\"Gough%27s%20Great%20Arrow\"&gt;Gough's Great Arrow&lt;/a&gt;s.\nThe Dragonslayer Greatbow makes up for its deficiencies by being one of two bows with knockback while also having some of the highest damage per shot in the game, but will be outclassed by &lt;a href=\"Gough%27s%20Greatbow\"&gt;Gough's Greatbow&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "60549", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=60549", "title": "Dragonslayer Greatbow (Dark Souls II)", "text": "The Dragonslayer Greatbow is a &lt;a href=\"Greatbows\"&gt;greatbow&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nAcquired by trading the &lt;a href=\"Old%20King%20Soul\"&gt;Old King Soul&lt;/a&gt; and 10,000 &lt;a href=\"Souls%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;souls&lt;/a&gt; with &lt;a href=\"Weaponsmith%20Ornifex\"&gt;Weaponsmith Ornifex&lt;/a&gt;.\nCharacteristics.\nThe Dragonslayer Greatbow, at first, seems to be unremarkable for its &lt;a href=\"weight\"&gt;weight&lt;/a&gt; and lower base damage, when compared to the &lt;a href=\"Alonne%20Greatbow\"&gt;Alonne Greatbow&lt;/a&gt;. However, what makes the former outclass the latter greatbow is its improved &lt;a href=\"Strength%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Strength&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Scaling%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;scaling&lt;/a&gt;, as well as requiring more Strength instead of &lt;a href=\"Dexterity%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Dexterity&lt;/a&gt;, effectively making the Dragonslayer Greatbow a Strength-oriented greatbow. This greatbow also consumes a very large amount of &lt;a href=\"Stamina%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;stamina&lt;/a&gt; per shot, meaning most players may only get one effective shot fired before low stamina penalties begin to occur on the successive attacks.\nUnique only to this greatbow and its &lt;a href=\"Twin-headed%20Greatbow\"&gt;Lanafir cousin&lt;/a&gt; is that it has a stabilizing anchor on the bottom, meaning that one must anchor the bow in the ground before pulling back the string, thus making it fire at an incredibly slow rate. This can be mitigated if the player takes their time and avoids enemy engagement at close range, allowing them to effectively snipe enemies for high damage at longer ranges.\nIt requires &lt;a href=\"Petrified%20Dragon%20Bone\"&gt;Petrified Dragon Bone&lt;/a&gt;s in order to be upgraded, and the scaling does not change at maximum reinforcement."}
{"id": "130383", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=130383", "title": "Dragonslayer Greatbow (Dark Souls III)", "text": "The Dragonslayer Greatbow is a &lt;a href=\"Greatbows%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;greatbow&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nFound in &lt;a href=\"Irithyll%20of%20the%20Boreal%20Valley\"&gt;Irithyll of the Boreal Valley&lt;/a&gt;.\nCharacteristics.\nOne of two greatbows available to the player in the base game, the Dragonslayer Greatbow is a powerful quality-scaling weapon that can devastate distant targets when used properly.\nTrue to its description, the Dragonslayer Greatbow is large, heavy and cumbersome, requiring great amounts of &lt;a href=\"Strength%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Strength&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Dexterity%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Dexterity&lt;/a&gt; to wield properly. In order to fire, the wielder must first anchor the weapon into the ground and draw back the bow, completely immobilizing them for some time; additionally, it may only fire &lt;a href=\"Ammunition_%28Dark_Souls_III%29%23Greatarrows\"&gt;Greatarrows&lt;/a&gt;, and standard arrows will not suffice. However, once an arrow is loosed, it will inflict extreme damage on any enemy it hits, as well as knocking them down (provided that &lt;a href=\"Onislayer%20Greatarrow\"&gt;Onislayer Greatarrow&lt;/a&gt;s or &lt;a href=\"Millwood%20Greatarrow\"&gt;Millwood Greatarrow&lt;/a&gt;s are not used). As such, this weapon is designed to be used strategically, attacking foes from a distance where they cannot easily run down the wielder while they are vulnerable.\nCare should be taken when lining up repeated shots from the same position, as the recoil from each greatarrow will push the wielder backwards slightly. This means that it will be necessary to occasionally re-position to prevent terrain from obscuring subsequent shots.\nUpgrades.\n&lt;br&gt;"}
{"id": "131821", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=131821", "title": "Dragonslayer Greatshield", "text": "The Dragonslayer Greatshield is a &lt;a href=\"Boss%20Soul%20Items%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;soul-transposed&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Greatshields%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;greatshield&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nObtained by transposing the &lt;a href=\"Soul%20of%20Dragonslayer%20Armour\"&gt;Soul of Dragonslayer Armour&lt;/a&gt; with &lt;a href=\"Ludleth%20of%20Courland\"&gt;Ludleth of Courland&lt;/a&gt; at &lt;a href=\"Firelink%20Shrine%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Firelink Shrine&lt;/a&gt;.\nCharacteristics.\nThe Dragonslayer Greatshield is a sturdy and reliable greatshield with very high stability and strong all-around elemental defenses, being exceptionally good at warding off &lt;a href=\"Lightning%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Lightning&lt;/a&gt; damage. However, it is also the second-heaviest greatshield in the game, beaten only by &lt;a href=\"Havel%27s%20Greatshield%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Havel's Greatshield&lt;/a&gt;, and has a high &lt;a href=\"Strength%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Strength&lt;/a&gt; requirement, so players who wish to wield this greatshield will have to invest heavily in both Strength and &lt;a href=\"Vitality%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Vitality&lt;/a&gt;.\nAt the stage of the game that it's available, this shield can be particularly useful against foes that deal lightning damage, such as the &lt;a href=\"The%20Nameless%20King\"&gt;Nameless King&lt;/a&gt;; in particular, its high elemental defenses also allow it to reliably block the fire breath attacks of the King of the Storm in the first phase. As well, it can be a lifesaver against its own former wielder, the &lt;a href=\"Iron%20Dragonslayer\"&gt;Iron Dragonslayer&lt;/a&gt;.\nIts &lt;a href=\"skill\"&gt;skill&lt;/a&gt; is also very noteworthy in that it is not the same as the standard &lt;a href=\"Shield%20Bash\"&gt;Shield Bash&lt;/a&gt; that its ilk possess. Rather, it is capable of outright knocking down its target, rather than simply staggering them. This can be useful in many situations, and can create windows of opportunity that other Shield Bashes cannot.\nUpgrades.\n&lt;br&gt;"}
