{"id": "135184", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=135184", "title": "Dragonslayer Set", "text": "The Dragonslayer Set is a &lt;a href=\"Heavy%20Armor%20Sets%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;heavy armor set&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nFound on the far side of the courtyard below &lt;a href=\"The%20Nameless%20King\"&gt;The Nameless King&lt;/a&gt;'s arena, after defeating the Nameless King.\nCharacteristics.\nReturning from \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\", the set of armor formerly worn by &lt;a href=\"Dragon%20Slayer%20Ornstein\"&gt;Dragon Slayer Ornstein&lt;/a&gt; has a varied and strong line of defenses against most threats that the player can expect to face.\nDespite being on the lower end of heavy armor sets, Ornstein's set boasts strong physical defenses, being equally resistant to &lt;a href=\"Slash%20%28damage%20type%29\"&gt;Slash&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Thrust%20%28damage%20type%29\"&gt;Thrust&lt;/a&gt; damage; however, like most other plate metal armor sets, it has a weakness to &lt;a href=\"Strike%20%28damage%20type%29\"&gt;Strike&lt;/a&gt; damage. As protection worn by one who harnessed the power of lightning to slay fire-breathing dragons, its elemental defenses are also very sound, being equally resistant against &lt;a href=\"Fire%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Fire&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Lightning%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Lightning&lt;/a&gt; damage, though as armor worn by a servant to the divinity it is also particularly weak to &lt;a href=\"Dark%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Dark&lt;/a&gt; damage. Its resistance to &lt;a href=\"Negative%20Status%20Effects%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;status effects&lt;/a&gt; is very sound across the board, being particularly resistant to &lt;a href=\"Bleed%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Bleed&lt;/a&gt; buildup.\nAs with all other heavy armor sets, the Dragonslayer Set provides a strong &lt;a href=\"Poise%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;poise&lt;/a&gt;-to-weight ratio, though it should be noted that as &lt;a href=\"Dragonslayer%20Spear%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Ornstein's spear&lt;/a&gt; does not possess any &lt;a href=\"Hyper%20Armor\"&gt;Hyper Armor&lt;/a&gt; frames in \"Dark Souls III\", it is of little help except when wielding heavier weapons."}
{"id": "3929", "revid": "56333033", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3929", "title": "Dragonslayer Spear", "text": "The Dragonslayer Spear is a &lt;a href=\"Spears\"&gt;spear&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nThe Dragonslayer Spear is obtained by &lt;a href=\"Weapon%20Modification\"&gt;ascending&lt;/a&gt; any &lt;a href=\"Standard%20%28upgrade%20path%29\"&gt;Standard&lt;/a&gt; +10 &lt;a href=\"Spears\"&gt;spear&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"thrusting%20sword\"&gt;thrusting sword&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0at the\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Giant%20Blacksmith\"&gt;Giant Blacksmith&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Anor%20Londo\"&gt;Anor Londo&lt;/a&gt; with the &lt;a href=\"Soul%20of%20Ornstein\"&gt;Soul of Ornstein&lt;/a&gt; and 5,000 &lt;a href=\"souls\"&gt;souls&lt;/a&gt;.\nCharacteristics.\nUnlike other weapons that scale with Faith, the Dragonslayer Spear gains &lt;a href=\"Lightning%20%28damage%20type%29\"&gt;Lightning&lt;/a&gt; damage, not &lt;a href=\"Magic%20%28damage%20type%29\"&gt;Magic&lt;/a&gt; damage, from the Faith stat. It's also the only weapon in the game with scaling Lightning damage.\nThe special lightning bolt projectile is calculated like any attack using the weapon's Physical and Lightning AR and the attack specific Motion Values (100 Physical, 110 Lightning). It has a range of approximately 28 in-game units, suffers from damage drop off at long ranges and does not benefit from the Hawk Ring. This special attack degrades 20 Durability.\nAn easy way to obtain the Dragonslayer Spear is to downgrade the Lightning Spear dropped by the Mimic in Sen's Fortress to a +10 Spear, and then upgrading it to the Dragonslayer Spear. However, a +5 Dragonslayer Spear will not significantly outperform a +5 Lightning Spear at lower Faith levels (~16 or below) until the user well exceeds the required levels in Strength or Dexterity. A fully-upgraded &lt;a href=\"Demon%27s%20Spear\"&gt;Demon's Spear&lt;/a&gt; also has a higher overall damage rating at low Faith levels, and deals more Lightning damage at Faith levels of 42 and below. This weapon cannot be &lt;a href=\"Weapon%20Augmentation\"&gt;Enchanted&lt;/a&gt; and almost any buffable weapon of any class will out-perform this Spear in terms of damage potential. "}
{"id": "52556", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=52556", "title": "Dragonslayer Spear (Dark Souls II)", "text": "The Dragonslayer Spear is a &lt;a href=\"Spears%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;spear&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nTrade the &lt;a href=\"Old%20Dragonslayer%27s%20Soul\"&gt;Old Dragonslayer's Soul&lt;/a&gt;, along with 1,500 &lt;a href=\"Souls%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;souls&lt;/a&gt;, to &lt;a href=\"Weaponsmith%20Ornifex\"&gt;Weaponsmith Ornifex&lt;/a&gt;.\nCharacteristics.\nThis weapon, born of the soul of the &lt;a href=\"Old%20Dragonslayer\"&gt;Old Dragonslayer&lt;/a&gt;, is one of two spears that inflict &lt;a href=\"Lightning%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;lightning&lt;/a&gt; damage by default, the other being the &lt;a href=\"Heide%20Spear\"&gt;Heide Spear&lt;/a&gt;. This weapon, however, is able to fire bolts of lightning at the cost of &lt;a href=\"durability\"&gt;durability&lt;/a&gt;. It upgrades with\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Petrified%20Dragon%20Bone\"&gt;Petrified Dragon Bone&lt;/a&gt;s. It cannot be &lt;a href=\"infuse\"&gt;infuse&lt;/a&gt;d or buffed."}
{"id": "134327", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=134327", "title": "Dragonslayer Spear (Dark Souls III)", "text": "The Dragonslayer Spear is a &lt;a href=\"Spears%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;spear&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nFound in &lt;a href=\"Archdragon%20Peak\"&gt;Archdragon Peak&lt;/a&gt;. From the Dragon-Kin Mausoleum &lt;a href=\"Bonfire%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;bonfire&lt;/a&gt;, proceed up the nearby stairs and the spear can be obtained by interacting with the metal gate that leads to the courtyard below &lt;a href=\"the%20Nameless%20King\"&gt;the Nameless King&lt;/a&gt;'s arena.\nCharacteristics.\nThe Dragonslayer Spear possesses decent dexterity scaling and a long reach, but is quite heavy and requires a high amount of &lt;a href=\"Strength%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;strength&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Dexterity%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;dexterity&lt;/a&gt; to wield. However, its most unique trait is its innate &lt;a href=\"Lightning%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;lightning&lt;/a&gt; damage, which scales with &lt;a href=\"Faith%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;faith&lt;/a&gt;. This makes it a solid choice for players with dexterity and faith investment.\nThe Lightning Charge functions much like the standard &lt;a href=\"Charge\"&gt;Charge&lt;/a&gt; skill, but with a lightning projectile being fired at the end of it. Aside from the advantage of a ranged attack, this move can also deal massive amounts of damage when the final thrust and projectile hit the same target.\nMoveset.\n&lt;br&gt;\nUpgrades.\n&lt;br&gt;"}
{"id": "130632", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=130632", "title": "Dragonslayer Swordspear", "text": "The Dragonslayer Swordspear is a &lt;a href=\"Boss%20Soul%20Items%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;soul-transposed&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Spears%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;spear&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nObtained by transposing the &lt;a href=\"Soul%20of%20the%20Nameless%20King\"&gt;Soul of the Nameless King&lt;/a&gt; with &lt;a href=\"Ludleth%20of%20Courland\"&gt;Ludleth of Courland&lt;/a&gt; for 10,000 &lt;a href=\"Soul%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;souls&lt;/a&gt;.\nCharacteristics.\nThe Dragonslayer Swordspear is a unique weapon with a different playstyle from other polearms.\nAs a cross spear, it is designed to allow for sweeping and thrusting attacks, giving it great versatility whether fighting single foes or multiple opponents, and whether in narrow corridors or in open fields. Choosing between the weak and strong attacks allows the wielder to perform both types of attacks, regardless of one-handing or two-handing the weapon.\nThe Dragonslayer Swordspear also requires a particular set of stats to wield effectively. Despite having respectable &lt;a href=\"Faith%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Faith&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Parameter%20Bonus%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;scaling&lt;/a&gt;, the base &lt;a href=\"Lightning%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Lightning&lt;/a&gt; damage is rather lackluster, negating any Faith invested. However, this Lightning damage can be augmented by performing its &lt;a href=\"skill\"&gt;skill&lt;/a&gt;, launching a bolt at a distant target while buffing the weapon. This, combined with its moderate physical scaling, makes the Swordspear best suited for quality builds that invest points into Faith for utility &lt;a href=\"Miracle%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Miracles&lt;/a&gt;, and less so for high Faith builds that invest little into &lt;a href=\"Strength%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Strength&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Dexterity%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Dexterity&lt;/a&gt;.\nHowever, the Dragonslayer Swordspear's most interesting quirk is that it is the only spear in the game with &lt;a href=\"Hyper%20Armor\"&gt;Hyper Armor&lt;/a&gt;, meaning that unlike its brethren it can take advantage of &lt;a href=\"Poise%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Poise&lt;/a&gt;. Caution should be exercised though, as it still has the weakest Poise health out of all weapons in the game, placing it below halberds."}
{"id": "2415", "revid": "56333033", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=2415", "title": "Drake Sword", "text": "The Drake Sword is a &lt;a href=\"Straight%20Swords%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;straight sword&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nThe Drake Sword is obtainable in the &lt;a href=\"Undead%20Parish\"&gt;Undead Parish&lt;/a&gt;. To obtain the sword, the player must deal 240 damage when in the base game cycle to the &lt;a href=\"Hellkite%20Dragon\"&gt;Hellkite Dragon&lt;/a&gt;'s tail to sever it, placing the sword in their inventory. One method of doing this is to stand on the right side of the bridge under the drake and shoot its tail with a &lt;a href=\"bow\"&gt;bow&lt;/a&gt;. Another method is to simply wait for the dragon to land, run to the right side and attack the tail a few times. This is best done with a weapon that is at least +5. The drake's tail will respawn, but the sword can only be obtained once per playthrough.\nCharacteristics.\nThe Drake Sword entirely lacks Stat Scaling and is hard to upgrade making it a weak pick even in the early game. Once the player has upgraded their weapon to &lt;a href=\"Standard%20%28upgrade%20path%29\"&gt;Standard&lt;/a&gt; +5 quite a few weapons picked up before or just after Drake Sword will be comparable or entirely out damage its 200 AR at +0. Take for instance &lt;a href=\"Zweihander\"&gt;Zweihander&lt;/a&gt;, at minimum stats to wield two-handed at +5 it will have 257 AR which immediately out performs Drake Sword. &lt;a href=\"Claymore\"&gt;Claymore&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Halberd\"&gt;Halberd&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Reinforced%20Club\"&gt;Reinforced Club&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Club\"&gt;Club&lt;/a&gt; will all deal comparable damage to Drake Sword at +5 with the minimum stats to two-hand each weapon. Drake Sword is not worth the arrows used to cut the Hellkite Drake's tail and should not be acquired outside of it being needed for the &lt;a href=\"Knight%27s%20Honor\"&gt;Knight's Honor&lt;/a&gt; Achievement since all Standard path weapons are able to be upgraded to +5 almost immediately upon entry into &lt;a href=\"Undead%20Parish\"&gt;Undead Parish&lt;/a&gt; and meeting &lt;a href=\"Andre%20of%20Astora\"&gt;Andre of Astora&lt;/a&gt;. \nThe Drake Sword upgrades quite poorly, gaining 20 base damage per upgrade, costing 10,000 souls and requiring rare &lt;a href=\"Dragon%20Scale\"&gt;Dragon Scale&lt;/a&gt;s. This is less of an increase in base damage than even the low base damage &lt;a href=\"Dagger\"&gt;Dagger&lt;/a&gt; gains when going from +0 to +5, a process which costs 7,700 souls, if all &lt;a href=\"Titanite%20Shard\"&gt;materials&lt;/a&gt; are purchased. Furthermore, base damage is used in the calculation for scaling, and upgrades to scaling weapons may also increase the parameter bonus directly, making the gap in damage even larger in practice.\nWhen wielded with both hands, the strong attack unleashes a ranged vertical cleave (similar to the Stormruler from \"&lt;a href=\"Demon%27s%20Souls\"&gt;Demon's Souls&lt;/a&gt;\") at the cost of 30 weapon &lt;a href=\"durability\"&gt;durability&lt;/a&gt;, degrading and then breaking the weapon quickly. Unlike most dragon weapons, the Drake Sword cannot be &lt;a href=\"Weapon%20Augmentation\"&gt;enchanted&lt;/a&gt;. It grants 15 points of &lt;a href=\"Fire%20%28damage%20type%29\"&gt;Flame&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Magic%20%28damage%20type%29\"&gt;Magic&lt;/a&gt; Defense when wielded. This effect remains active when in the off-hand and two handing a weapon in the right. "}
