{"id": "135825", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=135825", "title": "Drakeblood Gauntlets (Dark Souls III)", "text": "The Drakeblood Gauntlets are in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\". They are part of the &lt;a href=\"Drakeblood%20Set%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Drakeblood Set&lt;/a&gt;.\nAvailability.\nFound in the &lt;a href=\"Consumed%20King%27s%20Garden\"&gt;Consumed King's Garden&lt;/a&gt;, on the corpse that teaches the &lt;a href=\"Gestures%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Path of the Dragon&lt;/a&gt; gesture. For it to appear, the player must first defeat at least one &lt;a href=\"Drakeblood%20Knight%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Drakeblood Knight&lt;/a&gt; at &lt;a href=\"Archdragon%20Peak\"&gt;Archdragon Peak&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "83317", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=83317", "title": "Drakeblood Greatsword", "text": "The Drakeblood Greatsword is a &lt;a href=\"Greatswords%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;greatsword&lt;/a&gt; in \"\".\nAvailability.\nLocated on a corpse in the &lt;a href=\"Dragon%27s%20Sanctum\"&gt;Dragon's Sanctum&lt;/a&gt;. The corpse is found shortly after the &lt;a href=\"Lair%20of%20the%20Imperfect\"&gt;Lair of the Imperfect&lt;/a&gt; bonfire, on the small piece of dry land, past an elevator leading to the first bonfire of &lt;a href=\"Shulva\"&gt;Shulva&lt;/a&gt;.\nCharacteristics.\nThe Drakeblood Greatsword is a well-balanced &lt;a href=\"Greatswords%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;greatsword&lt;/a&gt;; it has relatively low requirements, boasts a very versatile &lt;a href=\"Moveset%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;moveset&lt;/a&gt; of &lt;a href=\"Slash%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;slash&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Thrust%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;thrust&lt;/a&gt; attacks, and is one of the &lt;a href=\"Weight\"&gt;lighter&lt;/a&gt; greatswords found in the game.\nAlthough most of its damage draws from the player's &lt;a href=\"Dexterity%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Dexterity&lt;/a&gt; pool, the &lt;a href=\"Magic%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;magic&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Lightning%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;lightning&lt;/a&gt; damage also allow players to deal \"chip damage\" through an enemy's guard, making it a suitable choice against defensive opponents. It is also fully-buffable with &lt;a href=\"Spells%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;spells&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"resins\"&gt;resins&lt;/a&gt;, and the very high counterstrength allows the weapon to deal astronomical damage when paired with the &lt;a href=\"Old%20Leo%20Ring\"&gt;Old Leo Ring&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe only two drawbacks are it can only be pillaged from a corpse in the \"&lt;a href=\"Crown%20of%20the%20Sunken%20King\"&gt;Crown of the Sunken King&lt;/a&gt;\" expansion, and it requires &lt;a href=\"petrified%20dragon%20bone\"&gt;petrified dragon bone&lt;/a&gt;s in order to be upgraded."}
{"id": "132928", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=132928", "title": "Drakeblood Greatsword (Dark Souls III)", "text": "The Drakeblood Greatsword is a &lt;a href=\"Greatswords%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;greatsword&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nFound in &lt;a href=\"Archdragon%20Peak\"&gt;Archdragon Peak&lt;/a&gt;. Guaranteed drop from the first &lt;a href=\"Drakeblood%20Knight%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Drakeblood Knight&lt;/a&gt; spawned by the &lt;a href=\"Man%20Serpent%20Summoner\"&gt;Man Serpent Summoner&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"Archdragon%20Peak%23Bonfires\"&gt;Dragon-Kin Mausoleum&lt;/a&gt;.\nCharacteristics.\nThe Drakeblood Greatsword is a very unique weapon with several properties that set it apart from all of its peers.\nIt deals innate &lt;a href=\"Magic%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Magic&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Lightning%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Lightning&lt;/a&gt; damage, making it a very useful tool for chipping through the &lt;a href=\"Shields%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;shields&lt;/a&gt; of enemies; on top of this, it can still be buffed or &lt;a href=\"Infusion%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;infused&lt;/a&gt;, greatly increasing its flexibility. However, it also has very poor physical scaling, so the split-damage nature of the weapon combined with its low physical damage means that each individual strike of the weapon does not deal as much damage as its high attack rating would otherwise indicate. Conversely, however, this split damage is greatly amplified when performing a critical attack, easily overwhelming a target's flat defenses from multiple fronts. Combined with its &lt;a href=\"Stance%20%28Greatsword%29\"&gt;Stance&lt;/a&gt; skill, the Drakeblood Greatsword is a very dangerous threat against shield-carrying opponents, as it can either damage enemies through their raised shields or knock it aside with a guard break for heavily damaging &lt;a href=\"Critical%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;ripostes&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe Drakeblood Greatsword also has the unfortunate distinction of being one of the shortest greatswords in the game, having less reach than even &lt;a href=\"Straight%20Swords%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;straight swords&lt;/a&gt; like the &lt;a href=\"Gotthard%20Twinswords\"&gt;Gotthard Twinswords&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Ringed%20Knight%20Straight%20Sword\"&gt;Ringed Knight Straight Sword&lt;/a&gt;. This makes it difficult to use against opponents who are good at outspacing the weapon. To counter this, however, it also possesses a moveset that blends the attacks of the &lt;a href=\"Bastard%20Sword%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Bastard Sword&lt;/a&gt; with those of the &lt;a href=\"Hollowslayer%20Greatsword\"&gt;Hollowslayer Greatsword&lt;/a&gt;. In particular, it shares the two-handed weak attacks of the Hollowslayer Greatsword, meaning that after the first swing, it gains almost immediate &lt;a href=\"Hyper%20Armor\"&gt;Hyper Armor&lt;/a&gt; which allows it to out-trade any smaller weapons that attempt to punish its short reach.\nOverall, the Drakeblood Greatsword possesses many intrinsic advantages that makes it very strong in the hands of a build that does not prioritize physical damage. Its innate elemental damage, combined with its ability to be buffed or infused, make it a force to be reckoned with when buffed with &lt;a href=\"Lightning%20Blade\"&gt;Lightning Blade&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Darkmoon%20Blade%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Darkmoon Blade&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Crystal%20Magic%20Weapon%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Crystal Magic Weapon&lt;/a&gt;, or when infused with any number of elemental gems to amplify its damage output."}
{"id": "83767", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=83767", "title": "Drakeblood Helm", "text": "The Drakeblood Helm is a piece in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\". It is part of the &lt;a href=\"Drakeblood%20Set\"&gt;Drakeblood Set&lt;/a&gt;.\nAvailability.\nFound on a body in the &lt;a href=\"Dragon%27s%20Sanctum\"&gt;Dragon's Sanctum&lt;/a&gt;, in a large, descending room before fighting &lt;a href=\"Elana%2C%20the%20Squalid%20Queen\"&gt;Elana, the Squalid Queen&lt;/a&gt;. It is in a room with six empty, opened iron chests, against a wall to the left."}
{"id": "135823", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=135823", "title": "Drakeblood Helm (Dark Souls III)", "text": "The Drakeblood Helm is a piece in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\". It is part of the &lt;a href=\"Drakeblood%20Set%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Drakeblood Set&lt;/a&gt;.\nAvailability.\nFound in the &lt;a href=\"Consumed%20King%27s%20Garden\"&gt;Consumed King's Garden&lt;/a&gt;, on the corpse that teaches the &lt;a href=\"Gestures%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Path of the Dragon&lt;/a&gt; gesture. For it to appear, the player must first defeat at least one &lt;a href=\"Drakeblood%20Knight%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Drakeblood Knight&lt;/a&gt; at &lt;a href=\"Archdragon%20Peak\"&gt;Archdragon Peak&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "84954", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=84954", "title": "Drakeblood Knight", "text": "Drakeblood Knights are &lt;a href=\"Enemies%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;enemies&lt;/a&gt; in .\nLore.\nThe Drakeblood Knights, who worshiped the blood of &lt;a href=\"dragons\"&gt;dragons&lt;/a&gt;, were led by &lt;a href=\"Sir%20Yorgh\"&gt;Sir Yorgh&lt;/a&gt; in a siege of the &lt;a href=\"Eternal%20Sanctum\"&gt;Eternal Sanctum&lt;/a&gt;, but sunk into the Sanctum when the &lt;a href=\"Sinh%2C%20the%20Slumbering%20Dragon\"&gt;sleeping dragon&lt;/a&gt; awoke. The red cloth wrapped around their black armor represents the sacred blood of dragons. The insignia chiseled upon their &lt;a href=\"Drakeblood%20Greatsword\"&gt;sword&lt;/a&gt; hilt symbolizes dragon's blood. To the Drakeblood Knights, fresh dragon blood was sacrosanct. They believed that by obtaining it, they could achieve a true understanding of life, transcending their own banal existence.\nDescription.\nDrakeblood Knights are suited in the &lt;a href=\"Drakeblood%20Set\"&gt;Drakeblood Set&lt;/a&gt; with matching &lt;a href=\"Drakeblood%20Greatsword\"&gt;Drakeblood Greatsword&lt;/a&gt;, as well as a &lt;a href=\"Spirit%20Tree%20Shield\"&gt;Spirit Tree Shield&lt;/a&gt;. They are player-sized, and fight similar to A.I. red phantoms, swapping between one-handing and two-handing their weapon and rolling.\nStrategy.\nA &lt;a href=\"Greatshields%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;greatshield&lt;/a&gt; with good &lt;a href=\"stability\"&gt;stability&lt;/a&gt; (like the &lt;a href=\"Havel%27s%20Greatshield%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Havel's Greatshield&lt;/a&gt;) is very useful against Drakeblood Knights, as they will &lt;a href=\"stagger\"&gt;stagger&lt;/a&gt; every time they hit it, giving the player ample time to &lt;a href=\"counterattack\"&gt;counterattack&lt;/a&gt;. They will occasionally try to perform a &lt;a href=\"guard%20break\"&gt;guard break&lt;/a&gt;, but if the player is well built in both &lt;a href=\"Endurance%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Endurance&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Poise%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Poise&lt;/a&gt;, they will only be slightly staggered but manage to keep their shield up. Additionally, even if the guard break was successful, the Drakeblood Knight usually won't follow it by attacking immediately."}
{"id": "142568", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=142568", "title": "Drakeblood Knight (Dark Souls III)", "text": "Drakeblood Knights are in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nDescription.\nDrakeblood Knights make a return from their appearance in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;: &lt;a href=\"Crown%20of%20the%20Sunken%20King\"&gt;Crown of the Sunken King&lt;/a&gt;\". They are clad in the &lt;a href=\"Drakeblood%20Set%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Drakeblood Set&lt;/a&gt; and come armed with the &lt;a href=\"Drakeblood%20Greatsword%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Drakeblood Greatsword&lt;/a&gt; and the &lt;a href=\"Spirit%20Tree%20Crest%20Shield\"&gt;Spirit Tree Crest Shield&lt;/a&gt;. Their greatsword deals both &lt;a href=\"Magic%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Magic&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Lightning%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Lightning&lt;/a&gt; damage, so they can still inflict some damage through shields. They boast a vast amount of vitality, but their combat tactics are quite predictable and easily avoided.\nThey appear exclusively as summons by the first &lt;a href=\"Man%20Serpent%20Summoner\"&gt;Man Serpent Summoner&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Archdragon%20Peak\"&gt;Archdragon Peak&lt;/a&gt; and their appearance in &lt;a href=\"Lothric\"&gt;Lothric&lt;/a&gt; is not given much explanation other than they were worshippers of dragons and Archdragon Peak is a sanctuary known for those kind of cults.\nLocation.\nFound in &lt;a href=\"Archdragon%20Peak\"&gt;Archdragon Peak&lt;/a&gt; only as summons from the first &lt;a href=\"Man%20Serpent%20Summoner\"&gt;Man Serpent Summoner&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"Archdragon%20Peak%23Bonfires\"&gt;Dragon-Kin Mausoleum&lt;/a&gt;. The summoner can call in Drakeblood Knights infinitely, although only one at a time. Once the summoner is dead, the last knight summoned will remain and he can then be killed permanently.\nLore.\nAn order of knights who venerate dragon blood. The blade of their swords is engraved with script symbolizing dragon blood. Drakeblood Knights were worshippers of the blood of dragons and the red cloth that decorates their garments is said to symbolize their yearning for blood. In ages past they laid siege to a &lt;a href=\"Shulva%2C%20Sanctum%20City\"&gt;city&lt;/a&gt; in order to kill the &lt;a href=\"Sinh%2C%20the%20Slumbering%20Dragon\"&gt;slumbering dragon&lt;/a&gt; that slept there believing its blood would grant them true understanding of life. Led by &lt;a href=\"Sir%20Yorgh\"&gt;Sir Yorgh&lt;/a&gt; they managed to kill the &lt;a href=\"Sunken%20King\"&gt;king&lt;/a&gt; of the city. However, when Yorgh attempted to kill the dragon with his spear, it awakened and spewed a cloud of toxic gas that enveloped the city, killing Sir Yorgh as well as most of the inhabitants and Drakeblood Knights.\nIt is said that dragon worship has captured the hearts and minds of warriors across the lands for many ages.\nStrategy.\nEven when Drakeblood Knights don't have the same rolling penalty they had in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\", they are much easier to defeat this time around. They boast a very high amount of health and can inflict both &lt;a href=\"Magic%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Magic&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Lightning%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Lightning&lt;/a&gt; damage through shields, however, so they should not be underestimated.\nThey come armed with the &lt;a href=\"Spirit%20Tree%20Crest%20Shield\"&gt;Spirit Tree Crest Shield&lt;/a&gt;, which grants them high defense against &lt;a href=\"Lightning%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;lightning&lt;/a&gt;-based attacks, although they rarely use it and instead prefer to hold their greatswords with both hands. Their attacks are slow and amply telegraphed, and they usually don't chain more than three swings, which allow the player to counterattack without taking too much risk once they finish a combo.\nThey frequently attempt to use the &lt;a href=\"Stance%20%28Greatsword%29\"&gt;Stance&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"skill\"&gt;skill&lt;/a&gt; with their weapons, which the player can use to their advantage by luring them into swinging and missing in order to score some hits.\nFarming.\nSince Drakeblood Knights spawn infinitely and yield a base amount of 4,000 &lt;a href=\"Souls%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;souls&lt;/a&gt;, they can be used for farming. By equipping the &lt;a href=\"Symbol%20of%20Avarice%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Symbol of Avarice&lt;/a&gt;, the &lt;a href=\"Shield%20of%20Want\"&gt;Shield of Want&lt;/a&gt;, the &lt;a href=\"Hornet%20Ring%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Hornet Ring&lt;/a&gt;, the &lt;a href=\"Slumbering%20Dragoncrest%20Ring%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Slumbering Dragoncrest Ring&lt;/a&gt;, and the &lt;a href=\"Covetous%20Silver%20Serpent%20Ring%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Covetous Silver Serpent Ring&lt;/a&gt; (and perhaps also &lt;a href=\"Aldrich%27s%20Ruby\"&gt;Aldrich's Ruby&lt;/a&gt; to alleviate some of the &lt;a href=\"HP%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;HP&lt;/a&gt; drain produced by the Symbol of Avarice), the player can maximize the amount of souls acquired for each knight killed.\nThe player just needs to stand behind their spawning spot and begin combat with a &lt;a href=\"Critical%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;backstab&lt;/a&gt;, the &lt;a href=\"Slumbering%20Dragoncrest%20Ring%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Slumbering Dragoncrest Ring&lt;/a&gt; will ensure they don't turn hostile prematurely and the &lt;a href=\"Hornet%20Ring%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Hornet Ring&lt;/a&gt; will increase the damage dealt, allowing the player to kill them with only a few more hits. Each knight defeated will yield 7,000+ souls and the process can be repeated as many times as necessary.\nCaution must be taken if the &lt;a href=\"Man%20Serpent%20Summoner\"&gt;Man Serpent Summoner&lt;/a&gt; summons &lt;a href=\"Havel%20the%20Rock%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Havel&lt;/a&gt;, though, in which case it's best to make haste to the nearby &lt;a href=\"Bonfire%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;bonfire&lt;/a&gt; and try again. If the true Havel has already been defeated, then the Summoner will only be able to summon Drakeblood Knights, allowing the farming process to continue without interruptions."}
{"id": "83771", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=83771", "title": "Drakeblood Leggings", "text": "The Drakeblood Leggings are a piece in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\".They are part of the &lt;a href=\"Drakeblood%20Set\"&gt;Drakeblood Set&lt;/a&gt;.\nAvailability.\nFound on a body in the\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Dragon%27s%20Sanctum\"&gt;Dragon's Sanctum&lt;/a&gt;, in a large, descending room before fighting &lt;a href=\"Elana%2C%20the%20Squalid%20Queen\"&gt;Elana, the Squalid Queen&lt;/a&gt;. It is in a room with six empty, opened iron chests, against a wall to the left."}
