{"id": "83761", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=83761", "title": "Drakeblood Set", "text": "The Drakeblood Set\u00a0is a &lt;a href=\"Medium%20Armor%20Sets%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;medium armor set&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Crown%20of%20the%20Sunken%20King\"&gt;Dark Souls II: Crown of the Sunken King&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nFound on a body in the &lt;a href=\"Dragon%27s%20Sanctum\"&gt;Dragon's Sanctum&lt;/a&gt;, in a large, descending room before fighting &lt;a href=\"Elana%2C%20the%20Squalid%20Queen\"&gt;Elana, the Squalid Queen&lt;/a&gt;. It is on a body in a room with five empty, opened iron chests, against a wall to the left.\nCharacteristics.\nThe Drakeblood set has very high defenses, most notably against &lt;a href=\"Slash%20%28damage%20type%29\"&gt;slash&lt;/a&gt; attacks, &lt;a href=\"Dark%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Dark&lt;/a&gt; damage, and &lt;a href=\"Fire%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Fire&lt;/a&gt; damage, but upgrades poorly to compensate. It is also one of the heaviest of the medium armor sets, with a weight of 29.6 units, being only a fraction of a unit (0.1) heavier than &lt;a href=\"Benhart%27s%20Set\"&gt;Benhart's Set&lt;/a&gt;, but lighter than the &lt;a href=\"Gyrm%20Set\"&gt;Gyrm Set&lt;/a&gt;.\nIt upgrades with regular &lt;a href=\"Titanite%20Shard%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;titanite&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "130418", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=130418", "title": "Drakeblood Set (Dark Souls III)", "text": "The Drakeblood Set is a &lt;a href=\"Heavy%20Armor%20Sets%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;heavy armor set&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nFound in the &lt;a href=\"Consumed%20King%27s%20Garden\"&gt;Consumed King's Garden&lt;/a&gt;, on the corpse that teaches the &lt;a href=\"Gestures%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Path of the Dragon&lt;/a&gt; gesture. For it to appear, the player must first defeat at least one &lt;a href=\"Drakeblood%20Knight%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Drakeblood Knight&lt;/a&gt; at &lt;a href=\"Archdragon%20Peak\"&gt;Archdragon Peak&lt;/a&gt;.\nCharacteristics.\nThe Drakeblood Set is arguably one of the most well-balanced heavy armor sets found within the game.\nIt boasts a consistent damage absorption across the chart due to its high physical and elemental absorptions. Unusually for a plate armor set, it is not weak to &lt;a href=\"Strike%20%28damage%20type%29\"&gt;Strike&lt;/a&gt; damage, which gives it a very useful advantage over other sets. Although it does have a weakness against &lt;a href=\"Lightning%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Lightning&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Dark%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Dark&lt;/a&gt; damage, it is not far out of line with its other resistances.\nThe most unique aspect of this armor set is its high resistance to &lt;a href=\"Slash%20%28damage%20type%29\"&gt;Slash&lt;/a&gt; damage and &lt;a href=\"Bleed%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Bleed&lt;/a&gt; buildup. In this way it is similar to the &lt;a href=\"Eastern%20Set%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Eastern Set&lt;/a&gt;, making it very strong against weapons like &lt;a href=\"Katanas%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Katanas&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Curved%20Greatswords%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Curved Greatswords&lt;/a&gt;, although it is much heavier in return for providing strong defenses against other sources of damage.\nThe cost for all these strong across-the-board defenses is that the Drakeblood Set has a sub-optimal &lt;a href=\"Poise%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;poise&lt;/a&gt;-to-weight ratio. While it can comfortably wield heavier weapons and trade using &lt;a href=\"Hyper%20Armor\"&gt;Hyper Armor&lt;/a&gt;, it is less adept in this field than many other heavy armor sets."}
{"id": "55941", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=55941", "title": "Drakekeeper", "text": "Drakekeepers are in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nLocation.\nThese enemies are fought in &lt;a href=\"Dragon%20Shrine\"&gt;Dragon Shrine&lt;/a&gt;.\nDescription.\nA large warrior, about the size of an &lt;a href=\"Old%20Knight\"&gt;Old Knight&lt;/a&gt;, clad in heavy black armor, wielding either a &lt;a href=\"Drakekeeper%27s%20Sword\"&gt;sword&lt;/a&gt;, an &lt;a href=\"Drakekeeper%27s%20Ultra%20Greatsword\"&gt;ultra greatsword&lt;/a&gt;, a &lt;a href=\"Drakekeeper%27s%20Great%20Hammer\"&gt;great hammer&lt;/a&gt;, or a &lt;a href=\"Drakekeeper%27s%20Warpick\"&gt;warpick&lt;/a&gt;. The ones with a sword also carry a &lt;a href=\"Drakekeeper%27s%20Shield\"&gt;shield&lt;/a&gt;, while the ones with a warpick carry a &lt;a href=\"Greatshield%20of%20Glory\"&gt;greatshield&lt;/a&gt;.\nGeneral information.\nMost Drakekeepers, namely the ones with a greatsword, ultra greatsword, or great hammer, have similar attack patterns to their Old Knight counterparts, except faster. They do have some new attacks, though. However, the warpick knights have their own unique movesets.\nAll of the movesets are described below:\nGreatsword:These drakekeepers have the same three-four part attack that Old Knights have, except faster. When the player is near them, they can also stab the player behind their shields. When the player is far from them, they can do a downward slash which releases soul arrow-type effect. This attack has a slow attack animation, so it is easy to spot coming.\nUltra Greatsword:These enemies mainly do a very quick vertical slash, and then a slower horizontal slash. Their downward slashes ignore shields, but don't deal much damage.\nGreat Hammer:The ones with great hammers are easily the most dangerous. They have the same attack pattern as their Old Knights counterparts, except faster but also with less vulnerability time after attacking. They have three attacks: a running attack, three horizontal strikes, one powerful overhead swing, or two vertical strikes. However, they do surprisingly little stamina damage. The singular overhead attack has a long windup compared to their other attacks and offers the best chance to circle around and attack. They can spam the three horizontal attacks into three to four strings or until the player is knocked out of range. If you must heal, flee and do it from around a corner or beyond their retreat point.\nDrakekeeper's Warpick:These drakekeepers have several attacks which include an blockable shield bash that instantly stun-lock if unblocked as well as a three-part strike attack with their weapon. Strangely enough, for such a large shield, their shield has very little physical damage reduction."}
{"id": "52379", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=52379", "title": "Drakekeeper's Great Hammer", "text": "The Drakekeeper's Great Hammer is a &lt;a href=\"Great%20Hammers%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;great hammer&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nDrops from the great hammer-wielding &lt;a href=\"Drakekeeper\"&gt;Drakekeeper&lt;/a&gt;s in\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Dragon%20Shrine\"&gt;Dragon Shrine&lt;/a&gt;.\nCharacteristics.\nThe Drakekeeper's Great Hammer is arguably one of the best &lt;a href=\"Great%20Hammers%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Great Hammers&lt;/a&gt; in the game. It has the same damage and overall stats as the &lt;a href=\"Demon%27s%20Great%20Hammer%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Demon's Great Hammer&lt;/a&gt;, with less &lt;a href=\"weight\"&gt;weight&lt;/a&gt; and more &lt;a href=\"durability\"&gt;durability&lt;/a&gt;, but also slightly less reach.\nCompared to the Demon's Great Hammer, it also upgrades with normal &lt;a href=\"Titanite%20Chunk%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Titanite&lt;/a&gt; instead of\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Twinkling%20Titanite%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Twinkling Titanite&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "51000", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=51000", "title": "Drakekeeper's Greataxe", "text": "The Drakekeeper's Greataxe is a &lt;a href=\"Greataxes%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;greataxe&lt;/a&gt; in\u00a0\"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nFound in a chest in &lt;a href=\"Dragon%20Shrine\"&gt;Dragon Shrine&lt;/a&gt;, along with\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Drakekeeper%27s%20Greatshield\"&gt;Drakekeeper's Greatshield&lt;/a&gt;.\nRare drop from &lt;a href=\"Kobold\"&gt;Kobold&lt;/a&gt;s in the &lt;a href=\"Shaded%20Woods\"&gt;Shaded Woods&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Aldia%27s%20Keep\"&gt;Aldia's Keep&lt;/a&gt;.\nCharacteristics.\nAlthough the Drakekeeper's Axe is neither the most powerful, nor the longest greataxe, it is indeed amongst the most versatile, especially for those looking for greataxes that have a varied moveset, high damage, long reach, and yet a very manageable &lt;a href=\"weight\"&gt;weight&lt;/a&gt;, as it is the lightest greataxe with a heavy greataxe moveset.\nIt is important to note that its moveset is almost identical to the &lt;a href=\"Crypt%20Blacksword\"&gt;Crypt Blacksword&lt;/a&gt; with the exception of the two-handed strong attack combo, which is that of a &lt;a href=\"Great%20Hammers%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Great Hammer&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe fact that this weapon aside from having increased &lt;a href=\"durability\"&gt;durability&lt;/a&gt; (as all Drakekeeper weapons do), and its regular &lt;a href=\"Titanite%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Titanite&lt;/a&gt; upgrade path, makes it a very easy to use and master."}
{"id": "51001", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=51001", "title": "Drakekeeper's Greatshield", "text": "The\u00a0Drakekeeper's Greatshield\u00a0is a\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Greatshields%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;greatshield&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nFound in a chest in\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Dragon%20Shrine\"&gt;Dragon Shrine&lt;/a&gt;, along with the &lt;a href=\"Drakekeeper%27s%20Greataxe\"&gt;Drakekeeper's Greataxe&lt;/a&gt;.\nCharacteristics.\nThis greatshield possesses some of the highest elemental defenses and status resistances, surpassed only by &lt;a href=\"Havel%27s%20Greatshield%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Havel's Greatshield&lt;/a&gt; in sheer versatility. However, although Havel's Greatshield outperforms this one in many areas, the Drakekeeper's Greatshield is significantly lighter, requiring much less investment in &lt;a href=\"Vitality%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Vitality&lt;/a&gt;.\nIt is useful in &lt;a href=\"Player%20versus%20Player%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;PvP&lt;/a&gt;, as it can, in most cases, completely negate the damage from &lt;a href=\"Homing%20Soulmass%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Homing Soulmass&lt;/a&gt;, as well as &lt;a href=\"Affinity\"&gt;Affinity&lt;/a&gt;.\nAll in all, this greatshield proves a useful means of defense, albeit a heavy one."}
{"id": "51003", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=51003", "title": "Drakekeeper's Shield", "text": "The Drakekeeper's Shield is a &lt;a href=\"Medium%20Shields%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;medium shield&lt;/a&gt; in\u00a0\"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nDrops from the sword and shield &lt;a href=\"Drakekeeper\"&gt;Drakekeeper&lt;/a&gt;s in\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Dragon%20Shrine\"&gt;Dragon Shrine&lt;/a&gt;.\nCharacteristics.\nThis &lt;a href=\"Shields%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;shield&lt;/a&gt; should be looked at as an improved version of the &lt;a href=\"Old%20Knight%27s%20Shield\"&gt;Old Knight's Shield&lt;/a&gt;, one such version that is in fact the polar opposite in terms of &lt;a href=\"durability\"&gt;durability&lt;/a&gt;, being capable of sustaining 4 times the damage the Old Knight Shield would be able to sustain before breaking, it is also slightly &lt;a href=\"Weight\"&gt;lighter&lt;/a&gt; and has more balanced stats. It does, however, have lower &lt;a href=\"stability\"&gt;stability&lt;/a&gt;.\nOverall, it is widely regarded as one of the top tier medium shields in the game, rivaling the &lt;a href=\"King%27s%20Shield\"&gt;King's Shield&lt;/a&gt;, for having almost identical stats."}
{"id": "52380", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=52380", "title": "Drakekeeper's Sword", "text": "The Drakekeeper's Sword is a\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Straight%20Swords%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;straight sword&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nDrops from sword-and-shield wielding\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Drakekeeper\"&gt;Drakekeeper&lt;/a&gt;s\u00a0in\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Dragon%20Shrine\"&gt;Dragon Shrine&lt;/a&gt;.\nIn , there is only one of these Drakekeepers. It stands alone at the beginning of the area, making it safe to farm.\nCharacteristics.\nThe Drakekeeper's Sword utilizes the same &lt;a href=\"Moveset%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;moveset&lt;/a&gt; as the &lt;a href=\"Broadsword%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Broadsword&lt;/a&gt;, making it incapable of thrust attacks, and relying on strong slashes. However, it has far greater reach that rivals the &lt;a href=\"Fume%20Sword\"&gt;Fume Sword&lt;/a&gt; and even some &lt;a href=\"Greatswords%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;greatswords&lt;/a&gt;.\nThis sword is one of the heaviest straight swords in the game at a &lt;a href=\"weight\"&gt;weight&lt;/a&gt; of six units, but it is also exceptionally &lt;a href=\"durable\"&gt;durable&lt;/a&gt; and can go through long journeys without having the need to &lt;a href=\"Repair%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;repair&lt;/a&gt; it."}
{"id": "52392", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=52392", "title": "Drakekeeper's Ultra Greatsword", "text": "The Drakekeeper's Ultra Greatsword\u00a0is an &lt;a href=\"Ultra%20Greatswords%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;ultra greatsword&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nRare drop from the two-handed Ultra Greatsword wielding &lt;a href=\"Drakekeeper\"&gt;Drakekeeper&lt;/a&gt;s in &lt;a href=\"Dragon%20Shrine\"&gt;Dragon Shrine&lt;/a&gt;.\nCharacteristics.\nThe Drakekeeper's Ultra Greatsword is a hard-hitter that can prove useful for &lt;a href=\"Strength%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Strength&lt;/a&gt;-oriented players.\nOnce fully reinforced, this weapon has both high base damage and &lt;a href=\"Strength%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Strength&lt;/a&gt; scaling, allowing it to deal good damage with a capable user. The high damage combines well with its moveset, which is similar to more common Ultra Greatswords, such as the &lt;a href=\"Zweihander%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Zweihander&lt;/a&gt;. These qualities makes it usable in a range of different situations.\nAdditionally, it is by far the most durable weapon of its class, further reinforcing its usefulness as it can be used with little fear of it breaking, even when the player must spend a long time away from a &lt;a href=\"Bonfire%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Bonfire&lt;/a&gt;. In , this spot is taken by the &lt;a href=\"King%27s%20Ultra%20Greatsword\"&gt;King's Ultra Greatsword&lt;/a&gt; at a massive 220 durability.\nHowever, these strengths comes at a matching cost, as the weapon is shorter and heavier than the average weapon of its class. Despite its performance, these drawbacks can make or break the weapon."}
{"id": "52378", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=52378", "title": "Drakekeeper's Warpick", "text": "The Drakekeeper's Warpick is a &lt;a href=\"Great%20Hammers%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;great hammer&lt;/a&gt; in\u00a0\"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nDropped by the great hammer and shield wielding &lt;a href=\"Drakekeeper\"&gt;Drakekeeper&lt;/a&gt;s at &lt;a href=\"Dragon%20Shrine\"&gt;Dragon Shrine&lt;/a&gt;. It can also be dropped by the &lt;a href=\"Dark%20Spirit\"&gt;Dark Spirit&lt;/a&gt; guarding the entrance of &lt;a href=\"Drangleic%20Castle\"&gt;Drangleic Castle&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"NG%2B%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;NG+&lt;/a&gt;, near the two &lt;a href=\"golems\"&gt;golems&lt;/a&gt; that open the gate. However, it is a very rare drop from both enemies.\nCharacteristics.\nThough its description describes it as a Great Hammer, the only similarities it does share within that &lt;a href=\"Weapon%20Types%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;weapon category&lt;/a&gt; is its absurd heavy &lt;a href=\"weight\"&gt;weight&lt;/a&gt;, its high &lt;a href=\"Scaling%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;scaling&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Strength%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Strength&lt;/a&gt;, high Strength requirement, and &lt;a href=\"Strike%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;strike&lt;/a&gt; damage. However, the Drakekeeper's Warpick is nothing but the heaviest Halberd in the game.\nAll of its &lt;a href=\"Moveset%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;moves&lt;/a&gt; are that of heavier Halberds, and it has a sweet spot that must found to deal the most amount of damage.\nAs such, if this weapon were in the category of Halberds, as it should, it would be the highest damaging Halberd in the game, dealing upwards of 800 damage on ideal, sweet spot hits.\nAdditionally, due to the nature of Drakekeeper items, its &lt;a href=\"durability\"&gt;durability&lt;/a&gt; is the highest of its class."}
