{"id": "67645", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=67645", "title": "Drakekeeper Set", "text": "The Drakekeeper Set\u00a0is a &lt;a href=\"Heavy%20Armor%20Sets%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;heavy armor set&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nDropped by the &lt;a href=\"Drakekeeper\"&gt;Drakekeeper&lt;/a&gt;s of &lt;a href=\"Dragon%20Shrine\"&gt;Dragon Shrine&lt;/a&gt;.\nCharacteristics.\nThe Drakekeeper Set has great &lt;a href=\"physical\"&gt;physical&lt;/a&gt; defenses; however, it has average &lt;a href=\"Poise%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;poise&lt;/a&gt; for its heavy &lt;a href=\"weight\"&gt;weight&lt;/a&gt;, and generally low &lt;a href=\"elemental\"&gt;elemental&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Negative%20Status%20Effects%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;status&lt;/a&gt; resistances. On the bright side, it is one of the few heavy armor sets that does not require &lt;a href=\"Twinkling%20Titanite%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;twinkling titanite&lt;/a&gt; to upgrade, making this much more easy to reinforce."}
{"id": "47552", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=47552", "title": "Drakewing Ultra Greatsword", "text": "The Drakewing Ultra Greatsword is an &lt;a href=\"Ultra%20Greatswords%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;ultra greatsword&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nThe Drakewing Ultra Greatsword can be traded for with &lt;a href=\"Weaponsmith%20Ornifex\"&gt;Weaponsmith Ornifex&lt;/a&gt;, in exchange for 1,500 souls and the &lt;a href=\"Guardian%20Dragon%20Soul\"&gt;Guardian Dragon Soul&lt;/a&gt;.\nCharacteristics.\nThe Drakewing Ultra Greatsword is one of the lightest Ultra Greatswords (on par with the &lt;a href=\"Lost%20Sinner%27s%20Sword\"&gt;Lost Sinner's Sword&lt;/a&gt; and the &lt;a href=\"Zweihander%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Zweihander&lt;/a&gt;), weighing only 12 units. It shares most of its moveset with the Zweihander, and so players that are comfortable with it will feel right at home when wielding the Drakewing Ultra Greatsword.\nUnlike most Ultra Greatswords, this weapon's scaling is mainly focused on &lt;a href=\"Dexterity%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Dexterity&lt;/a&gt; builds, making it an interesting option among the generally light-weight Dexterity weapons. \nThe Drakewing Ultra Greatsword features a special attack which consumes durability every time it is used. When the two-handed heavy attack is used, a green, glowing orb will be shot from the tip of the blade, dealing physical damage that scales with Physical AR on impact.\nSimilar to other weapons with a projectile attack, the special attack will do considerably more damage if the weapon itself hits the target when it is executed, allowing players to deal massive damage with just one hit. Wearing a &lt;a href=\"Bracing%20Knuckle%20Ring\"&gt;Bracing Knuckle Ring&lt;/a&gt; will increase the number of times the special attack can be used before breaking the weapon.\nPerhaps the biggest downside of this weapon is that it is the shortest Ultra Greatsword in the game (tied in with the &lt;a href=\"Ivory%20King%20Ultra%20Greatsword\"&gt;Ivory King Ultra Greatsword&lt;/a&gt;), and so it has quite a limited reach. However, being an Ultra Greatsword, it still has high poise damage and will still easily stagger groups of enemies with just one swing. \nTrivia.\nThe weapon's inventory icon shows the wings folded out. However, the wings are only folded out during the two-handed strong attack."}
