{"id": "137656", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=137656", "title": "Drang Knight", "text": "The Drang Knights are a pair of &lt;a href=\"Enemies%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;enemy&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Characters%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;characters&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nDescription.\nTwo skillful knights clad in the &lt;a href=\"Drang%20Set\"&gt;Drang Set&lt;/a&gt;, one wielding &lt;a href=\"Drang%20Hammers\"&gt;paired hammers&lt;/a&gt;, and the other &lt;a href=\"Drang%20Twinspears\"&gt;twinspears&lt;/a&gt;. They can spot the player from a very long distance and will rush to attack at the same time.\nUsing paired weapons gives them the ability to unleash many successive hits and &lt;a href=\"stunlock\"&gt;stunlock&lt;/a&gt; the player with ease, potentially dealing high amounts of damage. They have very good tracking (most notorious with the knight wielding twinspears), which allows them to hit the player even at a considerable distance.\nThey will generally buff their weapons with &lt;a href=\"Dark%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Dark&lt;/a&gt; before starting combat.\nLocation.\nBoth knights await near the staircase at the far end of the big courtyard scattered with dead &lt;a href=\"Giant%20Slave\"&gt;Giant Slave&lt;/a&gt;s located after the &lt;a href=\"Irithyll%20of%20the%20Boreal%20Valley%23Bonfires\"&gt;Pontiff Sulyvahn&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Bonfire%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;bonfire&lt;/a&gt;.\nStrategy.\nFighting these enemies can be dangerous due to all the hindrances present in the area where they are encountered. Three &lt;a href=\"Deacon\"&gt;Deacon&lt;/a&gt;s will be constantly shooting quick homing fireballs from a floor above, and two supposedly dead &lt;a href=\"Giant%20Slave\"&gt;Giant Slave&lt;/a&gt;s will come to life and attack if approached. In addition, both Drang Knights will attack at the same time, even if only one was alerted.\nRather than confronting them head on, a safer strategy consists in entering a path located on the left side of the courtyard, where several &lt;a href=\"Irithyllian%20Slave\"&gt;Irithyllian Slave&lt;/a&gt;s are congregated; dispose of them first and then damage one of the knights with a ranged attack, thus luring them to fight in that enclosed area, away from the &lt;a href=\"Giant%20Slave\"&gt;giants&lt;/a&gt; and the &lt;a href=\"Deacon\"&gt;Deacon&lt;/a&gt;s' fire.\nYet another strategy consists in climbing up the nearby staircase and making way through the upper floor, dealing with all the &lt;a href=\"Deacon\"&gt;Deacon&lt;/a&gt;s first. Run around the knights from above and surprise them by the rearguard before they have a chance to react, perhaps even starting the battle with a &lt;a href=\"Critical%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;backstab&lt;/a&gt;. Use the nearby staircases strategically to attack and escape, and also consider using the ladder behind the nearby &lt;a href=\"Illusory%20Wall%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;illusory wall&lt;/a&gt; to hide and lure them to fall to their deaths."}
{"id": "134310", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=134310", "title": "Drang Set", "text": "The Drang Set is a &lt;a href=\"Light%20Armor%20Sets%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;light armor set&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nFound in the &lt;a href=\"Cathedral%20of%20the%20Deep\"&gt;Cathedral of the Deep&lt;/a&gt;, in the murky waters near the staircase that leads to the &lt;a href=\"Deacons%20of%20the%20Deep\"&gt;Deacons of the Deep&lt;/a&gt;. It is guarded by a &lt;a href=\"Giant%20Slave\"&gt;Giant Slave&lt;/a&gt;, several &lt;a href=\"Writhing%20Rotten%20Flesh\"&gt;Writhing Rotten Flesh&lt;/a&gt; and a &lt;a href=\"Man-grub\"&gt;Man-grub&lt;/a&gt;.\nCharacteristics.\nA rather lightweight set, the Drang Set provides respectable defenses for its &lt;a href=\"weight\"&gt;weight&lt;/a&gt;. It is quite strong against &lt;a href=\"elemental\"&gt;elemental&lt;/a&gt; damage, although it has a severe weakness to &lt;a href=\"Fire%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Fire&lt;/a&gt; damage, and furthermore does not provide any appreciable amount of &lt;a href=\"Poise%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Poise&lt;/a&gt; despite the weight."}
